'''Charles Marc Hervé Perceval Leclerc''' ({{IPA|fr|ʃaʁl(ə) ləklɛʁ}};{{efn|In this [[French name]], the final consonants in the forename and surname are silent: {{respell|SHARL|_|la|CLER}}.}} born 16 October 1997) is a Monégasque [[racing driver]] who competes in [[Formula One]] for [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]]. Leclerc was runner-up in the [[Formula One World Drivers' Championship]] in {{F1|2022}} with Ferrari, and has won {{Numbertoword|{{F1stat|LEC|wins}}}} [[Formula One Grands Prix|Grands Prix]] across eight seasons.

Born and raised in [[Monte Carlo]], Leclerc began competitive [[kart racing]] aged seven. After a successful karting career—culminating in his victory at the [[KF3|junior direct-drive]] [[Karting World Cup|World Cup]] in 2011—Leclerc graduated to [[junior formulae]]. Progressing directly to [[Formula Renault 2.0]], he finished runner-up to [[Nyck de Vries]] in the [[2014 Formula Renault 2.0 Alps Series|Alps Series]] and achieved several podium finishes in the [[2014 Eurocup Formula Renault 2.0|Eurocup]]. Leclerc graduated to [[FIA Formula 3 European Championship|FIA European Formula 3]] in {{FIAF3|2015}}, winning several races as he finished fourth in his rookie season. He won his first championship at the [[2016 GP3 Series]] with [[ART Grand Prix|ART]]. Leclerc then won the inaugural [[FIA Formula 2 Championship]] in {{F2|2017}} with [[Prema Racing|Prema]], becoming the fourth driver to win the [[GP2 Series|GP2]]/Formula 2 championship in their rookie season and breaking several records.{{efn-num|Including most wins in a season (7, shared with [[Stoffel Vandoorne]] and [[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]]), most pole positions in a season (8), most consecutive pole positions (6), and then-youngest champion (19 years, 356 days).}}

Leclerc made his Formula One debut in {{F1|2018}} with [[Sauber]] as part of the [[Ferrari Driver Academy]], scoring several points finishes in the [[Sauber C37|C37]]. He joined Ferrari for {{F1|2019}} to partner [[Sebastian Vettel]] and became the [[List of Formula One driver records#Youngest polesitters|second-youngest polesitter in Formula One history]] at the {{F1GP|2019|Bahrain}}; he took his maiden career [[List of Formula One Grand Prix winners|win]] in [[2019 Belgian Grand Prix|Belgium]], before ending Ferrari's record [[2010 Italian Grand Prix|nine-year drought]] at the {{F1GP|2019|Italian}}, which saw him nicknamed "'''il Predestinato'''" in Italian media.{{efn|{{lit|'''the [[Predestined]]'''}}}} After winless seasons for Ferrari in {{F1|2020}} and {{F1|2021}}, Leclerc took several victories and finished runner-up to [[Max Verstappen]] in the {{F1|2022}} World Drivers' Championship. Following five pole positions and six podiums in his {{F1|2023}} campaign, Leclerc won the {{F1GP|2024|Monaco}} in {{F1|2024}}, becoming the first Monégasque driver to win the race in [[1931 Monaco Grand Prix|93 years]]; he achieved further victories in [[2024 Italian Grand Prix|Italy]] and the [[2024 United States Grand Prix|United States]] as he finished third in the championship.

As of the {{Latest F1GP}}, Leclerc has achieved {{Numbertoword|{{F1stat|LEC|wins}}}} race wins, {{F1stat|LEC|fastestlaps}} fastest laps, and {{F1stat|LEC|podiums}} podiums in Formula One; he also holds [[List of Formula One driver records|the record]] for the [[List of Formula One driver records#Other driver records|most pole positions without a World Drivers' Championship]] ({{F1stat|LEC|poles}}). Leclerc is contracted to remain at Ferrari until at least the end of the 2026 season.<ref name="contract"/> Outside of motor racing, Leclerc collaborated with pianist [[Sofiane Pamart]] on an [[extended play]], ''[[Dreamers (EP)|Dreamers]]'' (2024), which peaked at number two on the ''[[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'' [[classical music|Classical Albums]] chart.

{{TOC limit|4}}
== Early life ==
[[File:Charles Leclerc after winning F2 championship (cropped3).jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc ''(left)'' with his mother, Pascale, after winning the [[2017 FIA Formula 2 Championship]]|alt=Leclerc holds his trophy after winning the FIA Formula 2 Championship, with his arm around his mother]]
Charles Marc Hervé Perceval Leclerc was born on 16 October 1997 in [[Monte Carlo]], Monaco.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.lofficielibiza.com/culture/clarles-leclerc-interview-who-is-a-formula-1-driver-private-life-photos |title=Charles Leclerc talks about his "Red Passion" |last=Croci |first=Roberto |date=24 December 2022 |magazine=[[L'Officiel Ibiza]] |publisher=[[AMTD Digital]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=0030-0403 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250116080040/https://www.lofficielibiza.com/culture/clarles-leclerc-interview-who-is-a-formula-1-driver-private-life-photos |archive-date=16 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/f1s-next-big-thing-getting-to-know-charles-leclerc.4dz5iYdAM8wkkgWyS02GaS |title=F1's next big thing? Getting to know Charles Leclerc |date=16 August 2017 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241113015044/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/f1s-next-big-thing-getting-to-know-charles-leclerc.4dz5iYdAM8wkkgWyS02GaS |archive-date=13 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> His father, Hervé Leclerc, was a racing driver who competed in [[Formula Three]] in the 1980s and 1990s,<ref name="HERVE">{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/charles-leclerc-interview-monaco-gp-monte-carlo-fathers-death-it-has-changed-me-as-a-person-a8369231.html |title=Charles Leclerc on his father's death: 'It has changed me as a person, and also how I see things now' |last=Tremayne |first=David |date=25 May 2018 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230827172131/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/charles-leclerc-interview-monaco-gp-monte-carlo-fathers-death-it-has-changed-me-as-a-person-a8369231.html |archive-date=27 August 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> whilst his mother, Pascale Leclerc<!-- ({{nee}} maiden name)-->, is a former [[hairdresser]] who operated a [[hair salon]] in [[Fontvieille, Monaco|Fontvieille]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.lesoir.be/373674/article/2021-05-21/formule-1-charles-leclerc-un-vrai-monegasque |url-access=subscription |title=Formule 1: Charles Leclerc, un «vrai» Monégasque |trans-title=Formula 1: Charles Leclerc, a "real" Monégasque |last=Dricot |first=Dominique |date=21 May 2021 |work=[[Le Soir]] |publisher=[[Rossel (company)|Rossel]] |language=fr |issn=1375-5668 |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222213002/https://www.lesoir.be/373674/article/2021-05-21/formule-1-charles-leclerc-un-vrai-monegasque |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> His paternal step-grandfather founded the [[Novares Group]], a French [[manufacturing]] company;<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cityam.com/charles-leclerc-the-story-behind-ferraris-monegasque-marvel/ |title=Charles Leclerc: The story behind Ferrari's Monegasque marvel |last=Hardy |first=Matt |date=8 April 2022 |work=[[City A.M.]] |publisher=[[THG plc]] |issn=2516-5453 |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240915133050/https://www.cityam.com/charles-leclerc-the-story-behind-ferraris-monegasque-marvel/ |archive-date=15 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he helped cover miscellaneous costs throughout his [[karting]] career, but not the racing itself.<ref name="MC2017">{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/the-next-big-thing-exclusive-f1-interview-with-ferraris-rising-star/3221749/ |title=The next big thing? – Exclusive F1 interview with Ferrari's rising star |date=17 July 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222205525/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/the-next-big-thing-exclusive-f1-interview-with-ferraris-rising-star/3221749/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc studied at the [[Lycée Albert Premier]] in [[Monaco-Ville]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.lalibre.be/sports/moteurs/2019/05/25/a-monaco-le-petit-prince-charles-leclerc-court-a-domicile-gagner-chez-moi-serait-incroyable-JPD4YVOIVJBU3HWFA2MOTLSGI4/ |url-access=subscription |title=A Monaco, le petit prince Charles Leclerc court à domicile: "Gagner chez moi serait incroyable" |trans-title=In Monaco, the little prince Charles Leclerc runs at home: "Winning at home would be incredible" |last=de Wilde |first=Olivier |date=25 May 2019 |work=[[La Libre Belgique]] |language=fr |issn=1379-6992 |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220118225616/https://www.lalibre.be/sports/moteurs/2019/05/25/a-monaco-le-petit-prince-charles-leclerc-court-a-domicile-gagner-chez-moi-serait-incroyable-JPD4YVOIVJBU3HWFA2MOTLSGI4/ |archive-date=18 January 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Hervé died after a long illness, aged 54, four days before Leclerc won the feature race at the [[2017 Baku Formula 2 round]].<ref name="BAK17">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/charles-leclerc-emotional-baku-formula-2-pole-was-for-late-father-5001252/5001252/ |title=Charles Leclerc: Emotional Baku Formula 2 pole was for late father |last1=Valentin |first1=Khorounzhiy |last2=Kalinauckas |first2=Alex |date=23 June 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808154126/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/130319 |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="HERVE"/> Prior to his death, Leclerc lied to his father that he had signed a Formula One contract for the {{F1|2018}} season;<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/47523208 |title=Formula 1 2019: Ferrari's Charles Leclerc on his dying father's wish |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=13 March 2019 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222205933/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/47523208 |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> he signed with [[Sauber]] later that year.<ref name="2018contract"/> His older maternal half-brother, Lorenzo Tolotta-Leclerc, was best friends with [[Jules Bianchi]], who was Leclerc's godfather until [[2014 Japanese Grand Prix|his death in 2015]]<!--His death was in 2015, not 2014.--> and his mechanic in kart racing.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.autohebdof1.com/news/f1/collector-leclerc-arthur-leclerc-and-lorenzo-tolotta-leclerc-what-makes-the-difference-is-that-we-know-where-we-come-from.html |title=Collector Leclerc – Arthur Leclerc and Lorenzo Tolotta-Leclerc: "What makes the difference is that we know where we come from" |last=Satis |first=Jeremy |date=19 February 2025 |magazine=Auto Hebdo |issn=0395-4366 |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222205939/https://www.autohebdof1.com/news/f1/collector-leclerc-arthur-leclerc-and-lorenzo-tolotta-leclerc-what-makes-the-difference-is-that-we-know-where-we-come-from.html |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live |url-access=subscription}}</ref><ref name="MC2017"/> His younger brother, [[Arthur Leclerc|Arthur]], is also a racing driver who has competed in [[open-wheel racing|open-wheel]] and [[sportscar racing]], winning the [[Formula Regional Asian Championship]] in [[2022 Formula Regional Asian Championship|2022]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/f1s-racing-brothers-the-leclercs-join-an-exclusive-list/ |url-access=registration |title=F1's racing brothers: the Leclercs join an exclusive list |last=Kisby |first=Cambridge |date=6 December 2024 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222205940/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/f1s-racing-brothers-the-leclercs-join-an-exclusive-list/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Junior racing career ==
=== Karting (2005–2013) ===
==== 2005–2009: Early success in national championships ====
Leclerc first began [[karting]] aged five and started racing at [[Brignoles]]—a [[kart circuit]] owned by [[Jules Bianchi]]'s father.<ref name="VK2022">{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.vroomkart.com/news/40478/leclerc-what-a-start |title=Leclerc: What a start! |last=Marangon |first=Fabio |date=21 March 2022 |magazine=Vroomkart |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=1724-9147 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240524015646/https://www.vroomkart.com/news/40478/leclerc-what-a-start |archive-date=24 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="KC2024">{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2024/05/29/well-done-charles-and-thank-you/ |title=Well done Charles and thank you! |date=29 May 2024 |website=Kartcom |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240822122903/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2024/05/29/well-done-charles-and-thank-you/ |archive-date=22 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="LBA2009">{{Cite web |url=https://www.leblogauto.com/sport-auto/competitions-auto/rencontre-avec-charles-leclerc/ |title=Rencontre avec Charles Leclerc |trans-title=Meeting with Charles Leclerc |date=4 September 2009 |website=Le Blog Auto |language=fr |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222032646/https://www.leblogauto.com/sport-auto/competitions-auto/rencontre-avec-charles-leclerc/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He began his competitive career in 2005, winning the regional [[Provence-Alpes-Côte d'Azur|PACA]] championship in the Mini class with 15 wins from 18 races, which he successfully defended in 2006.<ref name="LBA2009"/> He advanced to Minime in 2007, winning the Trophée Claude Secq and finishing runner-up at the PACA championship.<ref name="KC2009">{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2009/08/31/gros-titre-pour-charles-leclerc/ |title=Gros titre pour Charles Leclerc |trans-title=Large title for Charles Leclerc |date=31 August 2009 |website=Kartcom |language=fr |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222023115/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2009/08/31/gros-titre-pour-charles-leclerc/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> The following year, he finished fifth in the Bridgestone Cup and runner-up in the French Championship,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/pressrel/au-top-de-lorganisation/ |title=Bridgestone Cup l'événement 2008 {{!}} Au top de l'organisation |trans-title=Bridgestone Cup 2008 {{!}} At the top of the organization |date=1 May 2008 |website=Kartcom |language=fr |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222023211/https://www.kartcom.com/en/pressrel/au-top-de-lorganisation/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2008/08/25/champions-benjamin-gerard-et-esteban-ocon/ |title=Champions, Benjamin Gérard et Esteban Ocon |trans-title=Champions, Benjamin Gérard and Esteban Ocon |date=25 August 2008 |website=Kartcom |language=fr |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222023554/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2008/08/25/champions-benjamin-gerard-et-esteban-ocon/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> as well as winning the PACA title.<ref name="AA2019">{{Cite magazine |url=https://autoaction.com.au/2019/04/10/feature-charles-leclerc-misseur-leclerc |title=Feature: Charles Leclerc – Misseur Leclerc |last1=Williams |first1=Bruce |last2=Knutson |first2=Dan |date=10 April 2019 |magazine=[[Auto Action]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=2204-9924 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222031102/https://autoaction.com.au/2019/04/10/feature-charles-leclerc-misseur-leclerc |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Progressing to the Cadet class in 2009, Leclerc won the French Championship and Bridgestone Cup,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2009/08/25/659375-lavelanet-karting-la-finale-du-championnat-tres-disputee.html |title=Lavelanet. Karting : la finale du championnat très disputée |trans-title=Lavelanet. Karting: the very disputed championship final |date=25 August 2009 |work=[[La Dépêche du Midi]] |language=fr |issn=2426-6388 |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210410054740/https://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2009/08/25/659375-lavelanet-karting-la-finale-du-championnat-tres-disputee.html |archive-date=10 April 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/pressrel/des-lots-grandioses-un-final-en-apotheose/ |title=Des lots grandioses, un final en apothéose ! |trans-title=Magnificent prizes, a grand finale! |date=24 September 2009 |website=Kartcom |language=fr |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222023832/https://www.kartcom.com/en/pressrel/des-lots-grandioses-un-final-en-apotheose/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> as well as the regional [[Rhône-Alpes]] title.<ref name="LBA2009"/> He partnered with [[Richard Mille]] that year, who supported him through the remainder of his karting career.<ref name="RM"/>

==== 2010–2011: Progression to international series ====
Leclerc progressed to [[List of kart racing championships|international competition]] in 2010, entering the junior [[KF3]] class, where he became the youngest winner of the [[CIK-FIA Monaco Kart Cup]]—his home event at the [[Circuit de Monaco]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2010/10/17/leclerc-princely-victory-in-monaco/ |title=Leclerc: Princely victory in Monaco |date=17 October 2010 |website=Kartcom |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240924023550/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2010/10/17/leclerc-princely-victory-in-monaco/ |archive-date=24 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="FS2012">{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/ten-karting-stars-to-watch/2035 |title=Ten karting stars to watch |last=Allen |first=Peter |date=26 September 2012 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240914212308/https://formulascout.com/ten-karting-stars-to-watch/2035 |archive-date=14 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished twenty-ninth on his [[Karting World Cup|World Cup]] debut,<ref name="KWC10"/> fifth in the inaugural [[Karting Academy Trophy|Academy Trophy]],<ref name="FS2012"/> and runner-up to [[Pierre Gasly]] in the French Championship.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/pressrel/impressive-record-of-titles-for-sodi-at-2010-french-championships/ |title=Impressive Record of Titles for Sodi at 2010 French Championships! |date=3 November 2010 |website=Kartcom |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230429190008/https://www.kartcom.com/en/pressrel/impressive-record-of-titles-for-sodi-at-2010-french-championships/ |archive-date=29 April 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc was [[scout (sport)|scout]]ed by [[Nicolas Todt]] in 2011, joining his ''All Road Management'' firm upon recommendation from Bianchi.<ref name="KC2024"/><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.sportauto.fr/sauber/c35/f1-leclerc-doit-sa-carriere-a-bianchi-17796.html |title=F1 – Leclerc doit sa carrière à Bianchi |trans-title=F1 – Leclerc owes his career to Bianchi |last=Lalanne-Sicaud |first=Vincent |date=4 December 2017 |work=[[Sport auto (France)|Sport Auto]] |publisher=[[Reworld Media]] |language=fr |issn=0151-6353 |access-date=26 October 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251026120849/https://www.sportauto.fr/sauber/c35/f1-leclerc-doit-sa-carriere-a-bianchi-17796.html |archive-date=26 October 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Todt negotiated his move to Intrepid that year, winning the World Cup at [[Sarno]];<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.vroomkart.com/news/41676/the-intrepid-guys-who-made-it-to-f1 |title=The Intrepid guys who made it to F1 |last=Marangon |first=Fabio |date=18 January 2023 |magazine=Vroomkart |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=1724-9147 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240713042552/https://www.vroomkart.com/news/41676/the-intrepid-guys-who-made-it-to-f1 |archive-date=13 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he later described it as "by far [his] best karting race ever".<ref name="VK2022"/> He further won the [[2011 CIK-FIA Karting Academy Trophy|Academy Trophy]] and the [[Masters of Paris-Bercy]],<ref name="AA2019"/> as well as finishing runner-up to [[Nicklas Nielsen]] in the [[WSK Final Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2011/10/31/wsk-final-cup-ortona-jour-de-finales/ |title=WSK Final Cup Ortona, jour de finales |trans-title=WSK Final Cup Ortona, finals day |date=31 October 2011 |website=Kartcom |language=fr |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222024418/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2011/10/31/wsk-final-cup-ortona-jour-de-finales/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2012–2013: Senior titles with ART ====
<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Charles Leclerc Max Verstappen.png|thumb|right|Leclerc ''(right)'' won several senior titles with [[ART Grand Prix]], amidst a rivalry with [[Max Verstappen]] ''(left)''.|alt=Leclerc leads Max Verstappen at the 2013 WSK Master Series at Castelletto]] -->
Leclerc graduated to the senior [[KF2]] category in 2012 with the [[factory-backed]] [[ART Grand Prix]] team,<ref name="KC2024"/> winning the [[WSK Euro Series]];<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.vroomkart.com/news/12148/art-grand-prix-and-charles-leclerc-conquered-wsk-euro-series-championship-zuera |title=ART Grand Prix and Charles Leclerc conquered the WSK Euro Series championship in Zuera |date=6 August 2012 |magazine=Vroomkart |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=1724-9147 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240418015156/https://www.vroomkart.com/news/12148/art-grand-prix-and-charles-leclerc-conquered-wsk-euro-series-championship-zuera |archive-date=18 April 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he was involved in an incident with [[Max Verstappen]] at the second round, which resulted in both drivers' disqualifications.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/back-story-of-hate-enriches-leclerc-vs-verstappen/ |title=Back story of 'hate' enriches Leclerc vs Verstappen |last=Mitchell-Malm |first=Scott |date=1 May 2022 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240827231236/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/back-story-of-hate-enriches-leclerc-vs-verstappen/ |archive-date=27 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished runner-up on his [[Karting European Championship|European Championship]] debut amidst a title battle with Verstappen and [[Ben Barnicoat]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2020/09/09/wackersdorf-leclerc-and-verstappen-kf2-duel-in-2012/ |title=Wackersdorf: Leclerc and Verstappen KF2 duel in 2012 |date=9 September 2020 |website=Kartcom |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220907013359/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2020/09/09/wackersdorf-leclerc-and-verstappen-kf2-duel-in-2012/ |archive-date=7 September 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> as well as at the under-18 [[Karting World Championship|World Championship]] by a single point.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2012/11/12/u18-easthope-wins-a-thriller/ |title=U18: Easthope wins a thriller |date=12 November 2012 |website=Kartcom |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222024637/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2012/11/12/u18-easthope-wins-a-thriller/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He achieved fifth-placed finishes in both the World Cup and WSK Final Cup,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2012/09/23/tiene-wins-the-kf2-world-cup/ |title=Tiene wins the KF2 World Cup |date=23 September 2012 |website=Kartcom |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222024714/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2012/09/23/tiene-wins-the-kf2-world-cup/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="DriverDB"/> and fourth at the [[SKUSA SuperNationals]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/news/2012/11/18/victoire-disputee-en-tag-senior-le-colombien-chaves-simpose/ |title=Victoire disputée en TaG Senior : le Colombien Chavès s'impose |trans-title=Victory in TaG Senior: Colombian Chavès wins |date=18 November 2012 |website=Kartcom |language=fr |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222024909/https://www.kartcom.com/news/2012/11/18/victoire-disputee-en-tag-senior-le-colombien-chaves-simpose/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In 2013, Leclerc progressed to the [[KZ (karting)|KZ]] senior [[gearbox]] class, aged 15.<ref name="TK2013">{{Cite web |url=https://tkart.it/en/magazine/editorial/charles-leclerc-from-rookie-in-shifter-kz-kz2-at-15-years-of-age-wins-the-winter-cup-with-a-fever |title=Charles Leclerc {{!}} As a rookie in the shifter class (at 15 years of age) he won the Winter Cup... with a fever! |url-access=subscription |last=Livraghi |first=Mattia |date=24 May 2022 |website=TKART |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250108113515/https://tkart.it/en/magazine/editorial/charles-leclerc-from-rookie-in-shifter-kz-kz2-at-15-years-of-age-wins-the-winter-cup-with-a-fever |archive-date=8 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He opened the season with victory at the South Garda Winter Cup in [[KZ2]].<ref name="TK2013"/> He finished twelfth in the WSK Euro Series, and fourth in the [[WSK Master Series]].<ref name="DriverDB"/> Leclerc finished sixth in the European Championship after claiming a podium in the final round at [[Karting Genk|Genk]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.vroomkart.com/news/14552/leclerc-kz-podium-art-grand-prix-european-bid |title=Leclerc on KZ podium for ART Grand Prix European bid |date=2 July 2013 |magazine=Vroomkart |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=1724-9147 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240620084730/https://www.vroomkart.com/news/14552/leclerc-kz-podium-art-grand-prix-european-bid |archive-date=20 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He duelled with rival Verstappen to become the youngest-ever [[Karting World Championship#125 Gearbox FIA Karting world champions and World Cup winners|KZ World Champion]] at [[Varennes-sur-Allier]], with Leclerc finishing runner-up to him.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fia.com/news/verstappen-kz-world-champion-15 |title=Verstappen is KZ World Champion at 15! |date=24 February 2014 |website=[[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220120232052/https://www.fia.com/news/verstappen-kz-world-champion-15 |archive-date=20 January 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.vroomkart.com/news/15587/leclerc-s-sweet-farewell-art-grand-prix-varennes |title=Leclerc's sweet farewell for ART Grand Prix in Varennes |date=24 September 2013 |magazine=Vroomkart |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=1724-9147 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240613032815/https://www.vroomkart.com/news/15587/leclerc-s-sweet-farewell-art-grand-prix-varennes |archive-date=13 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Upon his graduation to [[junior formulae]], Leclerc credited their "numerous clashes" with boosting his experience and character.<ref name="KC2014">{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2014/02/07/charles-leclerc-a-concentration-of-talent-from-monaco/ |title=Charles Leclerc, a concentration of talent from Monaco |date=7 February 2014 |website=Kartcom |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250222024941/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2014/02/07/charles-leclerc-a-concentration-of-talent-from-monaco/ |archive-date=22 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> ''Kartcom'' opined that "his rise [was] meteoric for a driver who [did not] spend much time training on the track".<ref name="KC2014"/>

=== Formula Renault 2.0 (2014) ===
==== Formula Renault 2.0 Alps ====
Leclerc graduated to [[junior formulae]] in [[2014 Formula Renault 2.0 Alps Series|2014]], signing for [[Fortec Motorsport|Fortec]] in [[Formula Renault 2.0]], aged 16.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/leclerc-teams-up-with-fortec-for-alps-campaign/12810 |title=Leclerc teams up with Fortec for Alps campaign |last=Goddard |first=Stephen |date=26 November 2013 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241016003357/https://formulascout.com/leclerc-teams-up-with-fortec-for-alps-campaign/12810 |archive-date=16 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He debuted in the [[Formula Renault 2.0 Alps|Alps Series]], retiring from both races in the opening round at [[Imola Circuit|Imola]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/nyck-de-vries-dominates-opening-race-of-alps-season/16313 |title=Nyck de Vries dominates opening race of Alps season |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=5 April 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241007044135/https://formulascout.com/nyck-de-vries-dominates-opening-race-of-alps-season/16313 |archive-date=7 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/nyck-de-vries-cruises-to-victory-in-race-two-of-alps-opener/16339 |title=Nyck de Vries cruises to victory in race two of Alps opener |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=6 April 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240911032104/https://formulascout.com/nyck-de-vries-cruises-to-victory-in-race-two-of-alps-opener/16339 |archive-date=11 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He achieved his maiden podium finish in the second race at [[Pau Circuit|Pau]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/de-vries-takes-fourth-consecutive-win-in-pau-race-two/17930 |title=De Vries takes fourth consecutive win in Pau race two |last=Gruz |first=David |date=11 May 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250115084817/https://formulascout.com/de-vries-takes-fourth-consecutive-win-in-pau-race-two/17930 |archive-date=15 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> After fourth-placed finishes at the [[Red Bull Ring]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/isaakyan-takes-maiden-alps-win-from-pole-at-spielberg/18240 |title=Isaakyan takes maiden Alps win from pole at Spielberg |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=24 May 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241004110319/https://formulascout.com/isaakyan-takes-maiden-alps-win-from-pole-at-spielberg/18240 |archive-date=4 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/isaakyan-does-the-double-at-spielberg/18275 |title=Isaakyan does the double at Spielberg |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=25 May 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240722045533/https://formulascout.com/isaakyan-does-the-double-at-spielberg/18275 |archive-date=22 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc scored a double podium during the [[Spa-Francorchamps]] round.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/de-vries-secures-victory-in-incident-ridden-spa-race/18674 |title=De Vries secures victory in incident-ridden Spa race |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=7 June 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240616023214/https://formulascout.com/de-vries-secures-victory-in-incident-ridden-spa-race/18674 |archive-date=16 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/de-vries-takes-comfortable-sixth-win-at-damp-spa/18729 |title=De Vries takes comfortable sixth win at damp Spa |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=8 June 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240717171017/https://formulascout.com/de-vries-takes-comfortable-sixth-win-at-damp-spa/18729 |archive-date=17 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.driverdb.com/results/26791 |title=Formula Renault 2.0 Alps Series {{!}} 2014 {{!}} Round 8 {{!}} Spa-Francorchamps |website=Driver Database |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250220140658/https://www.driverdb.com/results/26791 |archive-date=20 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He followed this up with his maiden [[formula racing]] victories at [[Monza Circuit|Monza]], the latter from [[pole position]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/leclerc-inherits-maiden-alps-win-at-monza/19487 |title=Leclerc inherits maiden Alps win at Monza |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=5 July 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241107085651/https://formulascout.com/leclerc-inherits-maiden-alps-win-at-monza/19487 |archive-date=7 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/charles-leclerc-grabs-second-win-of-monza-weekend/19536 |title=Charles Leclerc grabs second win of Monza weekend |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=6 July 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530233025/https://formulascout.com/charles-leclerc-grabs-second-win-of-monza-weekend/19536 |archive-date=30 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished second to [[Nyck de Vries]] in both [[Mugello Circuit|Mugello]] races,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.jenzermotorsport.ch/en/?view=article&id=646:f-renault-2-0-alps-monza-i-06-07-09e-2014&catid=15 |title=Race Report {{!}} Formula Renault 2.0 2014 Alps Championship, Rounds 11/12 |date=7 September 2014 |website=[[Jenzer Motorsport]] |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250220132239/https://www.jenzermotorsport.ch/en/?view=article&id=646:f-renault-2-0-alps-monza-i-06-07-09e-2014&catid=15 |archive-date=20 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> before claiming points finishes at the season-ending [[Circuito de Jerez|Jerez]] round.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/bonifacio-converts-pole-into-victory-in-race-one-at-jerez/21871 |title=Bonifacio converts pole into victory in race one at Jerez |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=5 October 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240618080414/https://formulascout.com/bonifacio-converts-pole-into-victory-in-race-one-at-jerez/21871 |archive-date=18 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/de-vries-ends-dominant-alps-season-with-ninth-victory/21885 |title=De Vries ends dominant Alps campaign with ninth victory |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=5 October 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241011062013/https://formulascout.com/de-vries-ends-dominant-alps-season-with-ninth-victory/21885 |archive-date=11 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> During the season, Leclerc took two victories from seven podium finishes as he finished runner-up to De Vries—a third-year Formula Renault 2.0 driver—and beat [[Matevos Isaakyan]] to the rookies' championship.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/2014-formula-renault-2-0-alps-season-review/22412 |title=2014 Formula Renault 2.0 Alps season review |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=28 October 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250123180533/https://formulascout.com/2014-formula-renault-2-0-alps-season-review/22412 |archive-date=23 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://fortecmotorsports.com/?p=2276 |title=Leclerc takes Rookie Championship title |date=8 October 2014 |website=[[Fortec Motorsport]] |access-date=2 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150228023238/http://fortecmotorsports.com/?p=2276 |archive-date=28 February 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

==== Formula Renault Eurocup ====
Fortec also entered Leclerc into select rounds of the [[2014 Eurocup Formula Renault 2.0|Eurocup]], part of the [[2014 World Series by Renault|World Series by Renault]], as a guest driver.<ref name="NYT2017"/> He set a track record at [[Circuit de Barcelona-Catalunya|Barcelona-Catalunya]] in pre-season testing.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2014/03/19/charles-leclerc-leaves-everyone-in-his-trail-in-barcelona/ |title=Charles Leclerc leaves everyone in his trail in Barcelona |date=19 March 2014 |website=Kartcom |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250220123934/https://www.kartcom.com/en/news/2014/03/19/charles-leclerc-leaves-everyone-in-his-trail-in-barcelona/ |archive-date=20 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> After finishing outside of the points on debut at Spa-Francorchamps,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/maiden-win-for-eurocup-rookie-dennis-olsen-in-spa/18413 |title=Maiden win for Eurocup rookie Dennis Olsen at Spa |last=Musker |first=Ant |date=31 May 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250115001648/https://formulascout.com/maiden-win-for-eurocup-rookie-dennis-olsen-in-spa/18413 |archive-date=15 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/bruno-bonifacio-claims-first-eurocup-win-at-spa/18489 |title=Bruno Bonifacio claims first Eurocup win at Spa |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=1 June 2014 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241206042728/https://formulascout.com/bruno-bonifacio-claims-first-eurocup-win-at-spa/18489 |archive-date=6 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc took his maiden podium in the series at the [[Nürburgring]], finishing second to [[Dennis Olsen (racing driver)|Dennis Olsen]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.autohebdo.fr/actualites/monoplace/fr20-c2-dennis-olsen-confirme-au-nurburgring.html |title=FR2.0-C2 : Dennis Olsen confirme au Nürburgring |trans-title=FR2.0-C2: Dennis Olsen wins at Nürburgring |last=Dupuis |date=13 July 2014 |magazine=Auto Hebdo |language=fr |issn=0395-4366 |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250220124125/https://www.autohebdo.fr/actualites/monoplace/fr20-c2-dennis-olsen-confirme-au-nurburgring.html |archive-date=20 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He then took further second-placed finishes in both races at the [[Hungaroring]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.driverdb.com/news/second-win-of-eurocup-season-for-pizzitola |title=Second win of Eurocup season for Pizzitola |date=15 September 2014 |website=Driver Database |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250220124613/https://www.driverdb.com/news/second-win-of-eurocup-season-for-pizzitola |archive-date=20 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://it.motorsport.com/frenault/news/eurocup-formula-renault-2.0-jack-aitken-domina-gara-2/599493/ |title=Jack Aitken domina Gara 2 |trans-title=Jack Aitken dominates Race 2 |last=Rauli |first=Giacomo |date=14 September 2014 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |language=it |access-date=20 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250220124732/https://it.motorsport.com/frenault/news/eurocup-formula-renault-2.0-jack-aitken-domina-gara-2/599493/ |archive-date=20 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> ending his campaign with three podiums from six starts.<ref name="NYT2017">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/14/sports/autoracing/charles-leclerc-ferrari-f1.html |url-access=registration |title=Charles Leclerc, a Teenage Driver, Shows Potential for Ferrari |last=Walker |first=Kate |date=14 September 2017 |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |access-date=20 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241130140909/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/09/14/sports/autoracing/charles-leclerc-ferrari-f1.html |archive-date=30 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Formula Three (2015) ===
==== FIA European Formula 3 ====
[[File:Charles Leclerc, Formel 3 2015 (cropped).JPG|thumb|Leclerc progressed to [[2015 FIA Formula 3 European Championship|FIA European Formula 3]] in [[2015 FIA Formula 3 European Championship|2015]], winning several races and finishing second at the [[2015 Macau Grand Prix|Macau Grand Prix]].|alt=Leclerc driving the Dallara F314 at the 2015 FIA European Formula 3 Spa-Francorchamps round]]
Leclerc graduated to [[Formula Three]] in 2015, contesting [[2015 FIA Formula 3 European Championship|FIA European F3]] with [[Van Amersfoort Racing]] amongst a highly-competitive field.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/nicolas-todt-protege-charles-leclerc-secures-f3-deal-for-2015-5325369/5325369/ |title=Nicolas Todt protege Charles Leclerc secures F3 deal for 2015 |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=14 January 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=14 January 2015 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303182822/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/117356 |archive-date=3 March 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name="MC2015"/> In the opening round at [[Silverstone Circuit|Silverstone]], he inherited [[pole position]] for the second and third races after [[Felix Rosenqvist]] was excluded for a technical infringement.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/silverstone-european-f3-rosenqvist-loses-two-poles-to-leclerc-5008622/5008622/ |title=Silverstone European F3: Rosenqvist loses two poles to Leclerc |date=11 April 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250219131552/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/silverstone-european-f3-rosenqvist-loses-two-poles-to-leclerc-5008622/5008622/ |archive-date=19 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> After finishing twelfth on debut,<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2015/04/11/rosenqvist-wins-disrupted-race-one/ |title=F3: Rosenqvist wins disrupted race one |date=11 April 2015 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=19 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250219134611/https://racer.com/2015/04/11/rosenqvist-wins-disrupted-race-one/ |archive-date=19 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> he clinched second in race two followed by his maiden victory amidst a race-long battle with [[Antonio Giovinazzi]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/george-russell-claims-victory-in-second-formula-3-start/26323 |title=George Russell claims victory on second Formula 3 start |last=Allen |first=Peter |date=11 April 2015 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=19 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241225221436/https://formulascout.com/george-russell-claims-victory-in-second-formula-3-start/26323 |archive-date=25 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/silverstone-european-f3-leclerc-records-maiden-victory-in-final-5008544/5008544/ |title=Silverstone European F3: Leclerc records maiden victory in final |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=12 April 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230328124433/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/silverstone-european-f3-leclerc-records-maiden-victory-in-final-5008544/5008544/ |archive-date=28 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc claimed an additional three consecutive podiums at the [[Hockenheimring]], winning the rain-affected third race after overtaking Rosenqvist.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/charles-leclerc-wins-wet-third-european-f3-race-at-hockenheim/27335 |title=Charles Leclerc wins wet third European F3 race at Hockenheim |last=Allen |first=Peter |date=3 May 2015 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=19 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240912150425/https://formulascout.com/charles-leclerc-wins-wet-third-european-f3-race-at-hockenheim/27335 |archive-date=12 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He increased his run to eight consecutive podiums at [[Pau Circuit|Pau]], including a third-placed finish at the [[Pau Grand Prix]]—the final race of the weekend.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2015/05/16/dennis-takes-first-f3-victory-in-pau/ |title=Dennis takes first F3 victory in Pau |date=16 May 2015 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=19 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250219134638/https://racer.com/2015/05/16/dennis-takes-first-f3-victory-in-pau/ |archive-date=19 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/european-f3-pau-jake-dennis-wins-again-in-race-two-5007019/5007019/ |title=European F3 Pau: Jake Dennis wins again in race two |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=16 May 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250219131801/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/european-f3-pau-jake-dennis-wins-again-in-race-two-5007019/5007019/ |archive-date=19 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/giovinazzi-snatches-pau-grand-prix-victory-after-dennis-slows/27794 |title=Giovinazzi snatches Pau Grand Prix victory after Dennis slows |last=Allen |first=Peter |date=17 May 2015 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=19 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213205111/https://formulascout.com/giovinazzi-snatches-pau-grand-prix-victory-after-dennis-slows/27794 |archive-date=13 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He suffered his first retirement of the season in the second race at [[Monza Circuit|Monza]] after colliding with [[Jake Dennis]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/monza-european-f3-felix-rosenqvist-wins-amid-chaos-and-big-crashes-5006330/5006330/ |title=Monza European F3: Felix Rosenqvist wins amid chaos and big crashes |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=30 May 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241006133958/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/monza-european-f3-felix-rosenqvist-wins-amid-chaos-and-big-crashes-5006330/5006330/ |archive-date=6 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> before returning to the podium in the curtailed final race.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/monza-european-f3-rosenqvist-wins-as-race-abandoned-after-crashes-5006293/5006293/ |title=Monza European F3: Rosenqvist wins as race abandoned after crashes |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=31 May 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211202044302/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/monza-european-f3-rosenqvist-wins-as-race-abandoned-after-crashes-5006293/5006293/ |archive-date=2 December 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref>

With his victory in the first race at [[Spa-Francorchamps]] from sixth on the grid—following a three-way battle with Rosenqvist and Giovinazzi—Leclerc took the championship lead;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fia.com/es/news/charles-leclerc-decides-thrilling-three-way-battle-his-favour |title=Charles Leclerc decides thrilling three-way battle in his favour |date=20 June 2015 |website=[[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile]] |access-date=19 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250219133439/https://www.fia.com/es/news/charles-leclerc-decides-thrilling-three-way-battle-his-favour |archive-date=19 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/european-f3-spa-charles-leclerc-wins-race-one-after-rivals-collide-5005349/5005349/ |title=European F3 Spa: Charles Leclerc wins race one after rivals collide |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=20 June 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230930064954/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/european-f3-spa-charles-leclerc-wins-race-one-after-rivals-collide-5005349/5005349/ |archive-date=30 September 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> he achieved a further podium in race three.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2015/06/21/dennis-wins-again-in-final-spa-race/ |title=F3: Dennis wins again in final Spa race |date=21 June 2015 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=19 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250219134724/https://racer.com/2015/06/21/dennis-wins-again-in-final-spa-race/ |archive-date=19 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> With a victory from pole followed by another podium at the [[Norisring]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/formula-european-masters/news/leclerc-dominates-wet-norisring-opener/613051/ |title=Leclerc dominates wet Norisring opener |last=Klein |first=Jamie |date=27 June 2015 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190502110400/https://www.motorsport.com/formula-european-masters/news/leclerc-dominates-wet-norisring-opener/613051/ |archive-date=2 May 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/norisring-european-f3-maximilian-gunther-wins-from-12th-on-grid-5004940/5004940/ |title=Norisring European F3: Maximilian Günther wins from 12th on grid |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=27 June 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230601032344/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/norisring-european-f3-maximilian-gunther-wins-from-12th-on-grid-5004940/5004940/ |archive-date=1 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc held a 42.5-point lead over Giovinazzi after six rounds.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/norisring-european-f3-carlins-antonio-giovinazzi-wins-race-three-5004901/5004901/ |title=Norisring European F3: Carlin's Antonio Giovinazzi wins race three |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=28 June 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230208140427/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/norisring-european-f3-carlins-antonio-giovinazzi-wins-race-three-5004901/5004901/ |archive-date=8 February 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc collided with [[Lance Stroll]] in race two at [[Circuit Zandvoort|Zandvoort]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2015/07/11/rosenqvist-wins-trouble-for-leclerc/ |title=F3: Rosenqvist wins, trouble for Leclerc |date=11 July 2015 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=19 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250219134804/https://racer.com/2015/07/11/rosenqvist-wins-trouble-for-leclerc/ |archive-date=19 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> and had to replace his [[Dallara F314]] chassis.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/zandvoort-european-f3-charles-leclerc-could-be-sidelined-by-crash-5004195/5004195/ |title=Zandvoort European F3: Charles Leclerc could be sidelined by crash |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=11 July 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906140523/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/119951 |archive-date=6 September 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref> From that point onwards, Leclerc did not score a single podium across the remaining four rounds, with fourth-placed finishes at the [[Red Bull Ring]] and [[Nürburgring]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/red-bull-ring-european-f3-rosenqvist-beats-giovinazzi-in-race-two-5003247/5003247/ |title=Red Bull Ring European F3: Rosenqvist beats Giovinazzi in race two |date=1 August 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230608055539/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/red-bull-ring-european-f3-rosenqvist-beats-giovinazzi-in-race-two-5003247/5003247/ |archive-date=8 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/nurburgring-european-f3-felix-rosenqvist-wins-and-closes-on-title-5000251/5000251/ |title=Nürburgring European F3: Felix Rosenqvist wins and closes on title |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=26 September 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230203201330/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/nurburgring-european-f3-felix-rosenqvist-wins-and-closes-on-title-5000251/5000251/ |archive-date=3 February 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> as he slipped to fourth in the standings—behind Rosenqvist, Giovinazzi, and Dennis.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/2015-fia-f3-european-championship-season-review/31898 |title=2015 FIA F3 European Championship season review |last=Allen |first=Peter |date=17 November 2015 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=19 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241222134831/https://formulascout.com/2015-fia-f3-european-championship-season-review/31898 |archive-date=22 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He clinched the rookies' championship,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fia.com/news/felix-rosenqvist-wins-–-charles-leclerc-wraps-rookie-title |title=Felix Rosenqvist wins – Charles Leclerc wraps up rookie title |date=26 September 2015 |website=[[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile]] |access-date=19 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241102153712/https://www.fia.com/news/felix-rosenqvist-wins-–-charles-leclerc-wraps-rookie-title |archive-date=2 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> having achieved four victories from 13 podium finishes,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/the-top-10-euro-f3-drivers-of-2015-5104988/5104988/ |url-access=subscription |title=The top 10 Euro F3 drivers of 2015 |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=6 November 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240421212308/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/the-top-10-euro-f3-drivers-of-2015-5104988/5104988/ |archive-date=21 April 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> and Valentin Khorounzhiy of ''[[Motorsport.com]]'' ranked him the best driver of the season.<ref name="MC2015">{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/formula-european-masters/news/top-10-european-formula-3-drivers-of-2015/653012/ |title=Top 10 European Formula 3 drivers of 2015 |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=29 October 2015 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240918213401/https://www.motorsport.com/formula-european-masters/news/top-10-european-formula-3-drivers-of-2015/653012/ |archive-date=18 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== Macau Grand Prix ====
Following his European F3 campaign, Leclerc entered the [[2015 Macau Grand Prix|Macau Grand Prix]] with Van Amersfoort.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f3/news/macau-gp-giovinazzi-leads-first-practice/658322/?s=1 |title=Macau GP: Giovinazzi leads first practice |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=19 November 2015 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=24 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213202127/https://www.motorsport.com/f3/news/macau-gp-giovinazzi-leads-first-practice/658322/?s=1 |archive-date=13 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> After qualifying third,<ref name="MAC1">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/macau-f3-grand-prix-felix-rosenqvist-denies-daniel-juncadella-pole-4996495/4996495/ |title=Macau F3 Grand Prix: Felix Rosenqvist denies Daniel Juncadella pole |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=20 November 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=24 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213213429/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/macau-f3-grand-prix-felix-rosenqvist-denies-daniel-juncadella-pole-4996495/4996495/ |archive-date=13 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc finished second to [[Felix Rosenqvist]] in the qualification race after a penalty for [[Antonio Giovinazzi]], which set the grid for the main race.<ref name="MAC2">{{Cite web |url=https://www.fia.com/news/first-job-completed-felix-rosenqvist-wins-qualification-race |title=First job completed: Felix Rosenqvist wins qualification race |date=21 November 2015 |website=[[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile]] |access-date=24 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213174045/https://www.fia.com/news/first-job-completed-felix-rosenqvist-wins-qualification-race |archive-date=13 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f3/news/macau-gp-rosenqvist-handed-qualifier-victory-giovinazzi-penalised/658813/?s=1 |title=Macau GP: Rosenqvist handed qualifier victory, Giovinazzi penalised |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=21 November 2015 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=24 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200924113435/https://www.motorsport.com/f3/news/macau-gp-rosenqvist-handed-qualifier-victory-giovinazzi-penalised/658813/?s=1 |archive-date=24 September 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc again finished second to Rosenqvist in the Grand Prix, following a race-long battle.<ref name="MAC3">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/f3-macau-gp-rosenqvist-holds-off-leclerc-to-become-dual-winner-4996406/4996406/ |title=F3 Macau GP: Rosenqvist holds off Leclerc to become dual winner |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=22 November 2015 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=24 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213222221/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/f3-macau-gp-rosenqvist-holds-off-leclerc-to-become-dual-winner-4996406/4996406/ |archive-date=13 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.scmp.com/sport/other-sport/article/1881878/back-back-titles-fabulous-felix-blazes-glory-again-macau-grand |title=Back-to-back titles: Fabulous Felix blazes to glory again in Macau Grand Prix |last=Scott |first=Mathew |date=23 November 2015 |work=[[South China Morning Post]] |publisher=[[Alibaba Group]] |access-date=24 January 2025 |issn=1563-9371 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230630070950/https://www.scmp.com/sport/other-sport/article/1881878/back-back-titles-fabulous-felix-blazes-glory-again-macau-grand |archive-date=30 June 2023 |url-status=live |url-access=subscription}}</ref> He described the result as crucial to his "mental strength" after the closing rounds of his F3 season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f3/news/leclerc-says-macau-result-a-vital-boost-mentally/659187/ |title=Leclerc says Macau result a vital boost mentally |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=23 November 2015 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230406031341/https://www.motorsport.com/f3/news/leclerc-says-macau-result-a-vital-boost-mentally/659187/ |archive-date=6 April 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== GP3 Series (2016) ===
In December 2015, Leclerc partook in post-season [[GP3 Series|GP3]] testing with [[ART Grand Prix|ART]] and [[Arden International|Arden]], ultimately signing with the former for the [[2016 GP3 Series]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/charles-leclerc-joins-art-grand-prix-for-2016-gp3-series-4993647/4993647/ |title=Charles Leclerc joins ART Grand Prix for 2016 GP3 Series |date=29 February 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241227114423/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/charles-leclerc-joins-art-grand-prix-for-2016-gp3-series-4993647/4993647/ |archive-date=27 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Also joining the [[Ferrari Driver Academy]] prior to the season,<ref name="FDA"/> Leclerc qualified third at [[2016 Catalunya GP3 Series round|Catalunya]] before winning his debut race by over six seconds;<ref name="CAT16">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/gp3-barcelona-ferrari-f1-junior-charles-leclerc-dominates-race-one-4988892/4988892/ |title=GP3 Barcelona: Ferrari F1 junior Charles Leclerc dominates race one |date=14 May 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250119075702/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/gp3-barcelona-ferrari-f1-junior-charles-leclerc-dominates-race-one-4988892/4988892/ |archive-date=19 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> in the [[GP3 Series#Race weekend|reverse-grid second race]],{{efn-num|In the [[2016 GP3 Series]], grid position for [[GP3 Series#Race weekend|race two]] was decided by [[FIA Formula 2 Championship#Race weekend|race one]] finishing position, with the top eight finishers subjected to a [[Glossary of motorsport terms#R|reverse-grid]].<ref name="CAT16"/>}} he finished ninth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/barcelona-gp3-albon-holds-off-tunjo-for-maiden-win-736890/736890/ |title=Barcelona GP3: Albon holds off Tunjo for maiden win |last=Klein |first=Jamie |date=15 May 2016 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218203232/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/barcelona-gp3-albon-holds-off-tunjo-for-maiden-win-736890/736890/ |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the [[2016 Red Bull Ring GP3 Series round|Red Bull Ring]], he took [[pole position]] by over half a second and led the first race from [[Glossary of motorsport terms#L|lights-to-flag]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://autosprint.corrieredellosport.it/news/pista/2016/07/02-342674/gp3_leclerc_vince_e_rafforza_la_sua_leadership |title=GP3, Leclerc vince e rafforza la sua leadership |trans-title=GP3, Leclerc wins and strengthens his lead |last=Gargantini |first=Alessandro |date=2 July 2016 |work=[[Corriere dello Sport|Autosprint]] |publisher=[[Corriere dello Sport]] |language=it |issn=2531-3843 |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160706123238/http://autosprint.corrieredellosport.it/news/pista/2016/07/02-342674/gp3_leclerc_vince_e_rafforza_la_sua_leadership/ |archive-date=6 July 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> He retired after colliding with [[Jake Dennis]] and [[Tatiana Calderón]] in race two, receiving a five-place [[Glossary of motorsport terms#G|grid penalty]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2016/07/03/leclerc-given-grid-penalty-for-crash/ |title=GP3: Leclerc given grid penalty for crash |date=3 July 2016 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230129181937/https://racer.com/2016/07/03/leclerc-given-grid-penalty-for-crash/ |archive-date=29 January 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Subsequently starting seventh at [[2016 Silverstone GP3 Series round|Silverstone]], Leclerc recovered to second- and third-placed finishes.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/silverstone-gp3-alexander-albon-holds-off-charging-charles-leclerc-5041039/5041039/ |title=Silverstone GP3: Alexander Albon holds off charging Charles Leclerc |last=Simmons |first=Marcus |date=9 July 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230613135349/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/silverstone-gp3-alexander-albon-holds-off-charging-charles-leclerc-5041039/5041039/ |archive-date=13 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.gazzetta.it/Formula-1/10-07-2016/gp3-silverstone-fuoco-primo-successo-gp3-160297961317.shtml |title=Fuoco dà lezioni di guida: primo successo in GP3 |trans-title=Fuoco gives driving lessons: first success in GP3 |last=Gattulli  |first=Antonio |date=10 July 2016 |work=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]] |publisher=[[RCS MediaGroup]] |language=it |issn=1120-5067 |access-date=18 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161019052019/http://www.gazzetta.it/Formula-1/10-07-2016/gp3-silverstone-fuoco-primo-successo-gp3-160297961317.shtml |archive-date=19 October 2016 |url-status=live}}</ref> After finishing sixth in race one at the [[2016 Hungaroring GP3 Series round|Hungaroring]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/hungaroring-gp3-matt-parry-scores-first-victory-with-koiranen-5040042/5040042/ |title=Hungaroring GP3: Matt Parry scores first victory with Koiranen |date=23 July 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240811182542/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/hungaroring-gp3-matt-parry-scores-first-victory-with-koiranen-5040042/5040042/ |archive-date=11 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he achieved a podium in race two as race-winner [[Alexander Albon]] took the championship lead.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/hungary-gp3-albon-takes-points-lead-with-sunday-win-801751/801751/ |title=Hungary GP3: Albon takes points lead with Sunday win |last=Gruz |first=David |date=24 July 2016 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218223550/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/hungary-gp3-albon-takes-points-lead-with-sunday-win-801751/801751/ |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He received a three-place grid drop for impeding [[Giuliano Alesi]] in qualifying at the [[2016 Hockenheimring GP3 Series round|Hockenheimring]], where he finished fifth in race one—behind Albon.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2016/07/30/ferrari-junior-fuoco-wins-hockenheim-opener/ |title=GP3: Ferrari junior Fuoco wins Hockenheim opener |date=30 July 2016 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218233338/https://racer.com/2016/07/30/ferrari-junior-fuoco-wins-hockenheim-opener/ |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> His third-placed finish in race two, coupled with Albon's retirement, saw Leclerc reclaim his points lead.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/gp3-hockenheim-jake-hughes-secures-dams-first-win-in-series-5039354/5039354/ |title=GP3 Hockenheim: Jake Hughes secures DAMS' first win in series |date=31 July 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803220430/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/gp3-hockenheim-jake-hughes-secures-dams-first-win-in-series-5039354/5039354/ |archive-date=3 August 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Leclerc took pole at [[2016 Spa-Francorchamps GP3 Series round|Spa-Francorchamps]] and held off Dennis to win race one,<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2016/08/27/leclerc-takes-lights-to-flag-win-at-spa/ |title=GP3: Leclerc takes lights-to-flag win at Spa |date=27 August 2016 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218233413/https://racer.com/2016/08/27/leclerc-takes-lights-to-flag-win-at-spa/ |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> before finishing sixth in the second race.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/spa-gp3-aitken-survives-three-restarts-for-maiden-victory-810784/810784/ |title=Spa GP3: Aitken survives three restarts for maiden victory |last=Klein |first=Jamie |date=28 August 2016 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218223612/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/spa-gp3-aitken-survives-three-restarts-for-maiden-victory-810784/810784/ |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Another pole followed at [[2016 Monza GP3 Series round|Monza]], where he finished fourth in race one—ahead of title rivals Albon and [[Antonio Fuoco]]—and retired from race two after colliding with teammate [[Nirei Fukuzumi]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/monza-gp3-jake-dennis-leads-arden-1-2-at-monza-to-claim-first-win-5036578/5036578/ |title=Monza GP3: Jake Dennis leads Arden 1–2 at Monza to claim first win |date=3 September 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210805230240/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/monza-gp3-jake-dennis-leads-arden-1-2-at-monza-to-claim-first-win-5036578/5036578/ |archive-date=5 August 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/monza-gp3-de-vries-scores-maiden-win-leclerc-collides-with-teammate-815403/815403/ |title=Monza GP3: De Vries scores maiden win, Leclerc collides with teammate |last=Gruz |first=David |date=4 September 2016 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218223641/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/monza-gp3-de-vries-scores-maiden-win-leclerc-collides-with-teammate-815403/815403/ |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc took his third consecutive pole at [[2016 Sepang GP3 Series round|Sepang]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2016/09/30/leclerc-grabs-third-straight-gp3-pole/ |title=GP3: Leclerc grabs third-straight pole |date=30 September 2016 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218233456/https://racer.com/2016/09/30/leclerc-grabs-third-straight-gp3-pole/ |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> finishing third and fifth in the races, which extended his championship lead to 29 points over Albon with one round remaining.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/sepang-gp3-albon-grabs-race-1-victory-as-de-vries-hits-leclerc-831837/831837/ |title=Sepang GP3: Albon grabs Race 1 victory as De Vries hits Leclerc |last=Gruz |first=David |date=1 October 2016 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218223606/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f3/news/sepang-gp3-albon-grabs-race-1-victory-as-de-vries-hits-leclerc-831837/831837/ |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/gp3-sepang-jake-dennis-wins-race-two-in-malaysia-5033247/5033247/ |title=GP3 Sepang: Jake Dennis wins race two in Malaysia |date=2 October 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Haymarket Media Group]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210727101309/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/gp3-sepang-jake-dennis-wins-race-two-in-malaysia-5033247/5033247/ |archive-date=27 July 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc clinched the title in race one at [[2016 Yas Marina GP3 Series round|Yas Marina]] after Albon retired, with Leclerc suffering race-ending damage himself after colliding with [[Santino Ferrucci]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/motor-sports/news/leclerc-clinches-gp3-title-despite-crashing-out-in-abu-dhabi-opener |title=Leclerc clinches GP3 title despite crashing out in Abu Dhabi opener |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=26 November 2016 |work=[[NBC Sports]] |publisher=[[NBC]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231201192742/https://www.nbcsports.com/motor-sports/news/leclerc-clinches-gp3-title-despite-crashing-out-in-abu-dhabi-opener |archive-date=1 December 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> and dedicated the title to his godfather [[Jules Bianchi]].<ref name="SkyF2">{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11070780/charles-leclerc-crowned-2017-f2-champion |title=Charles Leclerc crowned 2017 F2 champion |last=Esler |first=William |date=8 October 2017 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=18 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250114180156/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11070780/charles-leclerc-crowned-2017-f2-champion |archive-date=14 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> With three victories from eight podiums, Leclerc described the season as "amazing" and that it was the first time in his [[junior formulae]] career he felt pressure: "now I can handle the pressure".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/ferrari-junior-leclerc-2016-gp3-season-first-time-i-felt-pressure-5026996/5026996/ |title=Ferrari junior Leclerc: 2016 GP3 season first time I felt pressure |date=7 December 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231206173529/https://www.autosport.com/fia-f3/news/ferrari-junior-leclerc-2016-gp3-season-first-time-i-felt-pressure-5026996/5026996/ |archive-date=6 December 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== FIA Formula 2 (2017) ===
[[File:F2-Race1のシャルル１ (36974715682).jpg|thumb|right|Leclerc (pictured at [[2017 Monza Formula 2 round|Monza]]) graduated to [[FIA Formula 2]] with [[Prema Racing|Prema]] in {{F2|2017}}.|alt=Leclerc looking out of his Dallara GP2/11 with his visor raised before the 2017 Monza Formula 2 round]]
Following his GP3 title victory, Leclerc progressed to [[FIA Formula 2]] with [[Prema Racing|Prema]] for its inaugural {{F2|2017}} season, alongside fellow [[Ferrari Driver Academy]] member [[Antonio Fuoco]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.racer.com/international-racing/item/136792-ferrari-juniors-to-prema-in-gp2-for-2017 |title=GP2: Ferrari juniors to Prema for 2017 |date=28 November 2016 |work=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=28 November 2016 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161129151115/https://www.racer.com/international-racing/item/136792-ferrari-juniors-to-prema-in-gp2-for-2017 |archive-date=29 November 2016 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Debuting at [[2017 Sakhir Formula 2 round|Sakhir]], Leclerc took [[pole position]] for the [[FIA Formula 2 Championship#Race weekend|feature race]], where he finished third.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/bahrain-formula-2-markelov-beats-nato-and-leclerc-with-late-surge-5016732/5016732/ |title=Bahrain Formula 2: Markelov beats Nato and Leclerc with late surge |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=15 April 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170625124358/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/128986 |archive-date=25 June 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> In the [[FIA Formula 2 Championship#Race weekend|reverse-grid sprint race]],{{efn-num|In the [[2017 FIA Formula 2 Championship]], [[FIA Formula 2 Championship#Race weekend|sprint race]] grid position was decided by [[FIA Formula 2 Championship#Race weekend|feature race]] finishing position, with the top eight finishers subjected to a [[Glossary of motorsport terms#R|reverse-grid]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fia.com/sites/default/files/media_kit_2017_eng_v2__0.pdf |title=2017 Formula 1 Gulf Air Bahrain Grand Prix {{!}} Formula One Media {{!}} Official Media Kit |date=29 March 2017 |website=[[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile]] |access-date=2 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250102002252/https://www.fia.com/sites/default/files/media_kit_2017_eng_v2__0.pdf |archive-date=2 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>}} he opted for a mid-race [[pit stop]]—an uncommon practise in sprints—after creating a nine-second lead; Leclerc proceeded to overtake 13 drivers in nine laps to secure his maiden F2 victory.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/motor-sports/news/charles-leclerc-takes-stunning-bahrain-f2-win-after-charge-from-14th |title=Charles Leclerc takes stunning Bahrain F2 win after charge from 14th |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=16 April 2017 |work=[[NBC Sports]] |publisher=[[NBC]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241231010018/https://www.nbcsports.com/motor-sports/news/charles-leclerc-takes-stunning-bahrain-f2-win-after-charge-from-14th |archive-date=31 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/bahrain-formula-2-ferrari-junior-leclerc-beats-ghiotto-and-rowland-5016643/5016643/ |title=Bahrain Formula 2: Ferrari junior Leclerc beats Ghiotto and Rowland |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=16 April 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808154041/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/129011 |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> He took pole again in [[2017 Barcelona Formula 2 round|Barcelona]], holding off [[Luca Ghiotto]] to win his first feature amidst a [[radio]] issue, before finishing fourth in the sprint.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fia.com/news/f2-leclerc-scorches-feature-victory |title=F2 – Leclerc scorches to feature victory |date=13 May 2017 |website=[[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile]] |access-date=30 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230712025830/https://www.fia.com/news/f2-leclerc-scorches-feature-victory |archive-date=12 July 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/leclerc-column-barcelona-win-adds-to-perfect-start-in-f2-906696/906696/ |title=Leclerc column: Barcelona win adds to perfect start in F2 |last=Leclerc |first=Charles |date=16 May 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=30 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241230230540/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/leclerc-column-barcelona-win-adds-to-perfect-start-in-f2-906696/906696/ |archive-date=30 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc retired from both races at his home round in [[2017 Monte Carlo Formula 2 round|Monte Carlo]] after qualifying on pole, suffering [[Car suspension|suspension]] failure in the feature and collision damage with [[Norman Nato]] in the sprint.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/monaco-f2-rowland-takes-first-win-as-leclerc-retires-5003555/5003555/ |title=Monaco F2: Rowland takes first win as Leclerc retires |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=26 May 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808193301/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/129774 |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/monaco-f2-de-vries-rapax-sprint-race-911283/911283/ |title=Monaco F2: De Vries takes maiden win in Rapax 1–2 |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=27 May 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808155435/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/monaco-f2-de-vries-rapax-sprint-race-911283/?s=1 |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> Whilst retaining his championship lead, he described the weekend as "hugely disappointing".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/charles-leclerc-column-monaco-f2-heartbreak-912533/912533/ |title=Leclerc column: Moving on from Monaco misfortune |last=Leclerc |first=Charles |date=30 May 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808162457/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/charles-leclerc-column-monaco-f2-heartbreak-912533/ |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc dedicated his pole in [[2017 Baku Formula 2 round|Baku]] to his recently deceased father Hervé,<ref name="BAK17"/> before converting it to victory in the feature and second-place in the sprint, losing the win to Nato at the latter following a 10-second time penalty for ignoring [[yellow flag (motorsport)|yellow flag]]s.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/baku-f2-ferrari-junior-charles-leclerc-wins-red-flagged-race-5001107/5001107/ |title=Baku F2: Ferrari junior Charles Leclerc wins red-flagged race |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=24 June 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808072959/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/130343 |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=http://www.fiaformula2.com/Global/F2/2017/07_TheInsider/Insider2017-FIAF2-Issue4.pdf  |title=Baku, Round 4 {{!}} So Close! |date=28 June 2017 |work=The Insider |publisher=[[FIA Formula 2 Championship]] |issue=4 |page=4 |access-date=8 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808155503/http://www.fiaformula2.com/Global/F2/2017/07_TheInsider/Insider2017-FIAF2-Issue4.pdf |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=dead}}</ref> He won the [[2017 Spielberg Formula 2 round|Spielberg]] feature from pole, holding off teammate Fuoco and the [[DAMS]] of [[Nicholas Latifi]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fia.com/news/f2-leclerc-soars-feature-victory |title=F2 – Leclerc soars to feature victory |date=8 July 2017 |website=[[Fédération Internationale de l'Automobile]] |access-date=30 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220902105107/https://www.fia.com/news/f2-leclerc-soars-feature-victory |archive-date=2 September 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc collided with the former in the sprint, reducing his championship lead over [[Oliver Rowland]] to 49 points midway through the season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/artem-markelov-wins-austria-f2-sprint-race-charles-leclerc-crashes-4999864/4999864/ |title=Artem Markelov wins Austria F2 sprint race, Charles Leclerc crashes |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=9 July 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170808153304/http://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/130631 |archive-date=8 August 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Charles Leclerc Jerez 2017 (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc dominated F2 in his rookie season, taking a joint-record seven victories and clinching the championship in [[2017 Jerez Formula 2 round|Jerez]], aged 19.|alt=Charles Leclerc crossing the start/finish line during the 2017 Jerez Formula 2 round]]
Leclerc achieved a record-equalling sixth consecutive pole at [[2017 Silverstone Formula 2 round|Silverstone]],{{efn-num|[[Stoffel Vandoorne]] previously achieved six consecutive pole positions from [[2014 Spa-Francorchamps GP2 Series round|2014 Spa-Francorchamps]] to [[2015 Catalunya GP2 Series round|2015 Catalunya]], when the championship operated as the [[GP2 Series]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/f2-silverstone-ferraris-leclerc-equals-vandoorne-pole-record-4999485/4999485/ |title=F2 Silverstone: Ferrari's Leclerc equals Vandoorne pole record |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=14 July 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230329193535/https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/f2-silverstone-ferraris-leclerc-equals-vandoorne-pole-record-4999485/4999485/ |archive-date=29 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/silverstone-f2-ferrari-junior-leclerc-maintains-perfect-qualifying-streak-930488/930488/ |title=Silverstone F2: Leclerc maintains perfect qualifying streak |last=Gruz |first=David |date=14 July 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241231005550/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/silverstone-f2-ferrari-junior-leclerc-maintains-perfect-qualifying-streak-930488/930488/ |archive-date=31 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>}} winning the feature amidst multiple reliability issues, including his [[brake]]s and [[Exhaust gas|exhaust]] setting on fire.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/leclerc-survives-scare-to-win-silverstone-f2-feature-race/37812 |title=Charles Leclerc survives scare to win Silverstone F2 feature race |last=Allen |first=Peter |date=15 July 2017 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230329044754/https://formulascout.com/leclerc-survives-scare-to-win-silverstone-f2-feature-race/37812 |archive-date=29 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/leclerc-column-silverstone-victory-smoke-lost-mirror-restart-controversy-932438/932438/ |title=Leclerc column: Twice on fire en route to victory |last=Leclerc |first=Charles |date=18 July 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423215229/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/leclerc-column-silverstone-victory-smoke-lost-mirror-restart-controversy-932438/932438/ |archive-date=23 April 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was disqualified from pole in [[2017 Budapest Formula 2 round|Budapest]] for a technical infringement,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://au.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/prema-explains-leclerc-qualifying-dsq-935896/3038453/ |title=Prema explains Leclerc disqualification |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=29 July 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241231012905/https://au.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/prema-explains-leclerc-qualifying-dsq-935896/3038453/ |archive-date=31 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> finishing fourth in the feature and sprint after starting the former in last-place, albeit behind title rival Rowland in both.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fiaformula2.com/Latest/3BYS6RIdTEi0rzxWrStDVu/rowland-on-top-in-dramatic-budapest-feature |title=Rowland on top in dramatic Budapest feature |date=29 July 2017 |website=[[FIA Formula 2 Championship]] |publisher=[[Formula Motorsport Limited]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241231013616/https://www.fiaformula2.com/Latest/3BYS6RIdTEi0rzxWrStDVu/rowland-on-top-in-dramatic-budapest-feature |archive-date=31 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/hungary-f2-honda-f1-junior-matsushita-takes-sprint-race-victory-4998155/4998155/ |title=Hungary F2: Honda F1 junior Matsushita takes sprint race victory |last=Kalinaukas |first=Alex |date=30 July 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241231013147/https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/hungary-f2-honda-f1-junior-matsushita-takes-sprint-race-victory-4998155/4998155/ |archive-date=31 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc returned to pole at [[2017 Spa-Francorchamps Formula 2 round|Spa-Francorchamps]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/spa-formula-2-ferrari-f1-junior-charles-leclerc-on-pole-in-wet-4996789/4996789/ |title=Spa Formula 2: Ferrari F1 junior Charles Leclerc on pole in wet |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=25 August 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210513073906/https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/spa-formula-2-ferrari-f1-junior-charles-leclerc-on-pole-in-wet-4996789/4996789/ |archive-date=13 May 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> but was disqualified from his 25-second winning margin in the feature due to excessive [[skid block]] wear.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://formulascout.com/charles-leclerc-claims-crushing-spa-f2-feature-race-win/37945 |title=Charles Leclerc claims crushing Spa F2 feature race win |last=Allen |first=Peter |date=26 August 2017 |website=Formula Scout |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240529181522/https://formulascout.com/charles-leclerc-claims-crushing-spa-f2-feature-race-win/37945 |archive-date=29 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/spa-formula-2-charles-leclerc-and-oliver-rowland-disqualified-4996546/4996546/ |title=Spa Formula 2: Charles Leclerc and Oliver Rowland disqualified |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=26 August 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231023055107/https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/spa-formula-2-charles-leclerc-and-oliver-rowland-disqualified-4996546/4996546/ |archive-date=23 October 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc recovered to fifth after starting nineteenth in the sprint.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2017/08/27/sette-camara-wins-spa-f2-sprint-race/ |title=Sette Camara wins Spa F2 sprint race |date=27 August 2017 |work=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241231162326/https://racer.com/2017/08/27/sette-camara-wins-spa-f2-sprint-race/ |archive-date=31 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Whilst battling for the lead of the [[2017 Monza Formula 2 round|Monza]] feature with [[Nyck de Vries]], the pair collided on the final lap following a late-race [[safety car]], condemning both drivers to finish outside the points.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fiaformula2.com/Latest/31LrQfdiGzDBNmcLEIBnII/ghiotto-wins-in-dramatic-monza-feature |title=Ghiotto wins in dramatic Monza feature |date=2 September 2017 |website=[[FIA Formula 2 Championship]] |publisher=[[Formula Motorsport Limited]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203235433/https://www.fiaformula2.com/Latest/31LrQfdiGzDBNmcLEIBnII/ghiotto-wins-in-dramatic-monza-feature |archive-date=3 December 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/monza-f2-ghiotto-wins-after-last-lap-de-vries-leclerc-clash-948481/3044098/ |title=Monza F2: Ghiotto wins after last-lap de Vries/Leclerc clash |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=2 September 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211130065700/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/monza-f2-ghiotto-wins-after-last-lap-de-vries-leclerc-clash-948481/3044098/ |archive-date=30 November 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> With a 59-point margin over Rowland heading into the penultimate round at [[2017 Jerez Formula 2 round|Jerez]], Leclerc required pole position and victory to clinch the title in the feature;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/leclerc-column-jerez-title-mishap-lap-count-964048/3051381/ |title=Leclerc column: How lap count mishap nearly delayed F2 title |last=Leclerc |first=Charles |date=10 October 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=6 February 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220321175936/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/leclerc-column-jerez-title-mishap-lap-count-964048/3051381/  |archive-date=21 March 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> after achieving his eighth pole of the season,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/jerez-f2-leclerc-eighth-pole-of-season-962258/3050545/ |title=Jerez F2: Leclerc bags eighth pole of 2017 season |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=6 October 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220219200303/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/jerez-f2-leclerc-eighth-pole-of-season-962258/3050545/ |archive-date=19 February 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> he held off a late charge by Rowland to become the then-youngest GP2/Formula 2 champion—aged 19 years, 356 days—as well as the third rookie champion after [[Lewis Hamilton]], [[Nico Rosberg]], and [[Nico Hülkenberg]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nbcsports.com/motor-sports/news/leclerc-crowned-f2-champion-russell-wins-gp3-title-at-jerez |title=Leclerc crowned F2 champion, Russell wins GP3 title at Jerez |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=9 October 2017 |work=[[NBC Sports]] |publisher=[[NBC]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240412110231/https://www.nbcsports.com/motor-sports/news/leclerc-crowned-f2-champion-russell-wins-gp3-title-at-jerez |archive-date=12 April 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/charles-leclerc-seals-formula-2-title-with-jerez-feature-race-win-4994190/4994190/ |title=Leclerc seals F2 title with Jerez win |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=7 October 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 October 2017 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308051753/https://www.autosport.com/f2/news/132272/leclerc-seals-f2-title-with-jerez-win |archive-date=8 March 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-to-ferrari-the-stats-you-need-to-know.2P534xFSykq2isIYgucm0u |title=Leclerc to Ferrari: The stats you need to know |date=11 September 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241214224052/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-to-ferrari-the-stats-you-need-to-know.2P534xFSykq2isIYgucm0u |archive-date=14 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the season-ending [[2017 Yas Island Formula 2 round|Yas Island]] round, Leclerc inherited second-place in the feature after disqualifications for Rowland and teammate Fuoco.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/abu-dhabi-f2-oliver-rowland-loses-feature-win-fuoco-disqualified-4990706/4990706/ |title=Abu Dhabi F2: Oliver Rowland loses feature win, Fuoco disqualified |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=25 November 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231202154631/https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/abu-dhabi-f2-oliver-rowland-loses-feature-win-fuoco-disqualified-4990706/4990706/ |archive-date=2 December 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Starting seventh for the sprint, he overtook [[Alexander Albon]] on the final lap to secure his record-equalling seventh victory of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/abu-dhabi-leclerc-wins-finale-albon-983002/1380809/ |title=Abu Dhabi F2: Leclerc passes Albon on final lap to win |last=Klein |first=Jamie |date=26 November 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230331214324/https://www.motorsport.com/fia-f2/news/abu-dhabi-leclerc-wins-finale-albon-983002/1380809/ |archive-date=31 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/ferrari-junior-leclerc-wins-f2-finale-with-a-stellar-last-lap-move-4990664/4990664/ |title=Ferrari junior Leclerc wins F2 finale with a stellar last lap move |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=26 November 2017 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614044415/https://www.autosport.com/formula2/news/ferrari-junior-leclerc-wins-f2-finale-with-a-stellar-last-lap-move-4990664/4990664/ |archive-date=14 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/williams-bound-russell-claims-f2-title-in-style-at-yas-marina.30gxo8hzZSWwmaqAU80Oiw |title=Williams-bound Russell claims F2 title in style at Yas Marina |date=24 November 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240912164410/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/williams-bound-russell-claims-f2-title-in-style-at-yas-marina.30gxo8hzZSWwmaqAU80Oiw |archive-date=12 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc was named [[FIA Prize Giving Ceremony#Rookie of the Year|FIA Rookie of the Year]] for his efforts in 2017,<ref name="FIA17"/> achieving seven wins from 10 podiums and eight pole positions, finishing 72 points ahead of eventual runner-up [[Artem Markelov]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.fiaformula2.com/About/2vXGWHs8Qpz3EsMEOa7IG1/hall-of-fame-charles-leclerc |title=Charles Leclerc – 2017 Champion |website=[[FIA Formula 2 Championship]] |publisher=[[Formula Motorsport Limited]] |access-date=31 December 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240720044313/https://www.fiaformula2.com/About/2vXGWHs8Qpz3EsMEOa7IG1/hall-of-fame-charles-leclerc |archive-date=20 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Formula One career ==
[[File:Charles Leclerc - Haas & Felipe Massa - Williams (32724536820).jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc ''(left)'' joined the [[Ferrari Driver Academy]] in {{F1|2016}}, completing four [[free practice]] sessions with [[Haas F1 Team|Haas]].|alt=Leclerc driving the Haas VF-16 in free practice at the 2016 British Grand Prix, ahead of Felipe Massa]]
In {{F1|2016}}, Leclerc joined the [[Ferrari Driver Academy]] and was signed as a development driver for [[Haas F1 Team|Haas]] and [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]].<ref name="FDA">{{Cite web |url=http://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-gets-ferrari-and-haas-development-role-676625/?s=1 |title=Leclerc gets Ferrari and Haas development role |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=1 March 2016 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=1 March 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180630105640/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-gets-ferrari-and-haas-development-role-676625/?s=1 |archive-date=30 June 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his testing debut at [[Fiorano Circuit|Fiorano]] two months later, driving the [[Ferrari F14 T]].<ref name="CAT16"/> As part of his role at Haas, Leclerc participated in the first [[free practice]] sessions of the [[2016 British Grand Prix|British]], [[2016 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungarian]], [[2016 German Grand Prix|German]], and [[2016 Brazilian Grand Prix|Brazilian]] Grands Prix.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/gp3-winner-leclerc-gets-practice-outings-with-haas.3DBA2Za626iH1oss8DaxSY |title=GP3 winner Leclerc gets practice outings with Haas |date=24 June 2016 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241202194429/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/gp3-winner-leclerc-gets-practice-outings-with-haas.3DBA2Za626iH1oss8DaxSY |archive-date=2 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/18078070/charles-leclerc-gives-haas-fp1-appearance-abu-dhabi |title=Charles Leclerc gives up Haas FP1 appearance in Abu Dhabi |last=Saunders |first=Nate |date=18 November 2016 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171016183228/http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/18078070/charles-leclerc-gives-haas-fp1-appearance-abu-dhabi |archive-date=16 October 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-withdraws-from-haas-f1-practice-duties-to-prioritise-gp3-5028914/5028914/ |title=Leclerc withdraws from Haas F1 practice duties to prioritise GP3 |last1=Barretto |first1=Lawrence |last2=Beer |first2=Matt |date=17 November 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119200646/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-withdraws-from-haas-f1-practice-duties-to-prioritise-gp3-5028914/5028914/ |archive-date=19 January 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> After impressing Ferrari at the former, he completed his first official test for the team at [[Silverstone Circuit|Silverstone]] in the [[Ferrari SF16-H|SF16-H]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-gets-ferrari-f1-test-chance-after-impressing-haas-5041006/5041006/ |title=Charles Leclerc gets Ferrari F1 test chance after impressing Haas |last=Barretto |first=Lawrence |date=10 July 2016 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=24 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230312134910/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-gets-ferrari-f1-test-chance-after-impressing-haas-5041006/5041006/ |archive-date=12 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was initially rumoured to graduate direct to Formula One with Haas after winning the [[2016 GP3 Series]];<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/17129581/charles-leclerc-gp3-title-key-2017-f1-hopes |title=Charles Leclerc: GP3 title key to 2017 F1 hopes |last=Larkam |first=Lewis |date=23 July 2016 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=6 September 2016 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171231080125/http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/17129581/charles-leclerc-gp3-title-key-2017-f1-hopes |archive-date=31 December 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> team principal [[Guenther Steiner]] denied the rumours and stated that Leclerc would instead progress to [[2017 FIA Formula 2 Championship|FIA Formula 2]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2016/09/29/haas-rules-out-signing-leclerc-for-2017/ |title=F1: Haas rules out signing Leclerc for 2017 |date=29 September 2016 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127091103/https://racer.com/2016/09/29/haas-rules-out-signing-leclerc-for-2017/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Charles Leclerc 2017 Malaysia FP1.jpg|thumb|right|Leclerc completed four sessions with [[Sauber]] in {{F1|2017}}, as well as the mid-season test with [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]].|alt=Leclerc driving the Sauber C36 in free practice at the 2017 Malaysian Grand Prix]]
Leclerc took part in the {{F1|2017}} mid-season test at the [[Hungaroring]] with Ferrari—driving the [[Ferrari SF70H|SF70H]]—completing 98 laps and setting the fastest lap of the first day.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-heads-day-one-of-budapest-test-for-ferrari.6ven76x06QesO8UsOU6E0M |title=Leclerc heads day one of Budapest test for Ferrari |date=1 August 2017 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=8 August 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240912160030/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-heads-day-one-of-budapest-test-for-ferrari.6ven76x06QesO8UsOU6E0M |archive-date=12 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/20217843/ferrari-youngster-charles-leclerc-tops-opening-hungary-test |title=Ferrari youngster Charles Leclerc tops opening Hungary test |last=Saunders |first=Nate |date=1 August 2017 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170904190116/http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/20217843/ferrari-youngster-charles-leclerc-tops-opening-hungary-test |archive-date=4 September 2017 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Kimi Räikkönen]] praised his performance, stating "it's not easy to do well in a different car from what you normally drive", adding that "for sure he will do great things in the future".<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=http://autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1828826/kimi-raikkonen-praises-ferrari-f1-prospect-charles-leclerc-after-contract/ |title=Kimi Raikkonen praises Ferrari F1 prospect Charles Leclerc after contract extension |date=23 August 2017 |magazine=[[Autoweek]] |publisher=[[Crain Communications]] |access-date=30 May 2020 |issn=0192-9674 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200715002727/https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a1828826/kimi-raikkonen-praises-ferrari-f1-prospect-charles-leclerc-after-contract/ |archive-date=15 July 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc completed further free practice sessions with [[Sauber]] at the [[2017 Malaysian Grand Prix|Malaysian]], [[2017 United States Grand Prix|United States]], [[2017 Mexican Grand Prix|Mexican]], and [[2017 Brazilian Grand Prix|Brazilian]] Grands Prix, after signing with the team for {{F1|2018}}.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/20775411/ferrari-prodigy-charles-leclerc-handed-four-2017-friday-practice-sessions-sauber |title=Ferrari prodigy Charles Leclerc handed four Friday practice sessions by Sauber |last=Saunders |first=Nate |date=21 September 2017 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180312213114/http://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/20775411/ferrari-prodigy-charles-leclerc-handed-four-2017-friday-practice-sessions-sauber |archive-date=12 March 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Sauber (2018) ===
[[File:2018 Chinese Grand Prix FP3 Charles Leclerc (39897914770) (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc (pictured at the {{F1GP|2018|Chinese}}) debuted in Formula One with [[Sauber]] in {{F1|2018}}.|alt=Leclerc driving the Sauber C37 at the 2018 Chinese Grand Prix]]
Leclerc signed for [[Sauber]] in {{F1|2018}} as a full-time driver, replacing [[Pascal Wehrlein]] to partner [[Marcus Ericsson]].<ref name="2018contract">{{Cite web |url=https://au.motorsport.com/f1/news/sauber-confirms-ericsson-leclerc-for-2018-f1-season-985150/1381840/ |title=Sauber confirms Ericsson alongside Leclerc for 2018 |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=2 December 2017 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=2 December 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230223212952/https://au.motorsport.com/f1/news/sauber-confirms-ericsson-leclerc-for-2018-f1-season-985150/1381840/ |archive-date=23 February 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11108517/f1-2018-charles-leclerc-and-marcus-ericsson-confirmed-at-sauber |title=F1 2018: Charles Leclerc and Marcus Ericsson confirmed at Sauber |last1=Green |first1=Jonathan |last2=Galloway |first2=James |date=4 December 2017 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240918164831/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11108517/f1-2018-charles-leclerc-and-marcus-ericsson-confirmed-at-sauber |archive-date=18 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> With his debut at the {{F1GP|2018|Australian}}, Leclerc became the [[Formula One drivers from Monaco|first Monégasque driver]] to compete in Formula One since [[Olivier Beretta]] in {{F1|1994}}.{{efn-num|Beretta was the last Monégasque national to compete in Formula One; Dutch driver [[Robert Doornbos]] competed under a Monégasque licence in {{F1|2005}}.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ferrari.com/en-EN/formula1/articles/monaco-grand-prix-2021-preview |title=In Charles’ backyard after a one year break |date=18 May 2021 |website=[[Scuderia Ferrari]] |publisher=[[Ferrari]] |access-date=24 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230723174315/https://www.ferrari.com/en-EN/formula1/articles/monaco-grand-prix-2021-preview |archive-date=23 July 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.com/article/promising-charles-leclerc-to-race-on-monaco-streets-he-grew-up-on-kvps2h9pl |title=Promising Charles Leclerc to race on Monaco streets he grew up on |last=Clancy |first=Rebecca |date=23 May 2018 |work=[[The Times]] |publisher=[[News UK]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0140-0460 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127100840/https://www.thetimes.com/article/promising-charles-leclerc-to-race-on-monaco-streets-he-grew-up-on-kvps2h9pl |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>}} He qualified eighteenth and finished thirteenth on debut.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2018/03/25/motorsport/f1-leclerc-bianchi-ferrari-sauber/index.html |title=Charles Leclerc impresses on debut in Australia |date=25 March 2018 |work=[[CNN]] |publisher=[[WarnerMedia]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221207194725/https://edition.cnn.com/2018/03/25/motorsport/f1-leclerc-bianchi-ferrari-sauber/index.html |archive-date=7 December 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> After non-scoring finishes in [[2018 Bahrain Grand Prix|Bahrain]] and [[2018 Chinese Grand Prix|China]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/live/formula1/43420536 |title=How dramatic Bahrain GP unfolded |date=8 April 2018 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127104037/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/live/formula1/43420536 |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/sauber-f1-rookie-charles-leclerc-confused-by-chinese-gp-spin-5322154/5322154/ |title=Sauber F1 rookie Charles Leclerc confused by Chinese GP spin |last=Mitchell |first=Scott |date=16 April 2018 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231129093406/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/sauber-f1-rookie-charles-leclerc-confused-by-chinese-gp-spin-5322154/5322154/ |archive-date=29 November 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> a sixth-placed finish at the {{F1GP|2018|Azerbaijan}} saw him become the first Monégasque driver to score [[List of Formula One World Championship points scoring systems|points]] in Formula One since [[Louis Chiron]] in [[1950 Monaco Grand Prix|1950]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/sixth-like-a-win-first-time-points-scorer-leclerc.y3pnYEGtQ402eecAIsc44 |title=Sixth 'like a win' – first time points-scorer Leclerc |date=30 April 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240613005913/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/sixth-like-a-win-first-time-points-scorer-leclerc.y3pnYEGtQ402eecAIsc44 |archive-date=13 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored another point by finishing tenth at the {{F1GP|2018|Spanish}}.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/may/13/lewis-hamilton-wins-spain-lead-f1-title-race |title=Lewis Hamilton wins Spanish Grand Prix to stretch lead in F1 title race |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=13 May 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241225110312/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/may/13/lewis-hamilton-wins-spain-lead-f1-title-race |archive-date=25 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> At his first [[2018 Monaco Grand Prix|home Grand Prix in Monaco]], Leclerc suffered a brake failure in the closing laps, colliding with the [[diffuser (automotive)|diffuser]] of [[Brendon Hartley]] into the ''[[Circuit de Monaco|Nouvelle Chicane]]'' and forcing his first career retirement.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/brake-disc-failure-to-blame-for-leclerc-hartley-collision.3Kl1jE4UV2CMaiwA8yEw8i |title=Brake disc failure to blame for Leclerc–Hartley collision |date=27 May 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240713224912/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/brake-disc-failure-to-blame-for-leclerc-hartley-collision.3Kl1jE4UV2CMaiwA8yEw8i |archive-date=13 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/monaco-grand-prix-f1-stewards-exonerate-leclerc-over-hartley-crash-5319980/5319980/ |title=Monaco Grand Prix F1 stewards exonerate Leclerc over Hartley crash |last1=Freeman |first1=Glenn |last2=Codling |first2=Stuart |date=27 May 2018 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240616021902/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/monaco-grand-prix-f1-stewards-exonerate-leclerc-over-hartley-crash-5319980/5319980/ |archive-date=16 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Three consecutive points finishes followed in [[2018 Canadian Grand Prix|Canada]], [[2018 French Grand Prix|France]], and [[2018 Austrian Grand Prix|Austria]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/austria-result-a-huge-boost-for-sauber-leclerc.I4b2efS8g0EUComM6O4GG |title=Austria result a ‘huge boost’ for Sauber – Leclerc |date=2 July 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240718224642/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/austria-result-a-huge-boost-for-sauber-leclerc.I4b2efS8g0EUComM6O4GG |archive-date=18 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> before going five races without points.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/singapore-race-close-to-being-perfect-leclerc.5W3JUNveMgWKA4eY28YccI |title=Singapore race 'close to being perfect' – Leclerc |date=17 September 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240805163628/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/singapore-race-close-to-being-perfect-leclerc.5W3JUNveMgWKA4eY28YccI |archive-date=5 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> This run included three retirements: a loose wheel in [[2018 British Grand Prix|Britain]], [[Car suspension|suspension]] damage after colliding with [[Sergio Pérez]] in [[2018 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]], and a multi-car collision in [[2018 Belgian Grand Prix|Belgium]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2018/07/09/supreme-silverstone-adjusted-2018-british-grand-prix-driver/ |url-access=registration |title=Who was supreme at Silverstone? Adjusted 2018 British Grand Prix driver ratings |last=Slater |first=Luke |date=9 July 2018 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530163146/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2018/07/09/supreme-silverstone-adjusted-2018-british-grand-prix-driver/ |archive-date=30 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2018-hungarian-grand-prix-report/ |url-access=registration |title=2018 Hungarian Grand Prix report |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=30 July 2018 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240904173251/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2018-hungarian-grand-prix-report/ |archive-date=4 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/45314905 |title=Sebastian Vettel wins in Belgium after dramatic crash |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=26 August 2018 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230720145204/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/45314905 |archive-date=20 July 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc credited the [[halo device]] with saving him from severe injury during the latter, stating that he "was very happy to have it over [his] head".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/aug/27/charles-leclerc-thanks-halo-belgian-grand-prix-crash-fernando-alonso |title=Charles Leclerc pays tribute to halo after walking away from Belgian GP crash |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=27 August 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240726031424/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/aug/27/charles-leclerc-thanks-halo-belgian-grand-prix-crash-fernando-alonso |archive-date=26 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.roadandtrack.com/motorsports/a22839224/belgian-grand-prix-alonso-leclerc-halo-crash/ |title=Terrifying Belgian GP crash Shows How Well the Formula 1 Halo Works |last=Perkins |first=Chris |date=27 August 2018 |magazine=[[Road & Track]] |publisher=[[Hearst Magazines]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0035-7189 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220927205159/https://www.roadandtrack.com/motorsports/a22839224/belgian-grand-prix-alonso-leclerc-halo-crash/ |archive-date=27 September 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Further points finishes came with ninth- and seventh-place at the [[2018 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]] and [[2018 Russian Grand Prix|Russian]] Grands Prix, respectively,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/russia-debutant-leclerc-reflects-on-%27amazing-race%27-to-p7.zgQHcn4a5iuQqIISuqOAi |title=Russia debutant Leclerc reflects on 'amazing race' to P7 |date=30 September 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240617143931/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/russia-debutant-leclerc-reflects-on-'amazing-race'-to-p7.zgQHcn4a5iuQqIISuqOAi |archive-date=17 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> before retirements from a mechanical failure in [[2018 Japanese Grand Prix|Japan]] and damage from a collision with [[Romain Grosjean]] in the [[2018 United States Grand Prix|United States]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-left-unimpressed-with-%27stupid%27-magnussen.2ll93icC4IQmsQ4M6QcucI |title=Leclerc left unimpressed with 'stupid' Magnussen |date=7 October 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240625055600/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-left-unimpressed-with-'stupid'-magnussen.2ll93icC4IQmsQ4M6QcucI |archive-date=25 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/kevin-magnussen-excluded-from-f1-united-states-grand-prix-5290347/5290347/ |title=Kevin Magnussen excluded from F1 United States Grand Prix |last=
Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=21 October 2018 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240916155708/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/kevin-magnussen-excluded-from-f1-united-states-grand-prix-5290347/5290347/ |archive-date=16 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc closed his rookie season with three consecutive seventh-placed finishes in [[2018 Mexican Grand Prix|Mexico]], [[2018 Brazilian Grand Prix|Brazil]], and [[2018 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix|Abu Dhabi]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/f1-2018-mexican-grand-prix-report.43bcuMZV3i8yk2a8kQw06w |title=Verstappen wins in Mexico as Hamilton clinches fifth world title |date=28 October 2018 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240806151026/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/f1-2018-mexican-grand-prix-report.43bcuMZV3i8yk2a8kQw06w |archive-date=6 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/nov/11/lewis-hamilton-brazilian-grand-prix-max-verstappen |title=Verstappen shoves 'idiot' Ocon in clash following Hamilton's Brazil win |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=11 November 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240402121008/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/nov/11/lewis-hamilton-brazilian-grand-prix-max-verstappen |archive-date=2 April 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2018-abu-dhabi-grand-prix-report |url-access=registration |title=2018 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix report |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=26 November 2018 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220809234147/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2018-abu-dhabi-grand-prix-report |archive-date=9 August 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc finished thirteenth in the [[World Drivers' Championship]], with 39 points to teammate Ericsson's nine,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.redbull.com/au-en/f1-season-review-and-report-2018 |title=The F1 2018 report |last=Clayton |first=Matthew |date=2 December 2018 |website=[[Red Bull]] |publisher=[[Red Bull GmbH]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127134127/https://www.redbull.com/au-en/f1-season-review-and-report-2018 |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/ericsson-left-f1-strongest-season/4314568/ |title=Ericsson feels he left F1 after "strongest" season |last1=Mitchell
|first1=Scott |last2=Straw |first2=Edd |date=18 December 2018 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108191937/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/ericsson-left-f1-strongest-season/4314568/ |archive-date=8 November 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> and was again named [[FIA Prize Giving Ceremony#Rookie of the Year|FIA Rookie of the Year]].<ref name="FIA18"/>

=== Ferrari (2019–present) ===

==== 2019: Maiden victories and ''il Predestinato'' ====
[[File:2019 Formula One Test Days - Charles Leclerc's Ferrari SF90.jpg|thumb|Leclerc moved to [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]] in {{F1|2019}}, his second season in Formula One.|alt=Leclerc driving the Ferrari SF90 at 2019 Formula One pre-season testing]]
Leclerc signed for [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]] in {{F1|2019}}, swapping seats with [[Kimi Räikkönen]] to partner four-time World Drivers' Champion [[Sebastian Vettel]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/sep/11/kimi-raikkonen-to-leave-ferrari-f1-team-at-end-of-season |title=Charles Leclerc to replace Kimi Raikkonen as Ferrari ring changes |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=11 September 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221029130338/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2018/sep/11/kimi-raikkonen-to-leave-ferrari-f1-team-at-end-of-season |archive-date=29 October 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Then-team principal [[Maurizio Arrivabene]] stated that his contract would run until 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-ferrari-contract-until-2022/3176733/  |title=Ferrari signed Leclerc until at least 2022 |last=Cooper |first=Adam |date=14 September 2018 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=14 September 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180914204908/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-ferrari-contract-until-2022/3176733/ |archive-date=14 September 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc entered the 2018 post-season test with Ferrari at [[Yas Marina Circuit|Yas Marina]], setting the fastest time in the [[Ferrari SF71H|SF71H]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-fastest-ferrari-abu-dhabi-test/4305506/ |title=Leclerc leads second morning of Abu Dhabi test |last=Mitchell |first=Scott |date=28 November 2018 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=28 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181128164540/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-fastest-ferrari-abu-dhabi-test/4305506/ |archive-date=28 November 2018 |url-status=live}}</ref> He debuted for the team at the {{F1GP|2019|Australian}}, qualifying and finishing fifth.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2019-australian-grand-prix-report/ |url-access=registration |title=2019 Australian Grand Prix report |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=18 March 2019 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=25 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230926134213/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2019-australian-grand-prix-report/ |archive-date=26 September 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2019 Bahrain Grand Prix|Bahrain]], Leclerc took his maiden [[List of Formula One polesitters|pole position]] to become the [[List of Formula One driver records#Youngest polesitters|second-youngest polesitter in Formula One history]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/47760616 |title=Bahrain Grand Prix: Ferrari's Charles Leclerc takes maiden pole position |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=30 March 2019 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230410095819/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/47760616 |archive-date=10 April 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He led the majority of the race before suffering an engine issue with 10 laps remaining; overtaken by both [[Mercedes-Benz in Formula One|Mercedes]] drivers, he finished third, securing his maiden podium finish.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.repubblica.it/sport/formulauno/2019/03/31/news/formula_1_gp_barhain_hamilton_leclerc_bottas-222973148 |title=Formula 1, Gp del {{as written|Barhain| [sic]}}: Hamilton vince ma ammette: "Meritava la Ferrari di Leclerc" |trans-title=Formula 1, Bahrain GP; Hamilton wins but admits: "the Ferrari of Leclerc deserved it" |last=Retico |first=Alessandra |date=31 March 2019 |work=[[la Repubblica]] |publisher=[[GEDI Gruppo Editoriale]] |language=it |issn=0390-1076 |access-date=31 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331184120/https://www.repubblica.it/sport/formulauno/2019/03/31/news/formula_1_gp_barhain_hamilton_leclerc_bottas-222973148/ |archive-date=31 March 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc finished fifth in [[2019 Chinese Grand Prix|China]], [[2019 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan]], and [[2019 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]]—behind Vettel at the former and latter after being [[Team orders|ordered to let him pass]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11688577/ferrari-expand-on-charles-leclerc-sebastian-vettel-orders-in-china |title=Ferrari expand on Charles Leclerc, Sebastian Vettel orders in China |last=Galloway |first=James |date=15 April 2019 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=9 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190510082023/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11688577/ferrari-expand-on-charles-leclerc-sebastian-vettel-orders-in-china |archive-date=10 May 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.espn.com/f1/story/_/id/26627312/ferrari-explains-charles-leclerc-azerbaijan-grand-prix-strategy |title=Ferrari explains Charles Leclerc's Azerbaijan Grand Prix strategy |last=Saunders |first=Nate |date=28 April 2019 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=9 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190505063215/http://www.espn.com/f1/story/_/id/26627312/ferrari-explains-charles-leclerc-azerbaijan-grand-prix-strategy |archive-date=5 May 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/05/12/f1-spanish-grand-prix-2019-live-news-results-lewis-hamilton/ |url-access=registration |title=Flawless Lewis Hamilton leads home Valtteri Bottas for Spanish GP win and fifth consecutive Mercedes one–two |last1=Brown |first1=Oliver |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=12 May 2019 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240518005744/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/05/12/f1-spanish-grand-prix-2019-live-news-results-lewis-hamilton/ |archive-date=18 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the {{F1GP|2019|Monaco}}, he qualified sixteenth following a team strategy error; he suffered a race-ending tyre puncture after an overtake attempt on [[Nico Hülkenberg]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/05/26/local-boycharles-leclerc-crashes-monaco-gp-consoled-byprincess/ |url-access=registration |title=Local boy Charles Leclerc crashes out of Monaco GP but is consoled by Princess Charlene of Monaco |last=Brown |first=Oliver |date=26 May 2019 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241227095121/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/05/26/local-boycharles-leclerc-crashes-monaco-gp-consoled-byprincess/ |archive-date=27 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc qualified and finished third at both the [[2019 Canadian Grand Prix|Canadian]] and [[2019 French Grand Prix|French]] Grands Prix.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jun/09/lewis-hamilton-canadian-grand-prix-vettel-penalty |title=Lewis Hamilton handed Canadian GP win after Vettel's penalty pain |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=9 June 2019 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241203061418/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/jun/09/lewis-hamilton-canadian-grand-prix-vettel-penalty |archive-date=3 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/french-grand-prix-live-stream-latest-updates-f1-what-time-tv-channel-how-to-watch-hamilton-vettel-bottas-leclerc-a8970886.html |title=French Grand Prix 2019: Lewis Hamilton powers to victory to stretch F1 championship lead over Valtteri Bottas |last=de Menezes |first=Jack |date=23 June 2019 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220707145709/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/french-grand-prix-live-stream-latest-updates-f1-what-time-tv-channel-how-to-watch-hamilton-vettel-bottas-leclerc-a8970886.html |archive-date=7 July 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> He took pole at the {{F1GP|2019|Austrian}}, finishing second to [[Max Verstappen]] after his overtake on the third-to-last lap, during which they made contact—the stewards' investigation deemed it a [[Glossary of motorsport terms#R|racing incident]].<ref name="AUT19">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/austria-f1-2019-retrospective-the-defeat-that-sharpened-leclercs-teeth-4981664/4981664/ |title=Austria F1 2019 retrospective: The defeat that sharpened Leclerc's teeth |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=27 June 2020 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=23 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241112145505/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/austria-f1-2019-retrospective-the-defeat-that-sharpened-leclercs-teeth-4981664/4981664/ |archive-date=12 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> The pair engaged in a close battle throughout the {{F1GP|2019|British}}, with Leclerc finishing ahead in third to secure his fourth consecutive podium.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/48981658 |title=Lewis Hamilton wins record sixth British Grand Prix after Sebastian Vettel crash |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=14 July 2019 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230812065203/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/48981658 |archive-date=12 August 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He qualified in tenth-place in [[2019 German Grand Prix|Germany]] amidst a fuel system issue; he climbed to fourth in the rain-affected race before being called in for [[racing slick|dry tyres]] too early, causing him to lose traction and collide with the barriers.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2019-german-grand-prix-race-report-verstappen-stars-after-mercedes-meltdown/ |url-access=registration |title=2019 German Grand Prix race report – Verstappen stars after Mercedes meltdown |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=29 July 2019 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240518220347/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2019-german-grand-prix-race-report-verstappen-stars-after-mercedes-meltdown/ |archive-date=18 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He then finished fourth in [[2019 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/08/04/hungarian-grand-prix-2019-f1-live-updates-budapest-results-lewis/ |title=Lewis Hamilton chases down Max Verstappen for Hungarian GP victory to take commanding lead into break |url-access=registration |last1=Brown |first1=Oliver |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=4 August 2019 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240528145858/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/08/04/hungarian-grand-prix-2019-f1-live-updates-budapest-results-lewis/ |archive-date=28 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:Leclerc Hamilton 2019 Italian Grand Prix.jpg|left|thumb|Leclerc won the {{F1GP|2019|Italian}} amidst a battle with [[Lewis Hamilton]], which saw him nicknamed ''il Predestinato'' in Italian media.|alt=Leclerc racing against Lewis Hamilton at the 2019 Italian Grand Prix, with dirt being kicked up by Hamilton's tyres, who is partially off-track]]
Leclerc took pole for the {{F1GP|2019|Belgian}}, fending off [[Lewis Hamilton]] to become the [[List of Formula One driver records#Youngest winners|third-youngest Formula One Grand Prix winner]]—aged 21—as well as the [[Formula One drivers from Monaco|first Monégasque]].<ref name="BEL19">{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/09/01/belgian-grand-prix-2019-f1-live-updates-spa-francorchamps-results/ |url-access=registration |title=Belgian Grand Prix winner Charles Leclerc dedicates maiden victory to Anthoine Hubert |last1=Duncan |first1=Phil |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=1 September 2019 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241211080512/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/09/01/belgian-grand-prix-2019-f1-live-updates-spa-francorchamps-results/ |archive-date=11 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2019-formula-1-belgian-grand-prix-race-results/ |url-access=registration |title=2019 Formula 1 Belgian Grand Prix – race results |date=1 September 2019 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230928051721/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2019-formula-1-belgian-grand-prix-race-results/ |archive-date=28 September 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He dedicated his victory to [[Anthoine Hubert]], who was [[2019 Spa-Francorchamps FIA Formula 2 round|killed the day prior in FIA Formula 2]].<ref name="BEL19"/> Leclerc then won the {{F1GP|2019|Italian}} from pole, defending the lead from both Mercedes drivers to become the first Ferrari winner at [[Monza Circuit|Monza]] since [[Fernando Alonso]] in [[2010 Italian Grand Prix|2010]];<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/sep/08/ferrari-charles-leclerc-italian-f1-gp-monza-win |title=Ferrari's Charles Leclerc delights Italian F1 GP crowd with Monza win |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=8 September 2019 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230614024933/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/sep/08/ferrari-charles-leclerc-italian-f1-gp-monza-win |archive-date=14 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> his victories saw him nicknamed ''il Predestinato'' ({{lit|the [[Predestined]]}}) in Italian media.{{efn|name=ilP|Per several sources: <ref name="ilP1">{{Cite news |url=https://autosprint.corrieredellosport.it/news/sterzi-a-parte/2019/09/30-2400576/ora_basta_definire_charlesil_predestinato |title=Ora basta definire Charles il "Predestinato" |trans-title=Now just call Charles the "Predestined" |last=Donnini |first=Mario |date=30 September 2019 |work=[[Corriere dello Sport|Autosprint]] |publisher=[[Corriere dello Sport]] |language=it |issn=2531-3843 |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220102152017/https://autosprint.corrieredellosport.it/news/sterzi-a-parte/2019/09/30-2400576/ora_basta_definire_charlesil_predestinato |archive-date=2 January 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="ilP2">{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.gqitalia.it/sport/article/leclerc-ferrari-vince-gran-premio-monza-2019 |title=Leclerc con la Ferrari vince il Gran Premio di Monza 2019 |trans-title=Leclerc wins the 2019 Monza Grand Prix with Ferrari |last=Bonfanti |first=Francesco |date=8 September 2019 |magazine=[[GQ Italia]] |publisher=[[Condé Nast]] |language=it |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0016-6979 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221129221235/https://www.gqitalia.it/sport/article/leclerc-ferrari-vince-gran-premio-monza-2019 |archive-date=29 November 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="ilP3">{{Cite web |url=https://sport.sky.it/formula-1/2019/09/01/charles-leclerc-biografia |title=Formula 1, dalle origini al trionfo in Belgio: la storia di Charles Leclerc |trans-title=Formula 1, from the origins to triumph in Belgium: the story of Charles Leclerc |last=Principi |first=Federico |date=1 September 2019 |website=[[Sky Sport (Italy)|Sky Sport]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |language=it |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240713170823/https://sport.sky.it/formula-1/2019/09/01/charles-leclerc-biografia |archive-date=13 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="ilP4">{{Cite news |url=https://www.ilpiccolo.it/sport/marea-rossa-a-monza-la-ferrari-di-leclerc-si-fa-strada-fino-al-trionfo-mzk3j5ki |title=Marea rossa a Monza la Ferrari di Leclerc si fa strada fino al trionfo |trans-title=Red tide in Monza as the Ferrari of Leclerc makes its way to triumph |date=9 September 2019 |work=[[Il Piccolo]] |publisher=[[GEDI Gruppo Editoriale]] |language=it |issn=1723-2635 |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250128073014/https://www.ilpiccolo.it/sport/marea-rossa-a-monza-la-ferrari-di-leclerc-si-fa-strada-fino-al-trionfo-mzk3j5ki |archive-date=28 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="ilP5">{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/it/star/a28960284/charles-leclerc-monza-biografia-news/ |title=Ma come abbiamo fatto a non accorgerci di Charles Leclerc? Ci voleva il podio Ferrari a Monza |trans-title=But how did we not notice Charles Leclerc? It took the Ferrari podium in Monza |last=Gallo |first=Giovanna |date=9 September 2019 |magazine=[[Cosmopolitan (magazine)|Cosmopolitan]] |publisher=[[Hearst Communications]] |language=it |issn=1121-547X |access-date=27 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024023757/https://www.cosmopolitan.com/it/star/a28960284/charles-leclerc-monza-biografia-news/ |archive-date=24 October 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>}} He took pole again in [[2019 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]] and finished second after being [[Glossary of motorsport terms#U|undercut]] by teammate Vettel, promoting him to third in the championship.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/sep/22/sebastian-vettel-singapore-grand-prix-ferrari |title=Sebastian Vettel wins F1 Singapore Grand Prix in Ferrari one–two |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=22 September 2019 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230613100835/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/sep/22/sebastian-vettel-singapore-grand-prix-ferrari |archive-date=13 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc described the strategy as "unfair", to which team principal [[Mattia Binotto]] responded that Vettel was allowed to pit first to defend his position.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11817238/ferrari-explain-sebastian-vettel-charles-leclerc-calls-in-singapore |title=Ferrari explain Sebastian Vettel, Charles Leclerc calls in Singapore |last1=Galloway |first1=James |last2=Morlidge |first2=Matt |date=23 September 2019 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240203165721/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11817238/ferrari-explain-sebastian-vettel-charles-leclerc-calls-in-singapore |archive-date=3 February 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2019 Russian Grand Prix|Russia]], he took his fourth consecutive pole and finished third, after a [[virtual safety car]] saw both Mercedes drivers pass Leclerc with shortened [[pit stop]]s.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/09/29/russian-grand-prix-2019-f1-live-updates-sochi-results-lewis/ |url-access=registration |title=Lewis Hamilton leads Mercedes 1–2 in Russian GP as Sebastian Vettel defies Ferrari team orders |last1=Duncan |first1=Phil |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=29 September 2019 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250121090100/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/09/29/russian-grand-prix-2019-f1-live-updates-sochi-results-lewis/ |archive-date=21 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.deliciously-ironic-that-vettel-failure-inspired-hamilton-victory-mercedes.5YoCZ0E8KAt6Hq58XWfn2M.html |title='Deliciously ironic' that Vettel failure inspired Hamilton victory – Mercedes |date=29 September 2019 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=30 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190930084828/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.deliciously-ironic-that-vettel-failure-inspired-hamilton-victory-mercedes.5YoCZ0E8KAt6Hq58XWfn2M.html |archive-date=30 September 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref> He qualified second at the {{F1GP|2019|Japanese}},<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/form-vettel-takes-pole-position-2019-f1-japanese-grand-prix-qualifying/ |url-access=registration |title=In-form Vettel takes pole position: 2019 F1 Japanese Grand Prix qualifying |last=Dodgins |first=Tony |date=13 October 2019 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240528144135/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/form-vettel-takes-pole-position-2019-f1-japanese-grand-prix-qualifying/ |archive-date=28 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> but took damage in a first-lap collision with Verstappen after [[understeer]]ing into his sidepod;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/27833451/verstappen-slams-stewards-irresponsible-leclerc |title=Verstappen slams stewards and 'irresponsible' Leclerc |date=13 October 2019 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240816082251/https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/27833451/verstappen-slams-stewards-irresponsible-leclerc |archive-date=16 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he finished sixth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11843333/renaults-daniel-ricciardo-and-nico-hulkenberg-stripped-of-japan-grand-prix-points |title=Renault's Daniel Ricciardo and Nico Hulkenberg disqualified from Japanese GP for use of 'driver aid' |date=24 October 2019 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221225114935/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/11843333/renaults-daniel-ricciardo-and-nico-hulkenberg-stripped-of-japan-grand-prix-points |archive-date=25 December 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc finished fourth at the [[2019 Mexican Grand Prix|Mexican]] and [[2019 United States Grand Prix|United States]] Grands Prix,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/oct/27/lewis-hamilton-wins-mexico-grand-prix-wait-for-title |title=Lewis Hamilton claims Mexico Grand Prix but has to wait for title |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=27 October 2019 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230221095134/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2019/oct/27/lewis-hamilton-wins-mexico-grand-prix-wait-for-title |archive-date=21 February 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/50283946 |title=Lewis Hamilton wins sixth F1 World Championship at United States Grand Prix |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=3 November 2019 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230720143737/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/50283946 |archive-date=20 July 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> inheriting pole at the former after a [[Glossary of motorsport terms#G|grid penalty]] for Verstappen.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/10/26/f1-mexican-grand-prix-2019-qualifying-live-updates-mexico-city/ |url-access=registration |title=Max Verstappen stripped of pole as Valtteri Bottas is rushed to medical centre after final-corner crash |last1=Brown |first1=Oliver |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=26 October 2019 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201123125125/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2019/10/26/f1-mexican-grand-prix-2019-qualifying-live-updates-mexico-city/ |archive-date=23 November 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> A collision with Vettel caused both drivers to retire from the {{F1GP|2019|Brazilian}}, with Leclerc dropping below Verstappen in the standings.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/the-winners-and-losers-of-the-brazilian-grand-prix-2019.7rmlodlLkIFGfkFFmzVtZ2 |title=The Winners and Losers of the Brazilian Grand Prix |last=Barretto |first=Lawrence |date=18 November 2019 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240623212447/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/the-winners-and-losers-of-the-brazilian-grand-prix-2019.7rmlodlLkIFGfkFFmzVtZ2 |archive-date=23 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Both were reprimanded by Binotto, who stated they "should be sorry for the team".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/ferrari-drivers-set-for-talks-this-week-after-brazilian-gp-collision.3MgnAz1VNI7gy86BGjirD4 |title=Ferrari drivers set for talks this week after Brazilian GP collision |date=19 November 2019 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250112142220/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/ferrari-drivers-set-for-talks-this-week-after-brazilian-gp-collision.3MgnAz1VNI7gy86BGjirD4 |archive-date=12 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc finished the season-ending {{F1GP|2019|Abu Dhabi}} in third-place, clinching fourth in the World Drivers' Championship with 264 [[List of Formula One World Championship points scoring systems|points]], 24 ahead of teammate Vettel in fifth.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/hamilton-crowns-f1-title-crushing-win-2019-abu-dhabi-grand-prix-report |url-access=registration |title=Hamilton crowns F1 title with crushing win: 2019 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix report |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=1 December 2019 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220925030400/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/hamilton-crowns-f1-title-crushing-win-2019-abu-dhabi-grand-prix-report |archive-date=25 September 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="AS2019">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-first-ferrari-f1-season-better-than-i-expected-4984831/4984831/ |title=Charles Leclerc: First Ferrari F1 season better than I expected |last=Mitchell |first=Scott |date=17 December 2019 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=23 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240623035914/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-first-ferrari-f1-season-better-than-i-expected-4984831/4984831/ |archive-date=23 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> In addition to winning the [[FIA Pole Trophy]] with seven poles,<ref name="FIA19"/> Leclerc recorded two victories from 10 podiums,<ref name="AS2019"/> was awarded the [[Lorenzo Bandini Trophy]],<ref name="LBT"/> and extended his Ferrari contract until the end of 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-ferrari-contract-2024-vettel/4616117/ |title=Leclerc extends Ferrari F1 contract until 2024 |last=Elizalde |first=Pablo |date=23 December 2019 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241127094151/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-ferrari-contract-2024-vettel/4616117/ |archive-date=27 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2020–2021: Winless seasons for Ferrari ====
[[File:2020 F1 Pre-Season Testing Catalonia (49629830792).jpg|thumb|Leclerc (pictured at [[2020 Formula One pre-season testing|pre-season testing]]) achieved two podiums in {{F1|2020}}, driving the [[Ferrari SF1000|SF1000]].|alt=From above, Leclerc parked in the pit lane, with mechanics putting tyre blankets on his Ferrari SF1000 at 2020 Formula One pre-season testing]]
The {{F1|2020}} season was [[2020 Formula One World Championship#Impact of the COVID-19 pandemic|delayed and shortened]] due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/08/07/sports/autoracing/formula-1-season-coronavirus.html |url-access=registration |title=A Formula 1 Season Like No Other |last=Parkes |first=Ian |date=7 August 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |access-date=29 January 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240418011445/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/08/07/sports/autoracing/formula-1-season-coronavirus.html |archive-date=18 April 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Ferrari struggled for performance with the [[Ferrari SF1000|SF1000]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2020-wont-get-any-easier-for-ferrari/ |title=2020 won't get any easier for Ferrari |last=Parkes |first=Ian |date=7 July 2020 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530160413/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2020-wont-get-any-easier-for-ferrari/ |archive-date=30 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/how-ferraris-2020-design-has-caused-a-perfect-storm/ |title=How Ferrari's 2020 design has caused a perfect storm |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=10 July 2020 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=29 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230407104035/https://the-race.com/formula-1/how-ferraris-2020-design-has-caused-a-perfect-storm/ |archive-date=7 April 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12061716/ferrari-struggles-before-italian-gp-whats-gone-wrong-and-what-now |title=Ferrari struggles before Italian GP: What's gone wrong, and what now? |last=Morlidge |first=Matt |date=3 September 2020 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240524172727/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12061716/ferrari-struggles-before-italian-gp-whats-gone-wrong-and-what-now |archive-date=24 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> with Leclerc qualifying seventh for the season-opening {{F1GP|2020|Austrian}}.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/qualifying-report-scintillating-bottas-takes-masterful-pole-as-ferrari.9DCxyNAuIA3gywPVRvyc3 |title=Qualifying Report: Bottas beats Hamilton to pole as Ferrari struggle in Austria |date=4 July 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240907120111/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/qualifying-report-scintillating-bottas-takes-masterful-pole-as-ferrari.9DCxyNAuIA3gywPVRvyc3 |archive-date=7 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He recovered to third-place in the race via several overtakes following the final [[safety car]], promoted to second after a penalty for [[Lewis Hamilton]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/jul/05/valtteri-bottas-wins-f1-austrian-grand-prix-after-hamilton-suffers-penalty |title=Valtteri Bottas wins F1 Austrian Grand Prix after Hamilton suffers penalty |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=5 July 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230324022327/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/jul/05/valtteri-bottas-wins-f1-austrian-grand-prix-after-hamilton-suffers-penalty |archive-date=24 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/bottas-beats-leclerc-and-norris-to-win-dramatic-austrian-gp-as-hamilton-is.4hTWtVVkWLxgPKSqkmKfYF |title=Bottas beats Leclerc and Norris to win dramatic Austrian GP as Hamilton is penalised |date=5 July 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240911175256/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/bottas-beats-leclerc-and-norris-to-win-dramatic-austrian-gp-as-hamilton-is.4hTWtVVkWLxgPKSqkmKfYF |archive-date=11 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> In the build-up to the {{F1GP|2020|Styrian}}, Leclerc was investigated by the [[FIA]] for allegedly breaching [[COVID-19]] safety protocols whilst returning home to [[Monte Carlo]] with permission from Ferrari;<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/jul/09/bottas-and-leclerc-investigated-f1-covid-19-rules |title=Bottas and Leclerc to be investigated for breaking F1's Covid-19 rules |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=9 July 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221129034852/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/jul/09/bottas-and-leclerc-investigated-f1-covid-19-rules |archive-date=29 November 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> both Leclerc and Ferrari were given a warning for the incident.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/53364475 |title=Formula 1: Charles Leclerc warned for breaking coronavirus rules |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=10 July 2020 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210119195648/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/53364475 |archive-date=19 January 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-mercedes-set-to-be-warned-on-f1-coronavirus-protocols-4981312/4981312/ |title=Ferrari, Mercedes set to be warned on F1 coronavirus protocols |last1=Noble |first1=Jonathan |last2=Vinel |first2=Benjamin |date=9 July 2020 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240615054141/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-mercedes-set-to-be-warned-on-f1-coronavirus-protocols-4981312/4981312/ |archive-date=15 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> In Styria, Leclerc collided with teammate [[Sebastian Vettel]] on the first lap, causing them both to retire.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/07/13/motorsport/ferrari-f1-styrian-gp-charles-leclerc-sebastian-vettel-spt-intl/index.html |title=Ferrari implodes as Charles Leclerc and Sebastian Vettel collide and retire from Styrian GP |last=Morse |first=Ben |date=13 July 2020 |work=[[CNN]] |publisher=[[WarnerMedia]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231203122741/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/07/13/motorsport/ferrari-f1-styrian-gp-charles-leclerc-sebastian-vettel-spt-intl/index.html |archive-date=3 December 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc took full responsibility for the collision.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/vettel-and-leclerc-say-styria-crash-behind-them-as-they-focus-on-assessing.5C6yndRm4WnbKu5V2ame1w |title=Vettel and Leclerc say Styria crash 'behind them' as they focus on assessing Ferrari upgrades in Hungary |date=16 July 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241102221904/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/vettel-and-leclerc-say-styria-crash-behind-them-as-they-focus-on-assessing.5C6yndRm4WnbKu5V2ame1w |archive-date=2 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> After finishing eleventh at the {{F1GP|2020|Hungarian}},<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2020/07/19/f1-hungarian-grand-prix-2020-live-hungaroring-race-results-hamilton/ |url-access=registration |title=Lewis Hamilton wins Hungarian Grand Prix with perfect drive to take F1 Championship lead |last1=Duncan |first1=Phil |last2=Curtis |first2=Ben |date=19 July 2020 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220524090122/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2020/07/19/f1-hungarian-grand-prix-2020-live-hungaroring-race-results-hamilton/ |archive-date=24 May 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc secured another podium at the {{F1GP|2020|British}} following a late puncture for [[Valtteri Bottas]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/aug/02/lewis-hamilton-hangs-on-to-win-british-grand-prix-after-puncture-drama |title=Lewis Hamilton hangs on to win British Grand Prix after puncture drama |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=2 August 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241215131830/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/aug/02/lewis-hamilton-hangs-on-to-win-british-grand-prix-after-puncture-drama |archive-date=15 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/53629967 |title=Lewis Hamilton wins British Grand Prix after puncture on last lap |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=2 August 2020 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241124080821/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/53629967 |archive-date=24 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to the [[70th Anniversary Grand Prix]], Leclerc faced allegations of [[racism]] for opting to not [[take the knee]] during pre-race ceremonies;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12044246/charles-leclerc-angered-by-accusations-of-racism-on-social-media |title=Charles Leclerc angered by accusations of racism on social media |last=Galloway |first=James |date=7 August 2020 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210727030120/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12044246/charles-leclerc-angered-by-accusations-of-racism-on-social-media |archive-date=27 July 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> he responded by stating that racism is "disgusting" and accusing media outlets of manipulating his words, adding that he wanted to avoid promoting [[Violence and controversies during the George Floyd protests|violent protest]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/f1-charles-leclerc-racist-take-a-knee-70th-anniversary-grand-prix-twitter-black-lives-matter-a9659536.html |title=Charles Leclerc rages at critics who have labelled F1 driver 'racist' for not taking a knee before races |last=de Menezes |first=Jack |date=7 August 2020 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220706102543/http://www.independent.co.uk/f1/f1-charles-leclerc-racist-take-a-knee-70th-anniversary-grand-prix-twitter-black-lives-matter-a9659536.html |archive-date=6 July 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-kneeling-racism-accusations/4850674/ |title=Leclerc hits out at racism accusations over not taking a knee |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=6 August 2020 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=6 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200806165025/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-kneeling-racism-accusations/4850674/ |archive-date=6 August 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> He successfully completed a one-stop tyre strategy in the race, finishing fourth after qualifying eighth, stating that it "[felt] like victory".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/delighted-leclerc-says-fourth-place-feels-like-victory-after-strategy-gamble.4H2YVpxUjiKdpDyDB8pSdX |title=Delighted Leclerc says fourth place 'feels like victory' after strategy gamble pays off |date=9 August 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240724011311/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/delighted-leclerc-says-fourth-place-feels-like-victory-after-strategy-gamble.4H2YVpxUjiKdpDyDB8pSdX |archive-date=24 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/p8-a-realistic-picture-of-ferrari-performance-says-leclerc-after-silverstone.30n8iD8QVFCO5PrfC2nBMP |title=P8 a 'realistic picture' of Ferrari performance says Leclerc after Silverstone qualifying |date=8 August 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=9 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200918192127/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.p8-a-realistic-picture-of-ferrari-performance-says-leclerc-after-silverstone.30n8iD8QVFCO5PrfC2nBMP.html |archive-date=18 September 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc suffered reliability issues at the [[2020 Spanish Grand Prix|Spanish]] and [[2020 Belgian Grand Prix|Belgian]] Grands Prix, retiring from the former and finishing fourteenth at the latter.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/ferrari-say-theyve-identified-ecu-issue-behind-leclercs-spain-dnf-as-they.7ole7Rhxem0ROi1uo39o2C |title=Ferrari say they've identified ECU issue behind Leclerc's Spain DNF, as they ready for 'tough' Belgian GP |date=25 August 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240915164952/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/ferrari-say-theyve-identified-ecu-issue-behind-leclercs-spain-dnf-as-they.7ole7Rhxem0ROi1uo39o2C |archive-date=15 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/aug/30/lewis-hamilton-belgian-grand-prix-triumph-f1-formula-one |title=Lewis Hamilton closes on Schumacher's record after winning Belgian Grand Prix |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=30 August 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220820044036/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/aug/30/lewis-hamilton-belgian-grand-prix-triumph-f1-formula-one |archive-date=20 August 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the {{F1GP|2020|Italian}}, he qualified thirteenth before colliding with a tyre barrier at the ''[[Monza Circuit|Curva Parabolica]]'' and causing a [[red flag (motorsport)|red flag]] whilst running in fourth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12064192/ferraris-f1-woes-deepen-outside-the-top-10-on-home-italian-gp-grid |title=Ferrari's F1 woes deepen outside the top 10 on home Italian GP grid |last=Galloway |first=James |date=5 September 2020 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=6 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201022094700/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12064192/ferraris-f1-woes-deepen-outside-the-top-10-on-home-italian-gp-grid |archive-date=22 October 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/huge-leclerc-crash-puts-italian-grand-prix-under-red-flag-4979353/4979353/ |title=Huge Leclerc crash puts Italian Grand Prix under red flag |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=6 September 2020 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250123080046/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/huge-leclerc-crash-puts-italian-grand-prix-under-red-flag-4979353/4979353/ |archive-date=23 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/watch-italian-gp-red-flagged-as-leclerc-walks-away-from-huge-crash.6GqXitdCU6zq35K6x7vzyf |title=Watch: Italian GP red-flagged as Leclerc walks away from huge crash |date=6 September 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241214064522/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/watch-italian-gp-red-flagged-as-leclerc-walks-away-from-huge-crash.6GqXitdCU6zq35K6x7vzyf |archive-date=14 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He then finished seven consecutive races in the [[List of Formula One World Championship points scoring systems|points]] from [[2020 Tuscan Grand Prix|Tuscany]] to [[2020 Bahrain Grand Prix|Bahrain]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/vettel-says-his-bahrain-race-was-compromised-by-having-to-avoid-ruthless.1hbF9Unjw28wPobLe39E7V |title=Vettel says his Bahrain race was compromised by having to avoid 'ruthless' Leclerc at start |date=30 November 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241006001027/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/vettel-says-his-bahrain-race-was-compromised-by-having-to-avoid-ruthless.1hbF9Unjw28wPobLe39E7V |archive-date=6 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> with top-five finishes at the [[2020 Portuguese Grand Prix|Portuguese]], [[2020 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix|Emilia Romagna]], and [[2020 Turkish Grand Prix|Turkish]] Grands Prix;<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2020/10/25/f1-portuguese-grand-prix-2020-live-algarve-race-results-hamilton/ |url-access=registration |title=Lewis Hamilton dominates Portuguese Grand Prix to break Michael Schumacher's record of most F1 wins |last1=Duncan |first1=Phil |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=25 October 2020 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241127120229/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2020/10/25/f1-portuguese-grand-prix-2020-live-algarve-race-results-hamilton/ |archive-date=27 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/nov/01/hamilton-wins-emilia-romagna-gp-as-mercedes-claim-record-seventh-f1-title |title=Lewis Hamilton wins Emilia Romagna GP as Mercedes claim seventh F1 title |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=1 November 2020 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241226052036/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2020/nov/01/hamilton-wins-emilia-romagna-gp-as-mercedes-claim-record-seventh-f1-title |archive-date=26 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> at the latter, Leclerc lost a podium finish during a last-lap overtake attempt on [[Sergio Pérez]] for second,<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2020-turkish-grand-prix-report-sensational-hamilton-victory-to-clinch-7th-title/ |url-access=registration |title=2020 Turkish Grand Prix report: Hamilton's sensational win clinches 7th F1 title |last=Medland |first=Chris |date=15 November 2020 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221007082752/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2020-turkish-grand-prix-report-sensational-hamilton-victory-to-clinch-7th-title |archive-date=7 October 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-radio-rant-turkish-gp/4911417/ |title=Late Leclerc mistake led to radio outburst in Turkish GP |last1=Noble |first1=Jonathan |last2=Karpov |first2=Oleg |date=16 November 2020 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230204023059/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-radio-rant-turkish-gp/4911417/ |archive-date=4 February 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> having qualified for the rain-affected race in fourteenth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-has-no-explanation-for-ferraris-poor-wet-weather-qualifying-pace-in.540vye3ou9kAXiA9jxzSYj |title=Leclerc has 'no explanation' for Ferrari’s poor wet-weather qualifying pace in Turkey |date=14 November 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240919065608/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-has-no-explanation-for-ferraris-poor-wet-weather-qualifying-pace-in.540vye3ou9kAXiA9jxzSYj |archive-date=19 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He retired from the {{F1GP|2020|Sakhir}} after a first-lap collision with Pérez—for which he was given a three-place [[Glossary of motorsport terms#G|grid penalty]]—having qualified fourth.<ref name="SAK20">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-handed-three-place-grid-penalty-after-sakhir-gp-opening-lap-collision-4976523/4976523/ |title=Leclerc handed three-place grid penalty after Sakhir GP opening lap collision |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=6 December 2020 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230528133409/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-handed-three-place-grid-penalty-after-sakhir-gp-opening-lap-collision-4976523/4976523/ |archive-date=28 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-delighted-with-surprise-p4-in-sakhir-qualifying-as-vettel-exits-in.5nq11c8aqEjFBJXR8Le8hA |title=Leclerc delighted with surprise P4 in Sakhir qualifying, as Vettel exits in Q2 after middle-sector struggles |date=5 December 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240613114338/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-delighted-with-surprise-p4-in-sakhir-qualifying-as-vettel-exits-in.5nq11c8aqEjFBJXR8Le8hA |archive-date=13 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Ferrari struggled for pace at the season-ending {{F1GP|2020|Abu Dhabi}}, with Leclerc finishing thirteenth.<ref name="ABU20">{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-very-happy-with-personal-performance-in-2020-despite-ferraris.4ViAnICBxfSc7LwQx8sVbn |title=Leclerc 'very happy' with personal performance in 2020, despite Ferrari's struggles |date=15 December 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240917195039/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-very-happy-with-personal-performance-in-2020-despite-ferraris.4ViAnICBxfSc7LwQx8sVbn |archive-date=17 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He ended the season eighth in the standings with two podiums and 98 points, 65 ahead of teammate Vettel in thirteenth,<ref name="ABU20"/> as Ferrari finished sixth in the [[World Constructors' Championship]]—their lowest since {{F1|1980}}.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2021/03/27/motorsport/ferrari-2021-bounce-back-formula-one-spt-intl/index.html |title=After worst season in years, can Ferrari bounce back in 2021? |last1=Davies |first1=Amanda |last2=Morse |first2=Ben |date=27 March 2021 |work=[[CNN]] |publisher=[[WarnerMedia]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240325135211/https://edition.cnn.com/2021/03/27/motorsport/ferrari-2021-bounce-back-formula-one-spt-intl/index.html |archive-date=25 March 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/long-read-ferrari-on-the-disappointments-of-2020-and-why-they-have-renewed.3STWRgoGOKDj7Y6MxBORXF |title=Long Read: Ferrari on the disappointments of 2020 – and why they have renewed hope for 2021 |last=Barretto |first=Lawrence |date=26 January 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240919095930/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/long-read-ferrari-on-the-disappointments-of-2020-and-why-they-have-renewed.3STWRgoGOKDj7Y6MxBORXF |archive-date=19 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:2021 British Grand Prix (51349315261).jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc (pictured at the {{F1GP|2021|British}}) qualified on [[List of Formula One polesitters|pole position]] at the [[2021 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]] and [[2021 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan]] Grands Prix in {{F1|2021}}.|alt=Leclerc driving the Ferrari SF21 at the 2021 British Grand Prix]]
Leclerc was partnered by [[Carlos Sainz Jr.]] at Ferrari for his {{F1|2021}} campaign.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/52661201 |title=Ferrari sign Sainz & Ricciardo goes to McLaren for 2021 Formula 1 season |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=14 May 2020 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=26 May 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200529002116/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/52661201 |archive-date=29 May 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> He started the {{F1GP|2021|Bahrain}} in fourth and finished sixth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-calls-p3-in-constructors-reachable-for-ferrari-in-2021-but-says-2022.4lQbCbuDnP0OKGWijStG1o |title=Leclerc calls P3 in constructors' 'reachable' for Ferrari in 2021 – but says 2022 car is team's priority |date=15 April 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240918045627/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-calls-p3-in-constructors-reachable-for-ferrari-in-2021-but-says-2022.4lQbCbuDnP0OKGWijStG1o |archive-date=18 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He then finished fourth at the {{F1GP|2021|Emilia Romagna}} amidst a radio issue.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2021/04/18/f1-emilia-romagna-grand-prix-2021-live-race-results-imola/ |url-access=registration |title=Lewis Hamilton powers to second but error gifts Max Verstappen Imola win |last1=Duncan |first1=Phil |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=18 April 2021 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240625152136/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2021/04/18/f1-emilia-romagna-grand-prix-2021-live-race-results-imola/ |archive-date=25 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/broken-radios-and-right-to-reverse-what-you-missed-from-the-2021-emilia-romagna-grand-prix/ |url-access=registration |title=Broken radios and right to reverse: What you missed from the 2021 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix |last=Williams-Smith |first=Jake |date=19 April 2021 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210515052436/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/broken-radios-and-right-to-reverse-what-you-missed-from-the-2021-emilia-romagna-grand-prix |archive-date=15 May 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> His sixth-placed finish in [[2021 Portuguese Grand Prix|Portugal]] dropped him to fifth in the standings,<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2021/05/02/hamilton-eclipses-bottas-and-verstappen-in-portuguese-gp/ |title=Hamilton eclipses Bottas and Verstappen in Portuguese GP |last=Lamonato |first=Michael |date=2 May 2021 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230328023845/https://racer.com/2021/05/02/hamilton-eclipses-bottas-and-verstappen-in-portuguese-gp/ |archive-date=28 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.marca.com/en/f1/2021/05/02/608e89cb46163f86338b4592.html |title=Lewis Hamilton wins Formula 1's Portugal Grand Prix and championship standings |date=2 May 2021 |work=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |publisher=[[Unidad Editorial]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=2340-0595 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210523160027/https://www.marca.com/en/f1/2021/05/02/608e89cb46163f86338b4592.html |archive-date=23 May 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> before he finished fourth again in [[2021 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]].<ref name="2021ESP1"/><ref name="2021ESP2"/> Leclerc secured a surprise pole position at [[2021 Monaco Grand Prix|his home Grand Prix in Monaco]]—his first since the [[2019 Mexican Grand Prix]]—after colliding with the barrier at ''[[Circuit de Monaco|La Piscine]]'' in the final part of qualifying,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/57212855 |title=Monaco Grand Prix: Charles Leclerc on pole position despite crash |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=22 May 2021 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230502112506/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/57212855 |archive-date=2 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-fears-gearbox-damage-after-big-surprise-f1-pole-in-monaco/6513402/ |title=Leclerc fears gearbox damage after 'big surprise' F1 pole in Monaco |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=22 May 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240917151230/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-fears-gearbox-damage-after-big-surprise-f1-pole-in-monaco/6513402/ |archive-date=17 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> but was unable to start the race due to a related [[drive shaft]] issue.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/31496326/driveshaft-issue-rules-polesitter-leclerc-monaco-gp-start |title=Driveshaft issue rules out pole sitter Leclerc before Monaco GP start |last=Edmondson |first=Laurence |date=23 May 2021 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526072858/https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/31496326/driveshaft-issue-rules-polesitter-leclerc-monaco-gp-start |archive-date=26 May 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> He qualified on pole again at the next round in [[2021 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2021/06/05/azerbaijan-grand-prix-2021-qualifying-f1-live-hamilton-news/ |url-access=registration |title=Charles Leclerc takes Azerbaijan Grand Prix pole in chaotic, crash-filled session |last1=Duncan |first1=Phil |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=5 June 2021 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250124060746/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2021/06/05/azerbaijan-grand-prix-2021-qualifying-f1-live-hamilton-news/ |archive-date=24 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> before finishing fourth.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2021/jun/06/azerbaijan-grand-prix-f1-live |title=Sergio Pérez wins dramatic Azerbaijan GP after Verstappen crashes: F1 – as it happened |last=Hess |first=Alex |date=6 June 2021 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231105152040/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2021/jun/06/azerbaijan-grand-prix-f1-live |archive-date=5 November 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Tyre wear struggles at the {{F1GP|2021|French}} saw him finish sixteenth after taking an additional [[pit stop]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-explains-front-end-struggles-behind-qualifying-disaster/6586252/ |title=Leclerc explains front-end struggles behind qualifying "disaster" |last1=Smith |first1=Luke |last2=Cooper |first2=Adam |date=19 June 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250126043430/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-explains-front-end-struggles-behind-qualifying-disaster/6586252/ |archive-date=26 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/french-gp-verstappen-passes-hamilton-to-win-after-start-error/6590000/ |title=French GP: Verstappen passes Hamilton to win after start error |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=20 June 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250126043430/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/french-gp-verstappen-passes-hamilton-to-win-after-start-error/6590000/ |archive-date=26 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He then finished seventh and eighth at the [[2021 Styrian Grand Prix|Styrian]] and [[2021 Austrian Grand Prix|Austrian]] Grands Prix, respectively.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/57630205 |title=Max Verstappen wins Styrian Grand Prix, with Lewis Hamilton second |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=27 June 2021 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230324023833/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/57630205 |archive-date=24 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-austrian-grand-prix-race-results-verstappen-wins-from-bottas/6625519/ |title=F1 Austrian Grand Prix race results: Verstappen wins from Bottas |last=Bradley |first=Charles |date=4 July 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231129210243/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-austrian-grand-prix-race-results-verstappen-wins-from-bottas/6625519/ |archive-date=29 November 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the {{F1GP|2021|British}}, Leclerc qualified fourth before inheriting the lead on the first lap: he overtook Bottas off-the-line before passing both [[Max Verstappen]] and Hamilton after their collision.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/how-leclerc-almost-defied-hamilton-after-f1-title-rivals-collision-/6633574/ |url-access=subscription |title=How Leclerc almost defied Hamilton after F1 title rivals' Silverstone clash |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=19 July 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221204020402/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/how-leclerc-almost-defied-hamilton-after-f1-title-rivals-collision-/6633574/ |archive-date=4 December 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> He held the lead until the third-to-last lap—when Hamilton passed him—finishing in second-place to claim his sole podium of the season.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/archive/article/october-2021/34/how-hamilton-reeled-in-leclerc-to-win-the-2021-british-grand-prix |url-access=registration |title=How Hamilton reeled in Leclerc to win the 2021 British Grand Prix |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=October 2021 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |page=34 |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221128103602/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/archive/article/october-2021/34/how-hamilton-reeled-in-leclerc-to-win-the-2021-british-grand-prix |archive-date=28 November 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc retired from the rain-affected {{F1GP|2021|Hungarian}} after a first-lap collision with [[Lance Stroll]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/he-came-from-nowhere-leclerc-frustrated-by-stroll-as-he-likens-turn-1-crash.39IgS7fkFpgGMhJXNYNv7K |title='He came from nowhere' – Leclerc frustrated by Stroll as he likens Turn 1 crash to 'bowling game' |date=1 August 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250117231926/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/he-came-from-nowhere-leclerc-frustrated-by-stroll-as-he-likens-turn-1-crash.39IgS7fkFpgGMhJXNYNv7K |archive-date=17 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> demoting him to seventh in the championship, below teammate Sainz.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2021/08/03/mid-season-f1-driver-ratings-has-starred-pressure-heading-summer/ |url-access=registration |title=Mid-season F1 driver ratings: Who has starred and who is under pressure heading into the summer break? |last=Slater |first=Luke |date=3 August 2021 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240524223555/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2021/08/03/mid-season-f1-driver-ratings-has-starred-pressure-heading-summer/ |archive-date=24 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished eighth at the curtailed {{F1GP|2021|Belgian}},<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/verstappen-takes-victory-in-severely-shortened-rain-affected-belgian-gp-as.4AqGhiKQfFaqr7KZjyDjPZ |title=Verstappen takes win and Russell first podium in shortest ever Grand Prix as heavy rain hits Spa |date=29 August 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241215123709/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/verstappen-takes-victory-in-severely-shortened-rain-affected-belgian-gp-as.4AqGhiKQfFaqr7KZjyDjPZ |archive-date=15 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> and fifth in the [[2021 Dutch Grand Prix|Netherlands]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-takes-home-win-at-dutch-gp/6661121/ |title=F1 Dutch GP: Verstappen takes home win and regains championship lead |last=Kew |first=Matt |date=5 September 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231025193652/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-takes-home-win-at-dutch-gp/6661121/ |archive-date=25 October 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2021 Italian Grand Prix|Italy]], Leclerc finished fourth after a penalty for Pérez.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-calls-battling-p4-at-monza-one-of-my-top-five-performances-in-f1.7L8tyFtUx4g6gixOYqaYgk |title=Leclerc calls battling P4 at Monza 'one of my top five performances in F1' |date=12 September 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241207170639/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-calls-battling-p4-at-monza-one-of-my-top-five-performances-in-f1.7L8tyFtUx4g6gixOYqaYgk |archive-date=7 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He took grid penalties for the {{F1GP|2021|Russian}}, forcing him to start nineteenth; after climbing to third,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-vows-to-learn-from-losing-late-points-in-sochi-rain-shower/6678305/ |title=Leclerc vows to learn from losing F1 points in late Sochi rain shower |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=30 September 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241214003639/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-vows-to-learn-from-losing-late-points-in-sochi-rain-shower/6678305/ |archive-date=14 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he was the last to pit for [[Formula One tyres|intermediate tyres]] in changing conditions, demoting him to fifteenth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/sochi-result-hurts-says-leclerc-after-slick-gamble-doesnt-pay-off.PRg22JLEo1r2fZg6r2Eog |title=Sochi result 'hurts' says Leclerc after slick gamble doesn't pay off |date=28 September 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241118204238/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/sochi-result-hurts-says-leclerc-after-slick-gamble-doesnt-pay-off.PRg22JLEo1r2fZg6r2Eog |archive-date=18 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc finished fourth at both the [[2021 Turkish Grand Prix|Turkish]] and [[2021 United States Grand Prix|United States]] Grands Prix, leading several laps at the former,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/no-regrets-for-leclerc-or-ferrari-over-turkish-gp-tyre-strategy/6684721/ |title='No regrets' for Leclerc or Ferrari over Turkish GP tyre strategy |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=10 October 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230127072621/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/no-regrets-for-leclerc-or-ferrari-over-turkish-gp-tyre-strategy/6684721/ |archive-date=27 January 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/i-was-thinking-about-the-podium-says-leclerc-as-he-admits-drive-to-p4-was.5AJ8Foy18kJLZoMXgqzkES |title='I was thinking about the podium' says Leclerc as he admits drive to P4 was 'unexpected' |date=24 October 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241005035234/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/i-was-thinking-about-the-podium-says-leclerc-as-he-admits-drive-to-p4-was.5AJ8Foy18kJLZoMXgqzkES |archive-date=5 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> before finishing fifth in [[2021 Mexico City Grand Prix|Mexico City]] and [[2021 São Paulo Grand Prix|São Paulo]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2021/nov/07/max-verstappen-puts-title-in-sight-after-cruising-to-mexican-f1-gp-triumph |title=Max Verstappen puts title in sight after cruising to Mexican F1 GP triumph |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=7 November 2021 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221108180455/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2021/nov/07/max-verstappen-puts-title-in-sight-after-cruising-to-mexican-f1-gp-triumph |archive-date=8 November 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/five-talking-points-from-a-sizzling-sao-paulo-gp/ |title=Five talking points from a sizzling São Paulo GP |last=Smith |first=Damien |date=15 November 2021 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241007120922/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/five-talking-points-from-a-sizzling-sao-paulo-gp/ |archive-date=7 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> After scoring [[List of Formula One World Championship points scoring systems|points]] in [[2021 Qatar Grand Prix|Qatar]] and [[2021 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix|Saudi Arabia]], Leclerc moved up to fifth in the championship,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2021/nov/21/lewis-hamilton-dominates-f1-qatar-gp-to-cut-max-verstappens-title-lead |title=Lewis Hamilton dominates F1 Qatar GP to cut Max Verstappen's title lead |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=21 November 2021 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213110741/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2021/nov/21/lewis-hamilton-dominates-f1-qatar-gp-to-cut-max-verstappens-title-lead |archive-date=13 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-grand-prix-race-results-hamilton-wins-wild-saudi-gp/6854398/ |title=F1 Grand Prix race results: Hamilton wins wild Saudi GP |last=Bradley |first=Charles |date=5 December 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240803044622/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-grand-prix-race-results-hamilton-wins-wild-saudi-gp/6854398/ |archive-date=3 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> four points ahead of [[Lando Norris]] and 8.5 ahead of Sainz with one round remaining.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-says-fight-for-p5-gives-him-extra-motivation-as-norris-sets-out-to.5DQWwgqJpl3w0Ob7IW0Ga8 |title=Leclerc says fight for P5 gives him 'extra motivation' as Norris sets out to beat Ferrari drivers in Abu Dhabi |date=9 December 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725151700/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-says-fight-for-p5-gives-him-extra-motivation-as-norris-sets-out-to.5DQWwgqJpl3w0Ob7IW0Ga8 |archive-date=25 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the {{F1GP|2021|Abu Dhabi}}, a pit stop gamble under the [[virtual safety car]] saw Leclerc lose track position, ultimately finishing in tenth;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-grand-prix-race-results-verstappen-wins-abu-dhabi-gp-claims-title/6878130/ |title=F1 Grand Prix race results: Verstappen wins Abu Dhabi GP, claims title |last=Bradley |first=Charles |date=12 December 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231025173158/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-grand-prix-race-results-verstappen-wins-abu-dhabi-gp-claims-title/6878130/ |archive-date=25 October 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> this result saw both Sainz and Norris surpass his points tally, with Leclerc finishing seventh in the World Drivers' Championship on 159 points.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/sainz-says-abu-dhabi-podium-was-the-ideal-end-to-a-magic-first-season-with.1Ze2VJQIt8PSolPZPGqAi5 |title=Sainz says Abu Dhabi podium was the ideal end to a 'magic' first season with Ferrari |date=13 December 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241007025338/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/sainz-says-abu-dhabi-podium-was-the-ideal-end-to-a-magic-first-season-with.1Ze2VJQIt8PSolPZPGqAi5 |archive-date=7 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> This marked the first time Leclerc had been outscored by a teammate in his [[formula racing]] career.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/palmer-my-star-performers-and-stand-out-moments-from-the-2021-season.I9VG1Y6WrF5Ld9JjirzpN |title=Palmer: My star performers and stand-out moments from the 2021 season |last=Palmer |first=Jolyon |date=24 December 2021 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=24 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241212092425/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/palmer-my-star-performers-and-stand-out-moments-from-the-2021-season.I9VG1Y6WrF5Ld9JjirzpN |archive-date=12 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2022: Curtailed title battle vs. Verstappen ====
[[File:Ferrari F1-75 in Melbourne.jpg|thumb|right|In {{F1|2022}}, Leclerc achieved his maiden career [[grand slam (Formula One)|grand slam]] at the {{F1GP|2022|Australian}} (pictured) and led the championship until his retirement in [[2022 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]].|alt=Leclerc driving the Ferrari F1-75 at the 2022 Australian Grand Prix]]
[[2022 Formula One World Championship#Technical regulations|New regulations]] utilising [[ground effect (cars)|ground effect]] saw Ferrari challenge [[Red Bull Racing|Red Bull]] in the first half of {{F1|2022}}.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/red-bull-vs-ferrari-the-2022-f1-development-war-so-far/ |title=Red Bull vs Ferrari: The 2022 F1 development war so far |last=Giuliana |first=Rosario |date=24 August 2022 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240909021958/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/red-bull-vs-ferrari-the-2022-f1-development-war-so-far/ |archive-date=9 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/ferraris-2022-f1-advantage-has-been-hiding-in-plain-sight/ |url-access=registration |title=Ferrari's 2022 F1 advantage has been hiding in plain sight |last=Williams-Smith |first=Jake |date=6 April 2022 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240416015009/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/ferraris-2022-f1-advantage-has-been-hiding-in-plain-sight/ |archive-date=16 April 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-bringing-low-downforce-solution-to-miami-to-combat-red-bull-speed/10246782/ |title=Ferrari bringing low downforce solution to Miami GP to combat Red Bull speed |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=28 April 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240910082425/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-bringing-low-downforce-solution-to-miami-to-combat-red-bull-speed/10246782/ |archive-date=10 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc qualified on pole position for the season-opening {{F1GP|2022|Bahrain}}, before winning the race amidst a close battle with [[Max Verstappen]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2022/03/20/motorsport/bahrain-grand-prix-charles-leclerc-ferrari-spt-intl/index.html |title=Bahrain Grand Prix: Ferrari dominates as Charles Leclerc wins dramatic season opener |last=Church |first=Ben |date=20 March 2022 |work=[[CNN]] |publisher=[[WarnerMedia]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230930110216/https://edition.cnn.com/2022/03/20/motorsport/bahrain-grand-prix-charles-leclerc-ferrari-spt-intl/index.html |archive-date=30 September 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> marking his and Ferrari's first victory since {{F1|2019}}.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/mar/20/charles-leclerc-wins-dramatic-bahrain-f1-gp-as-ferrari-bring-home-one-two |title=Charles Leclerc wins dramatic Bahrain F1 GP as Ferrari bring home one–two |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=20 March 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=20 March 2022 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220320224736/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/mar/20/charles-leclerc-wins-dramatic-bahrain-f1-gp-as-ferrari-bring-home-one-two |archive-date=20 March 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> The result saw him become the first Monégasque driver to lead the World Drivers' Championship.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/bahrain-grand-prix-facts-and-stats-ferrari-end-45-race-win-drought-zhou.38i07mI1623W0mhoWsGZjx |title=Facts and Stats: Ferrari end 45-race win drought in Bahrain Grand Prix, as Zhou scores on debut |last=Kelly |first=Sean |date=20 March 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=21 March 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220321175938/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.bahrain-grand-prix-facts-and-stats-ferrari-end-45-race-win-drought-zhou.38i07mI1623W0mhoWsGZjx.html |archive-date=21 March 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> After finishing second to Verstappen in another close-fought battle in [[2022 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix|Saudi Arabia]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/verstappen-beats-leclerc-in-frantic-fight-to-the-flag-2022-saudi-arabian-gp-report/ |url-access=registration |title=Verstappen beats Leclerc in frantic fight to the flag: 2022 Saudi Arabian GP report |last=Medland |first=Chris |date=28 March 2022 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250213141600/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/verstappen-beats-leclerc-in-frantic-fight-to-the-flag-2022-saudi-arabian-gp-report/ |archive-date=13 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc took a dominant victory from pole at the {{F1GP|2022|Australian}}, achieving his maiden [[grand slam (Formula One)|grand slam]] in Formula One and extending his championship lead to 34 [[List of Formula One World Championship points scoring systems|points]] over [[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]], 46 ahead of Verstappen in sixth.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/apr/10/charles-leclerc-wins-f1-australian-gp-after-max-verstappen-is-forced-to-retire |title=Charles Leclerc wins Australian F1 GP after Max Verstappen is forced to retire |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=10 April 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221102073012/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/apr/10/charles-leclerc-wins-f1-australian-gp-after-max-verstappen-is-forced-to-retire |archive-date=2 November 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a39682979/how-ferrari-charles-leclerc-opened-huge-f1-points-lead-with-austalian-grand-prix-win/ |title=How Ferrari, Charles Leclerc Opened Huge F1 Points Lead with Australian Grand Prix Win |last=Horton |first=Phillip |date=10 April 2022 |magazine=[[Autoweek]] |publisher=[[Hearst Communications]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0192-9674 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230413064028/https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a39682979/how-ferrari-charles-leclerc-opened-huge-f1-points-lead-with-austalian-grand-prix-win/ |archive-date=13 April 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-dominates-in-australia-as-verstappen-suffers-dnf.7Exhm5kuubqsywFoAe0QAK |title=Dominant Leclerc beats Pérez to Australian GP win as Verstappen retires |date=10 April 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=10 April 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220416230831/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.leclerc-dominates-in-australia-as-verstappen-suffers-dnf.7Exhm5kuubqsywFoAe0QAK.html |archive-date=16 April 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Following another battle with Verstappen in the {{F1GP|2022|Emilia Romagna}} sprint,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/61202419 |title=Emilia Romagna Grand Prix: Max Verstappen passes Charles Leclerc to win sprint race |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=23 April 2022 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220518224321/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/61202419 |archive-date=18 May 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc spun at the ''[[Imola Circuit|Variante Alta]]'' [[chicane]] whilst chasing [[Sergio Pérez]] for second-place in the main race,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-emilia-romagna-gp-verstappen-leads-red-bull-1-2-leclerc-spin-loses-podium/10179437/ |title=F1 Emilia Romagna GP: Verstappen leads Red Bull 1–2, Leclerc spin loses podium |last=Kew |first=Matt |date=24 April 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241215132035/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-emilia-romagna-gp-verstappen-leads-red-bull-1-2-leclerc-spin-loses-podium/10179437/ |archive-date=15 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> demoting him to sixth and reducing his advantage over Verstappen to 27 points.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-leclercs-imola-f1-spin-easily-done/10182993/ |title=Verstappen: Leclerc's Imola F1 spin "easily done" |last1=Cobb |first1=Haydn |last2=Kew |first2=Matt |date=24 April 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240301213121/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/verstappen-leclercs-imola-f1-spin-easily-done/10182993/ |archive-date=1 March 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished second to Verstappen after starting on pole at the {{F1GP|2022|Miami}}.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/61373963 |title=Miami Grand Prix: Max Verstappen takes hard-fought win over Charles Leclerc |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=8 May 2022 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231230122527/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/61373963 |archive-date=30 December 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2022 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]], Leclerc took pole again and led the race with a 13-second margin until a power unit failure forced his retirement,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/general/news/autosport-2022-top-50-2-charles-leclerc/10413528/ |title=Autosport 2022 Top 50: #2 Charles Leclerc |date=22 December 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230224134927/https://www.autosport.com/general/news/autosport-2022-top-50-2-charles-leclerc/10413528/ |archive-date=24 February 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> handing Verstappen the victory and championship lead.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/may/22/max-verstappen-wins-dramatic-spanish-f1-gp-after-charles-leclerc-retires |title=Max Verstappen wins dramatic Spanish F1 GP after Charles Leclerc retires |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=22 May 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241214045929/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/may/22/max-verstappen-wins-dramatic-spanish-f1-gp-after-charles-leclerc-retires |archive-date=14 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> After taking another pole at the {{F1GP|2022|Monaco}}, Leclerc finished fourth due to a strategical error in wet-weather conditions.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12623789/charles-leclerc-slams-ferrari-mistakes-at-monaco-gp-we-cannot-do-that-it-hurts-a-lot |title=Charles Leclerc slams Ferrari mistakes at Monaco GP: 'We cannot do that... it hurts a lot' |last=Morlidge |first=Matt |date=29 May 2022 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=2 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220602090453/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12623789/charles-leclerc-slams-ferrari-mistakes-at-monaco-gp-we-cannot-do-that-it-hurts-a-lot |archive-date=2 June 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> He took his fourth-successive pole at the {{F1GP|2022|Azerbaijan}},<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/azerbaijan-grand-prix-qualifying-results-leclerc-hamilton-verstappen-b2098918.html |title=Charles Leclerc claims Azerbaijan Grand Prix pole as Lewis Hamilton faces stewards |last=Duncan |first=Philip |date=11 June 2022 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220626094308/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/azerbaijan-grand-prix-qualifying-results-leclerc-hamilton-verstappen-b2098918.html |archive-date=26 June 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> where he again retired from the lead with a power unit issue, placing him third in the standings behind Pérez.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/61775861 |title=Azerbaijan Grand Prix: Max Verstappen wins in Baku as Charles Leclerc retires |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=12 June 2022 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=14 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220614184357/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/61775861 |archive-date=14 June 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.cbc.ca/sports/formula-one-azerbaijan-gp-recap-june-12-1.6486116 |title=Verstappen wins F1 Azerbaijan Grand Prix after Leclerc engine failure |date=12 June 2022 |work=[[CBC Sports]] |publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220725051956/https://www.cbc.ca/sports/formula-one-azerbaijan-gp-recap-june-12-1.6486116 |archive-date=25 July 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc started nineteenth for the {{F1GP|2022|Canadian}} due to an engine [[Glossary of motorsport terms#G|grid penalty]]; he recovered to fifth.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-calls-canadian-gp-super-frustrating-despite-recovering-from-back-row.2WE6F7ZVRYRYt5xkY8cXxX |title=Leclerc calls Canadian GP 'super-frustrating' despite recovering from back row to P5 |date=20 June 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=8 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220624034750/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.leclerc-calls-canadian-gp-super-frustrating-despite-recovering-from-back-row.2WE6F7ZVRYRYt5xkY8cXxX.html |archive-date=24 June 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> At the {{F1GP|2022|British}}, he finished fourth after losing out on a free [[pit stop]] under the [[safety car]] to his teammate, [[Carlos Sainz Jr.]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-explains-decision-not-to-pit-leclerc-under-late-british-gp-safety-car/10332619/ |title=Ferrari explains decision not to pit Leclerc under late British GP safety car |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=3 July 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=11 November 2022 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220704172102/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-explains-decision-not-to-pit-leclerc-under-late-british-gp-safety-car/10332619/ |archive-date=4 July 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:FIA F1 Austria 2022 Podium Race Winner Leclerc.jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc (pictured at the {{F1GP|2022|Austrian}}) achieved three victories as he finished runner-up in the World Drivers' Championship to [[Max Verstappen]].|alt=Leclerc lifting his trophy on the podium after winning the 2022 Austrian Grand Prix]]
Leclerc then took victory at the {{F1GP|2022|Austrian}} after a battle with Verstappen,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2022/jul/10/f1-austrian-grand-prix-live |title=Charles Leclerc pips Max Verstappen to F1 victory at Austrian GP – as it happened |last=Hess |first=Alex |date=10 July 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221017052143/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2022/jul/10/f1-austrian-grand-prix-live |archive-date=17 October 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> returning to second in the standings halfway through the season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/i-definitely-needed-that-one-says-leclerc-after-taking-first-win-in-three.01dC8Iv7gghhFfIsE9PGQ0 |title='I definitely needed that one' says Leclerc, after taking first win in three months in Austrian Grand Prix  |date=10 July 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=8 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221008171623/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.i-definitely-needed-that-one-says-leclerc-after-taking-first-win-in-three.01dC8Iv7gghhFfIsE9PGQ0.html |archive-date=8 October 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Ferrari struggled to match the performance of Red Bull from the {{F1GP|2022|French}} onwards,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/tech-tuesday-how-performance-has-swung-from-ferrari-to-red-bull-during-the-2022-season.31PFpwsa8ACPOGXGLOWaCq |title=Tech Tuesday: How performance has swung from Ferrari to Red Bull during the 2022 season |last1=Hughes |first1=Mark |last2=Piola |first2=Giorgio |date=20 September 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=12 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240913015040/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/tech-tuesday-how-performance-has-swung-from-ferrari-to-red-bull-during-the-2022-season.31PFpwsa8ACPOGXGLOWaCq |archive-date=13 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> where Leclerc started on pole before spinning out of the lead on lap 18 and colliding with a barrier.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/62284619 |title=French Grand Prix: Max Verstappen wins from Lewis Hamilton after Charles Leclerc crashes out |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=24 July 2022 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=26 July 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220726113103/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/62284619 |archive-date=26 July 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2022 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]], he qualified third and finished sixth after another strategic error by Ferrari put him on underperforming [[Formula One tyres|hard-compound tyres]]; Verstappen won the race and extended his advantage over Leclerc to 80 points going into the summer break.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/34327571/how-ferrari-got-strategy-wrong-hungary |title=How Ferrari got its strategy so wrong in Hungary |last=Edmondson |first=Laurence |date=1 August 2022 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=24 August 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220824122002/https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/34327571/how-ferrari-got-strategy-wrong-hungary |archive-date=24 August 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc started fifteenth following a grid penalty at the {{F1GP|2022|Belgian}},<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/verstappen-fastest-in-qualifying-but-sainz-set-to-start-on-pole-after.18uRqCjdY4iTx2s1CtiQ1m |title=Verstappen fastest in qualifying but Sainz set to start on pole after Belgian GP grid penalties |date=27 August 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=8 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220829095938/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-fastest-in-qualifying-but-sainz-set-to-start-on-pole-after.18uRqCjdY4iTx2s1CtiQ1m.html |archive-date=29 August 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> where he recovered to fifth, demoted to sixth after a five-second time penalty for [[speeding]] in the [[pit lane]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/verstappen-cruises-to-belgian-grand-prix-victory-from-p15-as-perez-completes.2J5xxc79o1DGvziQOegt7i |title=2022 Belgian Grand Prix race report and highlights: Verstappen cruises to Belgian Grand Prix victory from P14 as Pérez completes Red Bull 1–2 |date=28 August 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=25 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220829080749/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.verstappen-cruises-to-belgian-grand-prix-victory-from-p15-as-perez-completes.2J5xxc79o1DGvziQOegt7i.html |archive-date=29 August 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to the {{F1GP|2022|Dutch}}, he admitted that he had "stopped counting" his points deficit to Verstappen.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://the-race.com/formula-1/leclerc-has-stopped-counting-points-deficit-to-verstappen/ |title=Leclerc has 'stopped counting' F1 points deficit to Verstappen |last=Anderson |first=Ben |date=2 September 2022 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=25 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220925192957/https://the-race.com/formula-1/leclerc-has-stopped-counting-points-deficit-to-verstappen/ |archive-date=25 September 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> He took five consecutive podiums from there until the {{F1GP|2022|United States}},<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/facts-and-stats-perez-first-man-in-over-a-decade-to-do-monaco-singapore.2NAFspcpYnd1DdSBANcZ5t |title=Facts and Stats: Pérez first man in over a decade to do Monaco-Singapore double |last=Kelly |first=Sean |date=2 October 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241206044920/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/facts-and-stats-perez-first-man-in-over-a-decade-to-do-monaco-singapore.2NAFspcpYnd1DdSBANcZ5t |archive-date=6 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-suzuka-f1-penalty-was-right-after-last-lap-perez-fight/10382998/ |title=Leclerc: Suzuka F1 penalty was "right" after last-lap Pérez fight |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=11 October 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230326014736/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-suzuka-f1-penalty-was-right-after-last-lap-perez-fight/10382998/ |archive-date=26 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/the-familiar-ferrari-flaw-that-cost-leclerc-a-shot-at-us-gp-victory/ |url-access=registration |title=The familiar Ferrari flaw that cost Leclerc a shot at US GP victory |last=Gupta |first=Ekagra |date=25 October 2022 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221025231159/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/the-familiar-ferrari-flaw-that-cost-leclerc-a-shot-at-us-gp-victory |archive-date=25 October 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> including second-placed finishes from pole in [[2022 Italian Grand Prix|Italy]] and [[2022 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]];<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/max-verstappen-charles-leclerc-italian-grand-prix-b2164840.html |title=Max Verstappen wins the Italian Grand Prix as he holds off Ferrari's Charles Leclerc |last=Jackson |first=Kieran |date=11 September 2022 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230603214342/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/max-verstappen-charles-leclerc-italian-grand-prix-b2164840.html |archive-date=3 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12710051/singapore-gp-sergio-perez-holds-off-charles-leclerc-for-victory-in-chaotic-race-as-max-verstappen-denied-title |title=Singapore GP: Sergio Pérez holds off Charles Leclerc for victory in chaotic race as Max Verstappen denied title |date=3 October 2022 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=3 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221003104622/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12710051/singapore-gp-sergio-perez-holds-off-charles-leclerc-for-victory-in-chaotic-race-as-max-verstappen-denied-title |archive-date=3 October 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Verstappen clinched the title in [[2022 Japanese Grand Prix|Japan]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2022/10/09/japanese-grand-prix-2022-f1-live-race-results-suzuka-news-weather/ |url-access=registration |title=Max Verstappen secures title in confusing circumstances despite Japanese GP win |last1=Cary |first1=Tom |last2=Slater |first2=Luke |date=9 October 2022 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221220163859/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2022/10/09/japanese-grand-prix-2022-f1-live-race-results-suzuka-news-weather/ |archive-date=20 December 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc finished sixth and fourth at the [[2022 Mexico City Grand Prix|Mexico City]] and [[2022 São Paulo Grand Prix|São Paulo]] Grands Prix, respectively—after a collision with [[Lando Norris]] at the latter—leaving him tied-second in the championship with Pérez on 290 points going into the final round.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12474/12734737/mexico-city-gp-charles-leclerc-hurt-by-performance-as-paul-di-resta-outlines-fears-for-ferrari |title=Mexico City GP: Charles Leclerc 'hurt' by performance as Paul di Resta outlines fears for Ferrari |date=31 October 2022 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230328211019/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12474/12734737/mexico-city-gp-charles-leclerc-hurt-by-performance-as-paul-di-resta-outlines-fears-for-ferrari |archive-date=28 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-surprised-aggressive-norris-brazil-gp-clash/10400846/ |title=Leclerc surprised by "aggressive" Norris F1 Brazil GP clash |last=Cooper |first=Adam |date=17 November 2022 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240908223548/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-surprised-aggressive-norris-brazil-gp-clash/10400846/ |archive-date=8 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2022/nov/13/brazilian-grand-prix-formula-one-live |title=Brazilian GP: Russell secures first F1 win on triumphant day for Mercedes – as it happened |last=McLaughlin |first=Luke |date=13 November 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230321082120/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/live/2022/nov/13/brazilian-grand-prix-formula-one-live |archive-date=21 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc qualified third for the {{F1GP|2022|Abu Dhabi}} behind Pérez,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-abu-dhabi-gp-verstappen-trumps-perez-for-pole-leclerc-third/10402354/ |title=F1 Abu Dhabi GP: Verstappen trumps Pérez for pole, Leclerc third |last=Kew |first=Matt |date=19 November 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240808163855/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-abu-dhabi-gp-verstappen-trumps-perez-for-pole-leclerc-third/10402354/ |archive-date=8 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> before overtaking him with a one-stop strategy and clinching second in the World Drivers' Championship.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12751622/abu-dhabi-gp-charles-leclerc-praises-ferrari-for-delivering-under-pressure-in-f1-season-finale |title=Abu Dhabi GP: Charles Leclerc praises Ferrari for delivering under 'pressure' in F1 season finale |date=20 November 2022 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221121135906/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12751622/abu-dhabi-gp-charles-leclerc-praises-ferrari-for-delivering-under-pressure-in-f1-season-finale |archive-date=21 November 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> He totalled 308 points throughout the season, 146 behind Verstappen and 62 ahead of teammate Sainz in fifth.<ref name="2022analysis">{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/analysis-the-good-the-bad-and-the-future-whats-next-for-charles-leclerc.6WhHWZoRqEkNzY9bc5OLhg |title=Analysis: The good, the bad and the future – What's next for Charles Leclerc after his 2022 title defeat? |last=Barretto |first=Lawrence |date=17 December 2022 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241111175358/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/analysis-the-good-the-bad-and-the-future-whats-next-for-charles-leclerc.6WhHWZoRqEkNzY9bc5OLhg |archive-date=11 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/13/sports/autoracing/f1-ferrari-season.html |url-access=registration |title=For Ferrari, a Second-Place Season Full of Mistakes |last=Horton |first=Phillip |date=13 December 2022 |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241123003214/https://www.nytimes.com/2022/12/13/sports/autoracing/f1-ferrari-season.html |archive-date=23 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He led the field with nine pole positions,<ref name="2022analysis"/> and further achieved three victories from 11 podiums.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ranking-the-top-10-formula-1-drivers-of-2022/10411500/ |url-access=subscription |title=Ranking the top 10 Formula 1 drivers of 2022 |last1=Kalinauckas |first1=Alex |last2=Kew |first2=Matt |date=15 December 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230204120716/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ranking-the-top-10-formula-1-drivers-of-2022/10411500/ |archive-date=4 February 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2023–2024: First Monaco Grand Prix victory ====
[[File:FIA F1 Austria 2023 Nr. 16 (1).jpg|thumb|right|Leclerc (pictured at the {{F1GP|2023|Austrian}}) achieved five pole positions and six podium finishes in {{F1|2023}}.|alt=Leclerc driving the Ferrari SF-23 at the 2023 Austrian Grand Prix]]
Ferrari struggled for consistent race pace and tyre wear throughout
the early stages of {{F1|2023}}, as [[Red Bull Racing|Red Bull]] consolidated their advantage from the previous year.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/sainz-understanding-very-peaky-f1-car-ferraris-main-focus-for-2023/10510921/ |title=Sainz: Understanding "very peaky" F1 car Ferrari's main focus for 2023 |last=Cleeren |first=Filip |date=24 August 2023 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127022509/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/sainz-understanding-very-peaky-f1-car-ferraris-main-focus-for-2023/10510921/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12931215/charles-leclerc-says-belgian-gp-podium-gave-him-and-ferrari-a-smile-but-wants-team-to-understand-2023-car |title=Charles Leclerc says Belgian GP podium gave him and Ferrari a smile but wants team to 'understand' 2023 car |date=1 August 2023 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230810091655/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12931215/charles-leclerc-says-belgian-gp-podium-gave-him-and-ferrari-a-smile-but-wants-team-to-understand-2023-car |archive-date=10 August 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/why-ferrari-hit-a-ceiling-with-its-2023-f1-car-development/10557818/ |title=Why Ferrari hit a ceiling with its 2023 F1 car development |last1=Cleeren |first1=Filip |last2=Chinchero |first2=Roberto |date=14 December 2023 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=12 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240117074522/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/why-ferrari-hit-a-ceiling-with-its-2023-f1-car-development/10557818/ |archive-date=17 January 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc qualified third for the {{F1GP|2023|Bahrain}}, where he remained for the majority of the race before retiring with a technical issue.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/f1-charles-leclerc-ferrari-bahrain-grand-prix-b2294511.html |title='What happened guys?': Charles Leclerc left devastated after retiring at Bahrain Grand Prix |last=Rathborn |first=Jack |date=5 March 2023 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230330173538/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/f1-charles-leclerc-ferrari-bahrain-grand-prix-b2294511.html |archive-date=30 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/not-good-leclerc-despondent-after-bahrain-gp-double-blow/ |title='A second off' – Leclerc despondent at poor Ferrari pace and DNF |last1=Beer |first1=Matt |last2=Mitchell-Malm |first2=Scott |last3=Straw |first3=Edd |date=5 March 2023 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=6 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230305224959/https://the-race.com/formula-1/not-good-leclerc-despondent-after-bahrain-gp-double-blow/ |archive-date=5 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He subsequently took a [[Glossary of motorsport terms#G|grid penalty]] in [[2023 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix|Saudi Arabia]], recovering to seventh after starting twelfth with a ten-position drop.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/perez-fends-off-verstappen-to-win-action-packed-saudi-arabian-gp-as-alonso.329xV14gKVrf1iU6dOkISI |title=Pérez fends off Verstappen to win action-packed Saudi Arabian GP as Alonso takes 100th podium |date=19 March 2023 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]]  |access-date=9 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230319185544/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.perez-fends-off-verstappen-to-win-action-packed-saudi-arabian-gp-as-alonso.329xV14gKVrf1iU6dOkISI.html |archive-date=19 March 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc retired from the {{F1GP|2023|Australian}} following a first-lap collision with [[Lance Stroll]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-frustrated-by-worst-ever-start-to-an-f1-season-with-melbourne-dnf/10452656/ |title=Frustrated Leclerc says F1 2023 his "worst ever start" to a season |last=Cleeren |first=Filip |date=4 April 2023 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=9 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230509123640/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-frustrated-by-worst-ever-start-to-an-f1-season-with-melbourne-dnf/10452656/ |archive-date=9 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc then qualified on pole position at the {{F1GP|2023|Azerbaijan}}, finishing second in the sprint and third in the main race.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/apr/29/sergio-perez-wins-azerbaijan-sprint-race-for-red-bull-with-verstappen-third |title=Verstappen and Russell in angry clash after Pérez wins F1 Azerbaijan sprint |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=29 April 2023 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240527191924/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/apr/29/sergio-perez-wins-azerbaijan-sprint-race-for-red-bull-with-verstappen-third |archive-date=27 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/perez-leads-red-bull-one-two-in-dramatic-azerbaijan-gp-to-cut-verstappens.3UgBHOtrbFlmDdYEixNuDR |title=Pérez heads Red Bull one–two in dramatic Azerbaijan GP to cut Verstappen's championship lead |date=30 April 2023 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=9 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230507130847/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.perez-leads-red-bull-one-two-in-dramatic-azerbaijan-gp-to-cut-verstappens.3UgBHOtrbFlmDdYEixNuDR.html |archive-date=7 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> After crashing out of qualifying in [[2023 Miami Grand Prix|Miami]], he started and finished seventh.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/ferrari-on-a-knife-edge-the-unknown-issues-plaguing-its-2023-f1-car/ |url-access=registration |title=Ferrari on a knife edge: the 'unknown' issues plaguing its 2023 F1 car |last=Dodgins |first=Tony |date=9 May 2023 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230510030859/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/ferrari-on-a-knife-edge-the-unknown-issues-plaguing-its-2023-f1-car/ |archive-date=10 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2023/05/07/miami-grand-prix-f1-live-latest-updates-news-weather/ |url-access=registration |title=Max Verstappen charges through field to take Miami Grand Prix win from Sergio Pérez |last=Cary |first=Tom |date=8 May 2023 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240103160557/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2023/05/07/miami-grand-prix-f1-live-latest-updates-news-weather/ |archive-date=3 January 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He improved to sixth at the {{F1GP|2023|Monaco}} after receiving a three-place grid drop for impeding [[Lando Norris]] in qualifying.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-apologised-to-leclerc-for-monaco-gp-qualifying-miscommunication/10475143/ |title=Ferrari apologised to Leclerc for Monaco F1 qualifying miscommunication |last=Cooper |first=Adam |date=29 May 2023 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240621020625/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-apologised-to-leclerc-for-monaco-gp-qualifying-miscommunication/10475143/ |archive-date=21 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> In [[2023 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]], he qualified nineteenth and started the race from the [[pit lane]]—describing the [[Ferrari SF-23|SF-23]] as "undriveable"; he finished the race eleventh.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-left-searching-for-answers-after-very-very-weird-feeling-leads-to.5iGhrcbOb9eujtTn9l2F4i |title=Leclerc left searching for answers after 'very, very weird' feeling leads to shock Q1 exit in Spain |date=3 June 2023 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250113195013/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-left-searching-for-answers-after-very-very-weird-feeling-leads-to.5iGhrcbOb9eujtTn9l2F4i |archive-date=13 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12896492/spanish-grand-prix-charles-leclerc-and-carlos-sainz-bemoan-ferrari-struggles-after-disappointing-race |title=Spanish Grand Prix: Charles Leclerc and Carlos Sainz bemoan Ferrari struggles after disappointing race |last=Johnston |first=Sam |date=5 June 2023 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230619071008/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12896492/spanish-grand-prix-charles-leclerc-and-carlos-sainz-bemoan-ferrari-struggles-after-disappointing-race |archive-date=19 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc recovered from tenth to fourth in [[2023 Canadian Grand Prix|Canada]] after a [[pit stop]] gamble under the [[safety car]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/18/sports/autoracing/f1-canadian-grand-prix-tv-results.html |url-access=registration |title=Verstappen Wins Another Day of Follow the Leader |last1=Das |first1=Andrew |last2=Katz |first2=Josh |date=18 June 2023 |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241122175958/https://www.nytimes.com/2023/06/18/sports/autoracing/f1-canadian-grand-prix-tv-results.html |archive-date=22 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/its-definitely-encouraging-says-leclerc-of-ferraris-canadian-gp-turnaround.4Q0WQVP3ivDWHYDH5Ep9UY |title='It's definitely encouraging' says Leclerc of Ferrari's Canadian GP turnaround as Sainz addresses team orders call |date=19 June 2023 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=14 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241016014217/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/its-definitely-encouraging-says-leclerc-of-ferraris-canadian-gp-turnaround.4Q0WQVP3ivDWHYDH5Ep9UY |archive-date=16 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He qualified on the front-row for the {{F1GP|2023|Austrian}}, leading briefly before being overtaken by [[Max Verstappen]] for the win.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/verstappen-makes-biggest-statement-so-far-amid-deluge-of-f1-track-limits-penalties-2023-austrian-gp-report/ |url-access=registration |title=Verstappen's biggest statement yet amid F1 penalty deluge: 2023 Austrian GP report |last=Medland |first=Chris |date=2 July 2023 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230703104705/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/verstappen-makes-biggest-statement-so-far-amid-deluge-of-f1-track-limits-penalties-2023-austrian-gp-report/ |archive-date=3 July 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished ninth and seventh at the [[2023 British Grand Prix|British]] and [[2023 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungarian]] Grands Prix, respectively, amidst issues with tyre degradation and strategy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12474/12918503/british-gp-charles-leclerc-says-ferraris-difficulties-at-silverstone-surpassed-his-expectations |title=British GP: Charles Leclerc says Ferrari's difficulties at Silverstone surpassed his expectations |date=11 July 2023 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250214192446/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12474/12918503/british-gp-charles-leclerc-says-ferraris-difficulties-at-silverstone-surpassed-his-expectations |archive-date=14 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/38062679/water-radio-issues-add-leclercs-hungary-frustrations |title=Water and radio issues add to Leclerc's Hungary frustrations |last=Edmondson |first=Laurence |date=24 July 2023 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230728084904/https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/38062679/water-radio-issues-add-leclercs-hungary-frustrations |archive-date=28 July 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc achieved another pole position at the {{F1GP|2023|Belgian}} after a grid penalty for Verstappen;<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/jul/28/charles-leclerc-on-pole-at-belgian-gp-after-max-verstappen-penalty |title=Charles Leclerc on pole at Belgian GP after Max Verstappen penalty |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=28 July 2023 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231112154151/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/jul/28/charles-leclerc-on-pole-at-belgian-gp-after-max-verstappen-penalty |archive-date=12 November 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> he finished third.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2023-belgian-grand-prix--7-talking-points/ |title=2023 Belgian Grand Prix {{!}} 7 talking points |last=Smith |first=Damien |date=31 July 2023 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213032656/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2023-belgian-grand-prix--7-talking-points/ |archive-date=13 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> After retiring from the rain-affected {{F1GP|2023|Dutch}} with damage,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/why-leclerc-getting-biggest-dutch-gp-call-right-is-important-for-ferraris-f1-future/10513176/ |url-access=subscription |title=Why Leclerc getting biggest Dutch GP call right is important for Ferrari's F1 future |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=30 August 2023 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240805035833/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/why-leclerc-getting-biggest-dutch-gp-call-right-is-important-for-ferraris-f1-future/10513176/ |archive-date=5 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc finished fourth at the following three races in [[2023 Italian Grand Prix|Italy]], [[2023 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]], and [[2023 Japanese Grand Prix|Japan]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/im-sure-many-people-did-not-enjoy-that-leclerc-and-sainz-reflect-on-their.4exq4m37oPwHiOb6CoNFuC |title='We were at the limit of the regulations' – Leclerc and Sainz reflect on their thrilling Italian GP battle |date=3 September 2023 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=14 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240916094023/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/im-sure-many-people-did-not-enjoy-that-leclerc-and-sainz-reflect-on-their.4exq4m37oPwHiOb6CoNFuC |archive-date=16 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/leclercs-singapore-sacrifice-for-sainz-a-driver-too-good-to-be-no2/ |url-access=registration |title=Leclerc's Singapore sacrifice for Sainz – a driver too good to be No2 |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=18 September 2023 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241211193525/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/leclercs-singapore-sacrifice-for-sainz-a-driver-too-good-to-be-no2/ |archive-date=11 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-thought-japan-f1-podium-was-on-after-mistaking-perez-for-verstappen/10525158/ |title=Leclerc thought Japan F1 podium was on after mistaking Pérez for Verstappen |last=Cleeren |first=Filip |date=25 September 2023 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240718081854/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-thought-japan-f1-podium-was-on-after-mistaking-perez-for-verstappen/10525158/ |archive-date=18 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He then finished fifth in [[2023 Qatar Grand Prix|Qatar]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/oct/08/verstappen-storms-to-qatar-win-after-hamilton-and-russells-gutting-crash  |title=Verstappen storms to Qatar win after Hamilton's and Russell's 'gutting' crash |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=8 October 2023 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240116145507/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/oct/08/verstappen-storms-to-qatar-win-after-hamilton-and-russells-gutting-crash |archive-date=16 January 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He returned to pole at the {{F1GP|2023|United States}} and finished second in the sprint.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/2023-f1-us-gp-results-max-verstappen-wins-sprint-at-austin/10535992/ |title=2023 F1 US GP results: Max Verstappen wins sprint in Austin |last=Bradley |first=Charles |date=21 October 2023 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240720200212/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/2023-f1-us-gp-results-max-verstappen-wins-sprint-at-austin/10535992/ |archive-date=20 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He fell to sixth in the main race before being disqualified for excessive [[skid block]] wear, alongside [[Lewis Hamilton]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/breaking-hamilton-and-leclerc-disqualified-from-united-states-grand-prix-for.10nvuyvEPfMgoeWxWOhw0a |title=Hamilton and Leclerc disqualified from United States Grand Prix for technical breach |date=23 October 2023 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=26 October 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231026025059/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article.breaking-hamilton-and-leclerc-disqualified-from-united-states-grand-prix-for.10nvuyvEPfMgoeWxWOhw0a.html |archive-date=26 October 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc again qualified on pole in [[2023 Mexico City Grand Prix|Mexico City]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/67252776 |title=Mexico City Grand Prix: Ferrari's Charles Leclerc takes surprise pole position ahead of Carlos Sainz |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=29 October 2023 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231102002451/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/67252776 |archive-date=2 November 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> finishing third after a first-corner collision with [[Sergio Pérez]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2023/10/29/mexico-city-grand-prix-f1-live-verstappen-hamilton-updates/ |url-access=registration |title=Max Verstappen eases to Mexico City GP win after Sergio Pérez crashes out on opening lap |last=Duncan |first=Filip |date=30 October 2023 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240114234953/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2023/10/29/mexico-city-grand-prix-f1-live-verstappen-hamilton-updates/ |archive-date=14 January 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He qualified on the front-row for the {{F1GP|2023|São Paulo}}, before crashing out of the [[formation lap]] amidst a [[Hydraulic cylinder|hydraulics]] issue at ''[[Interlagos Circuit|Ferradura]]''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/must-see-front-row-starter-charles-leclerc-spins-off-on-the-sao-paulo-gp.2wYo12iTPrKDXHPPYVuorJ |title=Must-See: Front-row starter Charles Leclerc spins off on the São Paulo GP formation lap |date=5 November 2023 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=12 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240526081314/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/must-see-front-row-starter-charles-leclerc-spins-off-on-the-sao-paulo-gp.2wYo12iTPrKDXHPPYVuorJ |archive-date=26 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He qualified on pole again for the inaugural {{F1GP|2023|Las Vegas}},<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/nov/18/las-vegas-f1-qualifying-report-charles-leclerc-pole-fans-no-apology |title=Charles Leclerc lights up Las Vegas for pole as F1 refuses to apologise after farce |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=18 November 2023 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240228104141/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/nov/18/las-vegas-f1-qualifying-report-charles-leclerc-pole-fans-no-apology |archive-date=28 February 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> where he was involved in a three-way battle for the lead with Verstappen and Pérez; Leclerc finished second after overtaking the latter on the final lap,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2023/11/19/las-vegas-grand-prix-2023-f1-live-latest-updates-usa/ |url-access=registration |title=Max Verstappen gets penalty, hits George Russell and still wins Las Vegas GP |last=Cary |first=Tom |date=19 November 2023 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241016010943/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2023/11/19/las-vegas-grand-prix-2023-f1-live-latest-updates-usa/ |archive-date=16 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> which later won him the [[Overtake Award]].<ref name="OA23"/> He finished second again in [[2023 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix|Abu Dhabi]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-explains-late-bid-to-help-perez-in-f1-abu-dhabi-gp/10552192/ |title=Leclerc explains late bid to help Pérez in F1 Abu Dhabi GP |last=Cleeren |first=Filip |date=26 November 2023 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240814174843/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-explains-late-bid-to-help-perez-in-f1-abu-dhabi-gp/10552192/ |archive-date=14 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> elevating him to fifth in the World Drivers' Championship on 206 [[List of Formula One World Championship points scoring systems|points]], level with [[Fernando Alonso]] in fourth,{{efn-num|Leclerc and Alonso both scored 206 points in {{F1|2023}}, with Alonso classified ahead on [[Glossary of motorsport terms#C|count-back]], by virtue of having more third-placed finishes.}} and six ahead of teammate [[Carlos Sainz Jr.]] in seventh.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/p2-is-all-that-mattered-leclerc-explains-late-race-tactics-with-perez-in-bid.6w7vZo2dvczq6hqRPArV0m |title='P2 is all that mattered' – Leclerc explains late-race tactics with Pérez in bid to help Ferrari overhaul Mercedes |date=26 November 2023 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=14 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240915165817/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/p2-is-all-that-mattered-leclerc-explains-late-race-tactics-with-perez-in-bid.6w7vZo2dvczq6hqRPArV0m |archive-date=15 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc achieved five pole positions and six podiums throughout the season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-2023-team-mate-head-to-head-battles/10555611/ |title=F1 2023 team-mate head-to-head battles |last=Hardy |first=Ed |date=6 December 2023 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240815084142/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-2023-team-mate-head-to-head-battles/10555611/ |archive-date=15 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

[[File:2024-08-24 Motorsport, Formel 1, Großer Preis der Niederlande 2024 STP 3435 by Stepro.jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc (pictured at the {{F1GP|2024|Dutch}}) won three Grands Prix from 13 podiums in {{F1|2024}}, including the {{F1GP|2024|Monaco}}.|alt=Leclerc driving the Ferrari SF-24 at the 2024 Dutch Grand Prix]]
Ahead of the {{F1|2024}} season, Leclerc opted to extend his contract with Ferrari beyond the [[2026 Formula One World Championship#Regulation changes|2026 regulation changes]].<ref name="contract">{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-signs-ferrari-f1-contract-extension/10569077/ |title=Leclerc signs Ferrari F1 contract extension |last=Cleeren |first=Filip |date=25 January 2024 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=25 January 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240125141820/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-signs-ferrari-f1-contract-extension/10569077/ |archive-date=25 January 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Red Bull remained the front-runners going into the [[2024 Bahrain Grand Prix|season-opener]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/f1-red-bull-mercedes-jenson-button-b2476222.html |title=Jenson Button predicts Red Bull's closest challengers in new F1 season |last=Jackson |first=Kieran |date=10 January 2024 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240227153246/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/f1-red-bull-mercedes-jenson-button-b2476222.html |archive-date=27 February 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/how-red-bull-got-a-2024-headstart-by-cutting-development-on-last-years-f1-car/ |url-access=registration |title=How Red Bull got a 2024 headstart by cutting development on last year's F1 car |last=Medland |first=Chris |date=1 March 2024 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241201235024/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/how-red-bull-got-a-2024-headstart-by-cutting-development-on-last-years-f1-car/ |archive-date=1 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> where Leclerc vowed he would do "absolutely everything" to contend;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-red-bull-form-a-mystery-after-it-hid-potential-in-f1-testing/10581032/ |title=Leclerc: Red Bull form a mystery after it hid potential in F1 testing |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=29 February 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240921022106/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-red-bull-form-a-mystery-after-it-hid-potential-in-f1-testing/10581032/ |archive-date=21 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he qualified on the front-row and finished fourth amidst brake issues.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-had-more-than-100-degrees-split-in-brake-temperature-in-f1-bahrain-gp/10582416/ |title=Leclerc had "more than 100 degrees split" in brake temperature in F1 Bahrain GP |last1=Cobb |first1=Hayden |last2=Cleeren |first2=Filip |date=2 March 2024 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250108135104/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-had-more-than-100-degrees-split-in-brake-temperature-in-f1-bahrain-gp/10582416/ |archive-date=8 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He improved to third at the {{F1GP|2024|Saudi Arabian}},<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/68524759 |title=Saudi Arabian Grand Prix 2024: Max Verstappen wins as Oliver Bearman finishes seventh |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=9 March 2024 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240913035755/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/68524759 |archive-date=13 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> before completing a Ferrari [[Glossary of motorsport terms#0–9|1–2 finish]] in [[2024 Australian Grand Prix|Australia]]—their first since the [[2022 Bahrain Grand Prix]]—as he finished second to Sainz.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/13100364/australia-gp-carlos-sainz-leads-ferrari-one-two-from-charles-leclerc-after-max-verstappen-streak-ends-with-retirement |title=Australian GP: Carlos Sainz leads Ferrari one–two from Charles Leclerc after Max Verstappen streak ends with retirement |date=25 March 2024 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241211173424/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/13100364/australia-gp-carlos-sainz-leads-ferrari-one-two-from-charles-leclerc-after-max-verstappen-streak-ends-with-retirement |archive-date=11 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> After finishing fourth at both the [[2024 Japanese Grand Prix|Japanese]] and [[2024 Chinese Grand Prix|Chinese]] Grands Prix,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/2024-f1-japanese-gp-results-max-verstappen-wins-red-flagged-race/10596032/ |title=2024 F1 Japanese GP results: Max Verstappen wins red-flagged race |last=Bradley |first=Charles |date=7 April 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240520164338/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/2024-f1-japanese-gp-results-max-verstappen-wins-red-flagged-race/10596032/ |archive-date=20 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2024/apr/21/max-verstappen-f1-chinese-grand-prix-victory-report-lando-norris-second |title=Max Verstappen charges to F1 Chinese GP victory with Lando Norris second |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=21 April 2024 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240529083347/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2024/apr/21/max-verstappen-f1-chinese-grand-prix-victory-report-lando-norris-second |archive-date=29 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc secured third-placed finishes in [[2024 Miami Grand Prix|Miami]] and [[2024 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix|Emilia Romagna]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2024/05/06/sport/lando-norris-2024-miami-grand-prix-spt-intl/index.html |title=Lando Norris claims first win of F1 career, storming to victory at Miami Grand Prix in front of star-studded crowd |last1=Morse |first1=Ben |last2=Schlachter |first2=Thomas |date=6 May 2024 |work=[[CNN]] |publisher=[[Warner Bros. Discovery]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241214022312/https://edition.cnn.com/2024/05/06/sport/lando-norris-2024-miami-grand-prix-spt-intl/index.html |archive-date=14 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.thetimes.com/sport/formula-one/article/lando-norris-keeps-pace-with-max-verstappen-italian-grand-prix-csrvmzs77 |url-access=subscription |title=Lando Norris finishes less than a second behind Max Verstappen at Imola |last=Hudson |first=Molly |date=19 May 2024 |work=[[The Times]] |publisher=[[News UK]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0140-0460 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240524102701/https://www.thetimes.com/sport/formula-one/article/lando-norris-keeps-pace-with-max-verstappen-italian-grand-prix-csrvmzs77 |archive-date=24 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> as well as second in the former sprint race.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/2024-f1-miami-gp-sprint-results-max-verstappen-wins/10606767/ |title=2024 F1 Miami GP sprint results: Max Verstappen wins |last=Bradley |first=Charles |date=4 May 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240530133744/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/2024-f1-miami-gp-sprint-results-max-verstappen-wins/10606767/ |archive-date=30 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc then won the {{F1GP|2024|Monaco}}—his home race—for the first time in his career, having started on pole position.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5520279/2024/05/26/charles-leclerc-f1-monaco-gp-results/ |title=Charles Leclerc wins F1 Monaco GP in emotional home victory |last=Coleman |first=Madeline |date=26 May 2024 |work=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240926224516/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5520279/2024/05/26/charles-leclerc-f1-monaco-gp-results/ |archive-date=26 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He became the first Monégasque driver to win the event since [[Louis Chiron]] in [[1931 Monaco Grand Prix|1931]], and the first in the Formula One World Championship.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/facts-and-stats-first-monegasque-winner-in-monaco-since-1931-as-leclerc.4iQxLmf1Hz5i9OLxtuXdDt |title=Facts and Stats: First Monégasque winner in Monaco since 1931, as Leclerc finally breaks his curse on home soil |last=Kelly |first=Sean |date=26 May 2024 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=27 May 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240527081444/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/facts-and-stats-first-monegasque-winner-in-monaco-since-1931-as-leclerc.4iQxLmf1Hz5i9OLxtuXdDt |archive-date=27 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc retired from the {{F1GP|2024|Canadian}} with [[Formula One engines|power unit]] issues.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://racer.com/2024/06/09/leclerc-frustrated-by-pu-issue-as-ferrari-suffers-double-dnf/ |title=Leclerc frustrated by PU issue as Ferrari suffers double-DNF |last=Medland |first=Chris |date=9 June 2024 |magazine=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer]] |publisher=[[Racer (magazine)|Racer Media & Marketing Inc.]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1066-6060 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241007033007/https://racer.com/2024/06/09/leclerc-frustrated-by-pu-issue-as-ferrari-suffers-double-dnf/ |archive-date=7 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> After placing fifth at the {{F1GP|2024|Spanish}},<ref name="ESP24">{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2024/06/23/spanish-grand-prix-live-updates/ |url-access=registration |title=Lando Norris rues costly bad start as Max Verstappen wins Spanish Grand Prix |last=Cary |first=Tom |date=23 June 2024 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240926150537/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2024/06/23/spanish-grand-prix-live-updates/ |archive-date=26 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he finished outside of the [[List of Formula One World Championship points scoring systems|points]] in [[2024 Austrian Grand Prix|Austria]] and [[2024 British Grand Prix|Britain]] due to collision damage and strategy errors,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2024-austrian-grand-prix--8-talking-points/ |title=2024 Austrian Grand Prix {{!}} 8 talking points |last=Smith |first=Damien |date=1 July 2024 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240719121515/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2024-austrian-grand-prix--8-talking-points/ |archive-date=19 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-in-worse-than-a-nightmare-after-failed-british-gp-intermediate-call/10632839/ |title=Leclerc in "worse than a nightmare" after failed British GP intermediate call |last1=Boxall-Legge |first1=Jake |last2=Cleeren |first2=Filip |date=7 July 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240719004323/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-in-worse-than-a-nightmare-after-failed-british-gp-intermediate-call/10632839/ |archive-date=19 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> dropping him from second to third in the standings behind Norris.<ref name="ESP24"/> He then finished fourth in [[2024 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/article/2024/jul/21/oscar-piastri-wins-f1-hungarian-gp-after-mcclaren-team-soap-opera |title=Oscar Piastri wins F1 Hungarian GP after McLaren order Norris to give up lead |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=21 July 2024 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240927235755/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/article/2024/jul/21/oscar-piastri-wins-f1-hungarian-gp-after-mcclaren-team-soap-opera |archive-date=27 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc again qualified on pole at the {{F1GP|2024|Belgian}} after a grid drop for Verstappen,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/articles/c897295r1p7o |title=Leclerc on Belgian GP pole as Verstappen takes grid penalty |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=27 July 2024 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240913045437/https://www.bbc.com/sport/articles/c897295r1p7o |archive-date=13 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> finishing third after a disqualification for [[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/george-russell-disqualified-belgian-gp-mercedes-f1-b2587297.html |title=George Russell disqualified after winning Belgian Grand Prix |last=Jackson |first=Kieran |date=28 July 2024 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250131222915/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/george-russell-disqualified-belgian-gp-mercedes-f1-b2587297.html |archive-date=31 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Another third-place followed at the {{F1GP|2024|Dutch}}.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/articles/cn9l7wn4xx3o |title=Dominant Norris fights back to win Dutch GP |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=25 August 2024 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240913034843/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/articles/cn9l7wn4xx3o |archive-date=13 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc received widespread acclaim for his surprise victory at the {{F1GP|2024|Italian}},<ref name="ITA24">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/nobodys-perfect-but-leclerc-came-close-with-final-monza-stint-/10650874/ |title="Nobody's perfect" – but Leclerc came close with final Monza stint |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=3 September 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240915205726/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/nobodys-perfect-but-leclerc-came-close-with-final-monza-stint-/10650874/ |archive-date=15 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/winners-losers-f1-2024-italian-grand-prix/ |title=Winners and losers from F1's 2024 Italian Grand Prix |last1=Suttill |first1=Josh |last2=Beer |first2=Matt |last3=Kanal |first3=Samarth |date=1 September 2024 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240916153211/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/winners-losers-f1-2024-italian-grand-prix/ |archive-date=16 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2024-italian-grand-prix--6-talking-points/ |title=2024 Italian Grand Prix {{!}} 6 talking points |last=Smith |first=Damien |date=2 September 2024 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241102075135/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2024-italian-grand-prix--6-talking-points/ |archive-date=2 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> completing a one-stop strategy to secure Ferrari's first home win since [[2019 Italian Grand Prix|2019]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/article/2024/sep/01/charles-leclerc-wins-italian-f1-gp-for-ferrari-oscar-piastri-lando-norris |title=Charles Leclerc wins Italian F1 GP for Ferrari after one-stop gamble |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=1 September 2024 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=1 September 2024 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240922182142/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/article/2024/sep/01/charles-leclerc-wins-italian-f1-gp-for-ferrari-oscar-piastri-lando-norris |archive-date=22 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc qualified first at the {{F1GP|2024|Azerbaijan}}—his fourth consecutive pole at the event—and finished second after a race-long battle with [[Oscar Piastri]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-azerbaijan-gp-race-report/10654520/ |title=F1 Azerbaijan GP: Piastri beats Leclerc after thrilling Baku battle |last=Cleeren |first=Filip |date=15 September 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241222173112/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-azerbaijan-gp-race-report/10654520/ |archive-date=22 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished fifth in [[2024 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-left-with-mixed-feelings-after-fightback-to-p5-in-singapore-as-he.10ZR07GCa8NNotxfSQ1ri6 |title=Leclerc left with 'mixed feelings' after fightback to P5 in Singapore as he takes blame for qualifying mistake |date=22 September 2024 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=15 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241003132900/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-left-with-mixed-feelings-after-fightback-to-p5-in-singapore-as-he.10ZR07GCa8NNotxfSQ1ri6 |archive-date=3 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> before taking his third victory of the season at the {{F1GP|2024|United States}}.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5857103/2024/10/20/charles-leclerc-f1-us-grand-prix-lando-norris-max-verstappen/ |title=Charles Leclerc wins F1 U.S. Grand Prix, Lando Norris loses podium to late penalty |last=Coleman |first=Madeline |date=20 October 2024 |work=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250205182214/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5857103/2024/10/20/charles-leclerc-f1-us-grand-prix-lando-norris-max-verstappen/ |archive-date=5 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He then finished third in [[2024 Mexico City Grand Prix|Mexico City]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2024/10/28/sport/carlos-sainz-mexican-grand-prix-f1-spt-intl/index.html |title=Carlos Sainz wins Mexican Grand Prix as penalties for Max Verstappen cut into championship lead |last=Joseph |first=Sam |date=28 October 2024 |work=[[CNN]] |publisher=[[Warner Bros. Discovery]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241204134837/https://edition.cnn.com/2024/10/28/sport/carlos-sainz-mexican-grand-prix-f1-spt-intl/index.html |archive-date=4 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> After a podium in the [[2024 São Paulo Grand Prix|São Paulo]] sprint,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2024/nov/02/norris-wins-brazil-gp-sprint-race-after-piastri-cedes-lead-under-team-orders |title=Norris wins São Paulo GP sprint to narrow gap as Verstappen hit with penalty |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=2 November 2024 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241126215747/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2024/nov/02/norris-wins-brazil-gp-sprint-race-after-piastri-cedes-lead-under-team-orders |archive-date=26 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> he finished fifth in the rain-affected Grand Prix amidst car performance concerns and a strategy error.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/sainz-cannot-explain-sao-paulo-crashes-as-leclerc-admits-sao-paulo-was.il6XaXBGLr7lkmstHuSol |title=Sainz 'cannot explain' São Paulo crashes as Leclerc admits weekend was 'damage limitation' for Ferrari |date=4 November 2024 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=15 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250129072326/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/sainz-cannot-explain-sao-paulo-crashes-as-leclerc-admits-sao-paulo-was.il6XaXBGLr7lkmstHuSol |archive-date=29 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Following a fourth-placed finish in [[2024 Las Vegas Grand Prix|Las Vegas]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/13259854/charles-leclerc-ferrari-driver-hits-out-at-team-in-expletive-laden-radio-rant-at-las-vegas-grand-prix |title=Charles Leclerc: Ferrari driver hits out at team in expletive-laden radio rant at Las Vegas Grand Prix |date=24 November 2024 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241211215057/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/13259854/charles-leclerc-ferrari-driver-hits-out-at-team-in-expletive-laden-radio-rant-at-las-vegas-grand-prix |archive-date=11 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc completed the season with podiums at the [[2024 Qatar Grand Prix|Qatar]] and [[2024 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix|Abu Dhabi]] Grands Prix, having started the latter in nineteenth.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2024/12/01/qatar-grand-prix-2024-f1-live-russell-verstappen0/ |url-access=registration |title=Lando Norris apologises for 'f------ up' Qatar GP as McLaren hit out at FIA penalty |last=Cary |first=Tom |date=1 December 2024 |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |access-date=1 December 2024 |issn=0307-1235 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241223122020/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/formula-1/2024/12/01/qatar-grand-prix-2024-f1-live-russell-verstappen0/ |archive-date=23 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="AS2024">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/general/news/autosport-top-50-of-2024-2-charles-leclerc/10683383/ |title=Autosport Top 50 of 2024: #2 Charles Leclerc |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=19 December 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250130164306/https://www.autosport.com/general/news/autosport-top-50-of-2024-2-charles-leclerc/10683383/ |archive-date=30 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished the season third in the championship on 356 points—81 behind champion Verstappen, 18 behind Norris, and 66 ahead of teammate Sainz in fifth;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/the-top-10-f1-drivers-of-2024/ |title=The top 10 F1 drivers of 2024 |last=Parkes |first=Ian |date=19 December 2024 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250113190249/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/the-top-10-f1-drivers-of-2024/ |archive-date=13 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/end-of-year-report-ferrari-a-huge-step-forward-in-a-successful-season-but.3WHiu8Kv6fNZVw3DNswyls |title=End of Year Report: Ferrari – A 'huge step forward' in a successful season, but can they improve further in 2025? |last=Francis |first=Anna |date=23 December 2024 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=15 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250129052714/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/end-of-year-report-ferrari-a-huge-step-forward-in-a-successful-season-but.3WHiu8Kv6fNZVw3DNswyls |archive-date=29 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> he outscored the rest of the field from the summer break onwards,<ref name="AS2024"/> and achieved three victories from 13 podiums.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/interview-charles-leclerc-on-hamilton-and-being-ready-for-the-championship/ |title=Interview: Charles Leclerc on Hamilton and being "ready for the championship" |last=Parkes |first=Ian |date=14 January 2025 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250118163548/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/interview-charles-leclerc-on-hamilton-and-being-ready-for-the-championship/ |archive-date=18 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2025: Partnership with Hamilton ====
[[File:FIA F1 Imola 2025 No. 16 Leclerc (2).jpg|thumb|right|Leclerc (pictured at the {{F1GP|2025|Emilia Romagna}}) is partnered by [[Lewis Hamilton]] from {{F1|2025}} onwards.|alt=Leclerc driving the Ferrari SF-25 at the 2025 Japanese Grand Prix]]
Leclerc is partnered by seven-time World Drivers' Champion [[Lewis Hamilton]] in {{F1|2025}}.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5243409/2024/02/01/lewis-hamilton-ferrari-mercedes/ |title=Lewis Hamilton to join Ferrari in shock switch from Mercedes |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=1 February 2024 |work=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250129012423/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5243409/2024/02/01/lewis-hamilton-ferrari-mercedes/ |archive-date=29 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Prior to the season, Leclerc stated he was "ready [to win] the championship",<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/interview-charles-leclerc-on-hamilton-and-being-ready-for-the-championship/ |title=Interview: Charles Leclerc on Hamilton and being "ready for the championship" |last=Parkes |first=Ian |date=14 January 2025 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=4 March 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250118163548/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/interview-charles-leclerc-on-hamilton-and-being-ready-for-the-championship/ |archive-date=18 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> with Ferrari now trailing [[McLaren]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/f1-2025-news-season-predictions-australia-gp-b2708153.html |title=F1 2025 season predictions: Who will win, Hamilton vs Leclerc and the biggest shock? |last=Jackson |first=Kieran |date=4 March 2025 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=4 March 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250305140557/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/f1-2025-news-season-predictions-australia-gp-b2708153.html |archive-date=5 March 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished eighth at the rain-affected {{F1GP|2025|Australian}} after a strategic error,<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a64197404/ferrari-falters-in-f1-opener-as-rain-shakes-up-melbourne-race/ |title=Ferrari Falters in F1 Opener as Rain Shakes Up Melbourne Race |last=Horton |first=Phillip |date=16 March 2025 |magazine=[[Autoweek]] |publisher=[[Hearst Communications]] |access-date=17 March 2025 |issn=0192-9674 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250317005105/https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a64197404/ferrari-falters-in-f1-opener-as-rain-shakes-up-melbourne-race/ |archive-date=17 March 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> and was disqualified from fifth in [[2025 Chinese Grand Prix|China]] after his [[Ferrari SF-25|SF-25]] was found to be underweight.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/lewis-hamilton-and-charles-leclerc-disqualified-from-chinese-gp-in-ferrari-f1-calamity-b2720061.html |title=Lewis Hamilton and Charles Leclerc disqualified from Chinese GP in F1 calamity for Ferrari |last=Jackson |first=Kieran |date=23 March 2025 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=23 March 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250323122547/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/lewis-hamilton-and-charles-leclerc-disqualified-from-chinese-gp-in-ferrari-f1-calamity-b2720061.html |archive-date=23 March 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He finished fourth at both the [[2025 Japanese Grand Prix|Japanese]] and [[2025 Bahrain Grand Prix|Bahrain]] Grands Prix amidst performance concerns,<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/racing/f1briefings/news/what-causes-f1-cars-to-spark-japanese-grand-prix-fires-explained-01jr22j8kzae |title=Charles Leclerc Calls Japan Race "Annoying" as Ferrari Struggle |last=Espinal |first=Nelson |date=6 April 2025 |magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]] |publisher=[[Minute Media]] |access-date=6 April 2025 |issn=0038-822X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250406184705/https://www.si.com/fannation/racing/f1briefings/news/charles-leclerc-calls-japan-race-annoying-as-ferrari-struggle-01jr5bybrtch |archive-date=6 April 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/ferraris-performance-a-snowball-effect-of-problems-says-leclerc/10713049/ |title=Ferrari's performance "a snowball effect" of problems, says Charles Leclerc |last=Harrington |first=Alex |date=13 April 2025 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=14 April 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250414010802/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/ferraris-performance-a-snowball-effect-of-problems-says-leclerc/10713049/ |archive-date=14 April 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> before claiming his first podium of the season with third-place in [[2025 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix|Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a64534559/formula-1-saudi-arabian-grand-prix-charles-leclerc-ferrari-first-f1-podium/ |title=Formula 1 Saudi Arabian Grand Prix: Charles Leclerc Gives Ferrari Its First F1 Podium of 2025 |last=Horton |first=Phillip |date=20 April 2025 |magazine=[[Autoweek]] |publisher=[[Hearst Communications]] |access-date=21 April 2025 |issn=0192-9674 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250421020753/https://www.autoweek.com/racing/formula-1/a64534559/formula-1-saudi-arabian-grand-prix-charles-leclerc-ferrari-first-f1-podium/ |archive-date=21 April 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He [[aquaplaned]] into the barriers during the [[parade lap|reconnaissance lap]] for the {{F1GP|2025|Miami}} sprint, later qualifying eighth for the main race, which he finished seventh.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-ferrari-f1-car-is-too-slow-after-disappointing-miami-quali/10719556/ |title=Leclerc: Ferrari F1 car is too slow after disappointing Miami quali |last=Cleeren |first=Filip |date=3 May 2025 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=3 May 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250504174538/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-ferrari-f1-car-is-too-slow-after-disappointing-miami-quali/10719556/ |archive-date=4 May 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/lewis-hamilton-charles-leclerc-ferrari-miami-gp-b2744994.html |title='No bad feelings' between Ferrari drivers after Miami GP radio spat, says Charles Leclerc |last=Clifford |first=Flo |date=5 May 2025 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=24 May 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250506150337/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/lewis-hamilton-charles-leclerc-ferrari-miami-gp-b2744994.html |archive-date=6 May 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He climbed from eleventh to fourth in [[2025 Emilia Romagna Grand Prix|Emilia Romagna]] before a late [[safety car]] saw him drop to sixth on aging [[Formula One tyres|tyres]]—85 [[List of Formula One World Championship points scoring systems|points]] behind championship leader [[Oscar Piastri]], Leclerc stated he "[could not] accept the situation [Ferrari were] in".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ferrari.com/en-GQ/formula1/articles/emilia-romagna-grand-prix-2025-race |title=Race recap: Lewis fourth, Charles sixth |date=18 May 2025 |website=[[Scuderia Ferrari]] |publisher=[[Ferrari]] |access-date=24 May 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250524185236/https://www.ferrari.com/en-GQ/formula1/articles/emilia-romagna-grand-prix-2025-race |archive-date=24 May 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/frustrated-charles-leclerc-cannot-accept-the-situation-at-ferrari/10724240/ |title=Frustrated Leclerc "cannot accept" the situation at Ferrari |last=Hunt |first=Ben |date=18 May 2025 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=24 May 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250518193504/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/frustrated-charles-leclerc-cannot-accept-the-situation-at-ferrari/10724240/ |archive-date=18 May 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Ferrari resurged in [[2025 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]] with Leclerc qualifying and finishing second,<ref name="MS2025">{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/mark-hughes-leclerc-is-senna-like-at-monaco-but-his-ferraris-a-dud/ |url-access=registration |title=Mark Hughes: 'Leclerc is Senna-like at Monaco but his Ferrari's a dud' |last=Hughes |first=Mark |date=28 May 2025 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=30 May 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250530054421/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/mark-hughes-leclerc-is-senna-like-at-monaco-but-his-ferraris-a-dud/ |archive-date=30 May 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> before claiming third in [[2025 Spanish Grand Prix|Spain]] following a late [[safety car]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2025/jun/01/oscar-piastri-holds-off-norris-as-mclaren-claim-one-two-in-spanish-f1-gp |title=Piastri leads McLaren one–two in Spanish F1 GP as Verstappen pays penalty |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=1 June 2025 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=10 June 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250602093222/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2025/jun/01/oscar-piastri-holds-off-norris-as-mclaren-claim-one-two-in-spanish-f1-gp |archive-date=2 June 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> fifth in [[2025 Canadian Grand Prix|Canada]],<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/13385519/ferrari-had-clumsy-canadian-gp-says-nico-rosberg-as-f1-team-admit-too-many-mistakes-made-in-montreal |title=Ferrari had 'clumsy' Canadian GP says Nico Rosberg as F1 team admit 'too many mistakes' made in Montreal |date=19 June 2025 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=27 June 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250623111030/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/13385519/ferrari-had-clumsy-canadian-gp-says-nico-rosberg-as-f1-team-admit-too-many-mistakes-made-in-montreal |archive-date=23 June 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> and third again in [[2025 Austrian Grand Prix|Austria]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-reveals-frustrating-lift-and-coast-strategy-in-lonely-austrian-gp/10738062/ |title=Charles Leclerc reveals frustrating lift and coast strategy in lonely Austrian GP |last=Mee |first=Lydia |date=30 June 2025 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=6 July 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250701025044/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-reveals-frustrating-lift-and-coast-strategy-in-lonely-austrian-gp/10738062/ |archive-date=1 July 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was self-critical after squandering [[pole position]] in [[2025 British Grand Prix|Britain]], qualifying sixth before finishing fourteenth on a mistimed wet-weather strategy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/british-gp-2025-f1-driver-rankings-edd-straw/ |title=Edd Straw's 2025 British Grand Prix F1 driver rankings |last=Straw |first=Edd |date=7 July 2025 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=24 July 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250708140014/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/british-gp-2025-f1-driver-rankings-edd-straw/ |archive-date=8 July 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Fourth in the {{F1GP|2025|Belgian}} sprint,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-ferrari-has-no-hope-of-fighting-for-f1-belgian-gp-win/10745398/ |title=Leclerc: Ferrari has no hope of fighting for F1 Belgian GP win |last=Codling |first=Stuart |date=26 July 2025 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=2 August 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250802155028/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-ferrari-has-no-hope-of-fighting-for-f1-belgian-gp-win/10745398/ |archive-date=2 August 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> he qualified third and held position from Verstappen in the wet–dry main race.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2025-belgian-grand-prix/ |title=Imperious Piastri passes Norris for Belgian win |last=Smith |first=Damien |date=28 July 2025 |website=[[Goodwood Circuit|Goodwood Road & Racing]] |publisher=[[Goodwood House]] |access-date=2 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250802155036/https://www.goodwood.com/grr/f1/2025-belgian-grand-prix/ |archive-date=2 August 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He took a surprise pole in [[2025 Hungarian Grand Prix|Hungary]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6532103/2025/08/02/charles-leclerc-pole-f1-hungarian-grand-prix-2025/ |title=How Charles Leclerc snared shock Ferrari Hungary pole: 'Today, I don't understand F1' |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=2 August 2025 |work=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=3 August 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250802213052/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6532103/2025/08/02/charles-leclerc-pole-f1-hungarian-grand-prix-2025/ |archive-date=2 August 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> where he led the majority of the race before dropping to fourth after encountering setup issues.<ref name="HUN25">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-explains-how-undriveable-ferrari-cost-him-hungary-f1-win/10748206/ |title=Leclerc explains how "undriveable" Ferrari F1 car cost him Hungarian GP win |last1=Vinel |first1=Ben |last2=Karpov |first2=Oleg |date=3 August 2025 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=3 August 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250803170241/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-explains-how-undriveable-ferrari-cost-him-hungary-f1-win/10748206/ |archive-date=3 August 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He ran fifth at the {{F1GP|2025|Dutch}} until a collision with [[Kimi Antonelli]] at ''[[Circuit Zandvoort|Hugenholtzbocht]]'' forced his retirement,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/wolff-backs-antonelli-after-leclerc-clash-we-want-him-to-go-for-moves/10755477 |title=Wolff backs Antonelli after Leclerc clash: "We want him to go for moves" |last1=Cleeren |first1=Filip |last2=Jaeggi |first2=Erwin |date=1 September 2025 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=3 September 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250903035258/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/wolff-backs-antonelli-after-leclerc-clash-we-want-him-to-go-for-moves/10755477/ |archive-date=3 September 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> before maintaining fourth in [[2025 Italian Grand Prix|Italy]] amidst an early battle with third-placed Piastri.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-ferraris-best-shot-at-2025-f1-victory-comes-at-these-three-grands-prix/10757558 |title=Charles Leclerc: Ferrari's best shot at 2025 F1 victory comes at these three grands prix |last=Mee |first=Lydia |date=7 September 2025 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 September 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250908222032/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-ferraris-best-shot-at-2025-f1-victory-comes-at-these-three-grands-prix/10757558/ |archive-date=8 September 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He crashed out of qualifying in [[2025 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan]] and finished ninth,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-cites-power-unit-glitch-for-subdued-azerbaijan-gp-start/10761419 |title=Charles Leclerc cites power unit glitch for subdued Azerbaijan GP start |last1=Harrington |first1=Alex |last2=Karpov |first2=Oleg |date=21 September 2025 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=25 October 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250925232722/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-cites-power-unit-glitch-for-subdued-azerbaijan-gp-start/10761419 |archive-date=25 September 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> prior to claiming sixth in [[2025 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]] amidst increasing concerns with the SF-25.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/46507017/leclerc-downbeat-singapore-passengers-car |title=Leclerc downbeat after Singapore: We're 'passengers to the car' |last=Saunders |first=Nate |date=6 October 2025 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=25 October 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251008102745/https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/46507017/leclerc-downbeat-singapore-passengers-car |archive-date=8 October 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Fifth in the [[2025 United States Grand Prix|United States]] sprint, he retained third in the Grand Prix in a race-long battle for second with [[Lando Norris]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.silverstone.co.uk/news/f1-2025-united-states-grand-prix-results-hunt-verstappen-claims-maximum-points-austin |title=F1 2025 United States Grand Prix results: The hunt is on as Verstappen claims maximum points in Austin |date=20 October 2025 |website=[[Silverstone Circuit]] |publisher=[[British Racing Drivers' Club]] |access-date=25 October 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251025214517/https://www.silverstone.co.uk/news/f1-2025-united-states-grand-prix-results-hunt-verstappen-claims-maximum-points-austin |archive-date=25 October 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> His [[Glossary of motorsport terms#F|front-row start]] in [[2025 Mexico City Grand Prix|Mexico City]] preceded a contentious first-corner encounter with Norris, Hamilton, and Verstappen, where Leclerc retained second after evading to the [[run-off area]] and withstanding a late Verstappen charge.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6751859/2025/10/26/mexico-city-grand-prix-briefing-norris-wins-bearman-impresses-disaster-for-hamilton |title=Mexico City Grand Prix briefing: Norris wins, Bearman impresses, disaster for Hamilton |last1=Coleman |first1=Madeline |last2=Smith |first2=Luke |date=26 October 2025 |work=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=30 October 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251030112816/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6751859/2025/10/26/mexico-city-grand-prix-briefing-norris-wins-bearman-impresses-disaster-for-hamilton/ |archive-date=30 October 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Driver profile ==
=== Qualifying pace ===
{{quote box|quote=As a driver, you always have the confidence you are the fastest and I do have that whenever I go for a qualifying lap.

It's all about that mindset and putting that lap together in qualifying when it is needed and the pressure is super-high. This is an exercise I have always loved.

I've always said I drive a lot with intuition, I work a lot, of course. But that is where one of my strengths is—that I feel things very, very quickly.|source=—Leclerc, asked by ''[[BBC Sport]]'' whether he was the fastest qualifier in Formula One in {{F1|2024}}<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/articles/c3gw95yx0pyo |title=Leclerc on 'incredible' Hamilton, mindset & Ferrari dip |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=18 July 2024 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250203083611/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/articles/c3gw95yx0pyo |archive-date=3 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>|width=35%|align=right|fontsize=85%}}
Leclerc has a strong qualifying history in Formula One, where he holds the record for [[List of Formula One driver records#Other driver records|most pole positions without a World Drivers' Championship]] ({{f1stat|LEC|poles}}).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/how-many-pole-positions-f1-drivers/ |title=How many pole positions does each 2025 F1 driver have? |date=20 January 2025 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127064455/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/how-many-pole-positions-f1-drivers/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He also holds the record in either [[FIA Formula 2]] or its predecessor [[GP2 Series|GP2]] for the most [[pole position]]s in a season (8).<ref name="SkyF2"/> His driving style tends to favour a car with [[oversteer]], allowing for precise micro-corrections and high cornering speeds, which has aided his qualifying pace.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/the-driving-style-secrets-of-f1s-current-stars/10568984/ |url-access=subscription |title=The driving style secrets of F1's current stars |last1=Chandhok |first1=Karun |last2=Kalinauckas |first2=Alex |date=26 January 2024 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=31 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127064451/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/the-driving-style-secrets-of-f1s-current-stars/10568984/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He became the youngest recipient of the [[FIA Pole Trophy]] in {{F1|2019}} for achieving the most pole positions,<ref name="FIA19"/> a feat he repeated in {{F1|2022}}.<ref name="2022analysis"/> Critics have noted his ability to outperform his machinery in qualifying conditions, which has frequently led to his one-lap pace relatively surpassing his race pace and a [[List of Formula One driver records#Percentage pole positions converted to wins (at least 5 poles)|pole–win conversion rate]] of {{percentage|5|{{F1stat|LEC|poles}}|1}}<!--AS OF HUN25-->.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/the-top-10-formula-1-drivers-of-2022/ |title=Top 10 Formula 1 drivers of 2022 – Our verdict |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=25 November 2022 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127064451/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/the-top-10-formula-1-drivers-of-2022/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/charles-leclerc-absurd-f1-ratio-criminally-undeserved/ |title=Leclerc's absurd F1 ratio is criminally undeserved |last1=Mitchell-Malm |first1=Scott |last2=Suttill |first2=Josh |date=7 January 2024 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127064452/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/charles-leclerc-absurd-f1-ratio-criminally-undeserved/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Andrew Benson of ''[[BBC Sport]]'' described his pole lap at the [[2019 Singapore Grand Prix]] as "one of the qualifying performances of the season".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/49781160 |title=Singapore GP qualifying: Charles Leclerc beats Lewis Hamilton to pole |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=21 September 2019 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250211074709/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/49781160 |archive-date=11 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> A study by [[Amazon Web Services]] in 2020 listed Leclerc as the seventh-fastest Formula One driver of all time.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/machine-learning/the-fastest-driver-in-formula-1/ |title=The fastest driver in Formula 1 |last1=Smedley |first1=Rob |last2=Wise |first2=Colby |last3=Enkhbayar |first3=Delger |last4=Price |first4=George |last5=Cheng |first5=Ryan |last6=Yang |first6=Guang |date=20 August 2020 |website=[[Amazon Web Services]] |publisher=[[Amazon (company)|Amazon]] |access-date=15 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127064451/https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/machine-learning/the-fastest-driver-in-formula-1/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> 

After his back-to-back poles at the [[2021 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]] and [[2021 Azerbaijan Grand Prix|Azerbaijan]] Grands Prix in {{F1|2021}}, then-teammate [[Carlos Sainz Jr.]] proclaimed Leclerc as the best qualifier in Formula One.<ref name="TR21">{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/sainz-claims-leclerc-is-f1s-best-qualifier-our-verdict/ |title=Sainz claims Leclerc is F1's 'best qualifier' – Our verdict |last=Suttill |first=Josh |date=17 June 2021 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250128134945/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/sainz-claims-leclerc-is-f1s-best-qualifier-our-verdict/ |archive-date=28 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Edd Straw of ''The Race'' commented that "if you’re talking about a driver who can consistently wring the neck of a car regardless of its limitations and successfully live on the edge in a livewire qualifying lap then you need to look no further than [Leclerc]", and that "his willingness to be on or even slightly over the limit, mitigated by his outstanding car control when things do get untidy, allows him to drag stunning lap times even out of cars that aren’t handling well."<ref name="TR21"/> He described his "relentless pursuit of perfect laps" as a characteristic that could make Leclerc "one of [the] all-time greatest qualifiers".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/why-leclerc-may-go-down-as-an-all-time-f1-qualifying-great/ |title=Why Leclerc may go down as an all-time F1 qualifying great |last=Straw |first=Edd |date=5 June 2022 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=26 March 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240525045331/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/why-leclerc-may-go-down-as-an-all-time-f1-qualifying-great/ |archive-date=25 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Laurence Edmondson of ''[[ESPN]]'' described his pole lap at the [[2022 Azerbaijan Grand Prix]] as his "latest example of his pinpoint precision and masterful speed", adding that he was "undoubtedly making a claim for the title of [Formula One]'s fastest driver over a single lap"; he praised "his ability to extract the fastest laps consistently while dealing with the pressure of a title fight".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/34075200/is-charles-leclerc-fastest-driver-f1 |title=Is Charles Leclerc the fastest driver in F1? |last1=Edmondson |first1=Laurence |last2=Saunders |first2=Nate |date=11 June 2022 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250212045527/https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/34075200/is-charles-leclerc-fastest-driver-f1 |archive-date=12 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Mark Hughes (journalist)|Mark Hughes]] described him as "[[Ayrton Senna|Senna]]-like" at [[Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]], noting his {{convert|5|kph|mph|abbr=on}} advantage at the high-speed ''[[Circuit de Monaco|Tabac]]'' in [[2025 Monaco Grand Prix|2025]].<ref name="MS2025"/> His pole lap at the {{F1GP|2025|Hungarian}} that year—where he usurped the dominant [[McLaren MCL39]]—was described as "sensational".{{efn|Per several sources: <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/articles/cqledzx1wgno |title=Spectacular Leclerc takes surprise Hungarian Grand Prix pole |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=2 August 2025 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=3 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250803175144/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/articles/cqledzx1wgno |archive-date=3 August 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/ferrari-charles-leclerc-stuns-mclaren-shock-hungarian-gp-f1-pole/ |title=Leclerc stuns McLarens to take shock Hungary F1 pole |last=Khorounzhiy |first=Valentin |date=2 August 2025 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=3 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250803175232/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/ferrari-charles-leclerc-stuns-mclaren-shock-hungarian-gp-f1-pole/ |archive-date=3 August 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://speedcafe.com/f1-news-2025-charles-leclerc-stuns-mclaren-sensational-hungarian-grand-prix-pole/ |title=Leclerc stuns McLaren to take sensational Hungarian GP pole |last=Waterworth |first=Ben |date=3 August 2025 |website=[[Speedcafe]] |publisher=[[Speedcafe|BAM Media Group]] |access-date=3 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250803175507/https://speedcafe.com/f1-news-2025-charles-leclerc-stuns-mclaren-sensational-hungarian-grand-prix-pole/ |archive-date=3 August 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>}}<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/analysis-where-leclerc-found-his-hungary-f1-pole-advantage-and-where-mclaren-lost-its-pace/10747891/ |title=Analysis: Where Leclerc found his Hungary F1 pole advantage, and where McLaren lost its pace |last=Boxall-Legge |first=Jake |date=2 August 2025 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=3 August 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250803174238/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/analysis-where-leclerc-found-his-hungary-f1-pole-advantage-and-where-mclaren-lost-its-pace/10747891/ |archive-date=3 August 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Karun Chandhok]] has acclaimed Leclerc as the fastest qualifier of all time,<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/archive/article/february-2025/48/the-top-ten-f1-drivers-of-2024/ |url-access=registration |title=The top ten F1 drivers of 2024 |last=Chandhok |first=Karun |date=February 2025 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |pages=50–51 |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127064451/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/archive/article/february-2025/48/the-top-ten-f1-drivers-of-2024/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Martin Brundle]] opined he was the fastest amongst the {{F1|2023}} drivers.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24096/13017491/martin-brundle-assessing-the-abu-dhabi-gp-and-delivering-the-verdict-on-formula-1s-2023-season |title=Martin Brundle: Assessing the Abu Dhabi GP and delivering the verdict on Formula 1's 2023 season |last=Brundle |first=Martin |date=28 November 2023 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250214111034/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24096/13017491/martin-brundle-assessing-the-abu-dhabi-gp-and-delivering-the-verdict-on-formula-1s-2023-season |archive-date=14 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Racecraft ===
[[File:Ferrari's Charles Leclerc battles for the podium with Mercedes' Lewis Hamilton at the 2022 British Grand Prix at Silverstone. (52196620083) (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc ''(back)'' racing against [[Lewis Hamilton]] ''(front)'' at the [[2022 British Grand Prix]]|alt=Leclerc racing against Lewis Hamilton at the 2022 British Grand Prix]]
Leclerc has been noted by critics for his proficiency in wheel-to-wheel racing.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2018/sep/12/charles-leclerc-ferrari-sauber-rookie |title=Charles Leclerc looks like a gamble by Ferrari – but he's not |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=12 September 2018 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231023055108/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/blog/2018/sep/12/charles-leclerc-ferrari-sauber-rookie |archive-date=23 October 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> After ceding the lead of the [[2019 Austrian Grand Prix]] to [[Max Verstappen]] in the closing laps, Leclerc claimed his move was "not the way you overtake" and that he would adjust his aggression going forward.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-verstappen-austrian-gp-pass-not-the-way-you-overtake-4991839/4991839/ |title=Leclerc: Verstappen Austrian GP pass "not the way you overtake" |last1=Mitchell |first1=Scott |last2=Nimmervoll |first2=Christian |date=30 June 2019 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=28 January 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230529033859/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/leclerc-verstappen-austrian-gp-pass-not-the-way-you-overtake-4991839/4991839/ |archive-date=29 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="AUT19"/> The [[2019 British Grand Prix|following race]], he beat Verstappen in a hard-fought contest for third, which Vijay Pattni of ''[[Top Gear (magazine)|Top Gear]]'' summarised as "holy heck, what a fight. Both younglings threw their cars at each other, both refused to yield any space, and both—miracously—avoided coming together."<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.topgear.com/car-news/formula-one/2019-british-gp-was-ace-because-verstappen-vs-leclerc |title=The 2019 British GP was ace because Verstappen vs Leclerc |last=Pattni |first=Vijay |date=15 July 2019 |magazine=[[Top Gear (magazine)|Top Gear]] |publisher=[[Immediate Media Company]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |issn=1350-9624 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240808161820/https://www.topgear.com/car-news/formula-one/2019-british-gp-was-ace-because-verstappen-vs-leclerc |archive-date=8 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc declared it "the most fun [he'd] had in [Formula One]",<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-declares-battling-silverstone-drive-the-most-fun-ive-had-in-f1.1YYTgHj5hME1kPfeOoDu4O |title=Leclerc declares battling Silverstone drive 'the most fun I've had in F1' |date=14 July 2019 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241210232149/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/leclerc-declares-battling-silverstone-drive-the-most-fun-ive-had-in-f1.1YYTgHj5hME1kPfeOoDu4O |archive-date=10 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> whilst Verstappen added "I think he was a little bit sore still from Austria so he was defending really hard, but it's fine, I'm all for that".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/robust-leclerc-still-sore-after-austria-formula-1-clash-verstappen-4991215/4991215/ |title=Robust Leclerc still 'sore' after Austria Formula 1 clash – Verstappen |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=15 July 2019 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220902061233/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/robust-leclerc-still-sore-after-austria-formula-1-clash-verstappen-4991215/4991215/ |archive-date=2 September 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was nicknamed ''il Predestinato'' ({{lit|the [[Predestined]]}}) in Italian media after defending his lead at the [[2019 Italian Grand Prix]] from both [[Lewis Hamilton]] and [[Valtteri Bottas]].{{efn|name=ilP}} He was praised for his first-corner overtake on Bottas at the [[2021 Spanish Grand Prix]],<ref name="2021ESP1">{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12302112/charles-leclerc-delighted-with-standout-and-amazing-ferrari-after-superb-fourth-at-spanish-gp |title=Charles Leclerc delighted with 'standout' and 'amazing' Ferrari after superb fourth at Spanish GP |date=9 May 2021 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=7 February 2025 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20250130022357/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/12433/12302112/charles-leclerc-delighted-with-standout-and-amazing-ferrari-after-superb-fourth-at-spanish-gp |archive-date=30 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> with Jonathan Noble of ''[[Motorsport.com]]'' describing the move as "sensational".<ref name="2021ESP2">{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-bottas-sensational-overtake-barcelona/6506044/ |title=F1: Leclerc explains sensational Bottas pass in Barcelona |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=10 May 2021 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=7 February 2025 |archive-url=http://web.archive.org/web/20250130021743/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/leclerc-bottas-sensational-overtake-barcelona/6506044/ |archive-date=30 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> 

Leclerc received acclaim for his battle with Verstappen at the [[2022 Bahrain Grand Prix]], noted for his effective use of the [[drag reduction system]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/mar/20/charles-leclerc-wins-dramatic-bahrain-f1-gp-as-ferrari-bring-home-one-two |title=Charles Leclerc wins dramatic Bahrain F1 GP as Ferrari bring home one–two |last=Richards |first=Giles |date=20 March 2022 |work=[[The Guardian]] |publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |issn=1756-3224 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241213121251/https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2022/mar/20/charles-leclerc-wins-dramatic-bahrain-f1-gp-as-ferrari-bring-home-one-two |archive-date=13 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/max-is-aggressive-but-so-am-i-how-leclerc-made-his-point/ |title='Max is aggressive, but so am I' – How Leclerc made his point |last=Mitchell-Malm |first=Scott |date=21 March 2022 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=23 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250213094906/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/max-is-aggressive-but-so-am-i-how-leclerc-made-his-point/ |archive-date=13 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-bahrain-gp-leclerc-leads-ferrari-1-2-red-bull-challenge-implodes/9167868/ |title=F1 Bahrain GP: Leclerc leads Ferrari 1–2, Red Bull challenge implodes |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=20 March 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250127070229/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-bahrain-gp-leclerc-leads-ferrari-1-2-red-bull-challenge-implodes/9167868/ |archive-date=27 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He was praised by Hamilton after their battle at the [[2022 British Grand Prix]], where Leclerc overtook him around the outside of ''[[Silverstone Circuit|Copse]]'' on older tyres.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24181/12645434/lewis-hamilton-aims-max-verstappen-dig-after-sensible-charles-leclerc-fight-at-british-gp |title=Lewis Hamilton aims Max Verstappen dig after 'sensible' Charles Leclerc fight at British GP |date=5 July 2022 |website=[[Sky Sports]] |publisher=[[Sky Group]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250206210101/https://www.skysports.com/f1/news/24181/12645434/lewis-hamilton-aims-max-verstappen-dig-after-sensible-charles-leclerc-fight-at-british-gp |archive-date=6 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Alex Kalinauckas of ''[[Autosport]]'' lauded his racecraft after the {{F1|2024}} season, highlighting several instances of his defensive driving against faster machinery, as well as an overtake on [[George Russell (racing driver)|George Russell]] at the {{F1GP|2024|Chinese}}.<ref name="AS2024"/> He was further acclaimed for his tyre management at the {{F1GP|2024|Italian}}.<ref name="ITA24"/> He has also been criticised for race-ending mistakes throughout his early seasons in Formula One, particularly at the [[2020 Italian Grand Prix|2020 Italian]], [[2020 Sakhir Grand Prix|2020 Sakhir]], and [[2022 French Grand Prix|2022 French]] Grands Prix;<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/leclercs-past-f1-mistakes-hint-at-how-hell-react-to-imola/ |title=Leclerc's past F1 mistakes hint at how he'll react to Imola |last=Mitchell-Malm |first=Scott |date=28 April 2022 |website=The Race |publisher=The Race Media |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240614064550/https://www.the-race.com/formula-1/leclercs-past-f1-mistakes-hint-at-how-hell-react-to-imola/ |archive-date=14 June 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="SAK20"/><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/critics-who-label-charles-leclerc-error-prone-have-got-it-wrong/ |url-access=registration |title='Critics who label Charles Leclerc error-prone have got it wrong' |last=Dodgins |first=Tony |date=30 July 2022 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220811092932/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/critics-who-label-charles-leclerc-error-prone-have-got-it-wrong |archive-date=11 August 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> he was further penalised for causing a collision with Verstappen at the [[2019 Japanese Grand Prix]] and for erratically defending from Russell at the [[2025 Hungarian Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/27833451/verstappen-slams-stewards-irresponsible-leclerc |title=Verstappen slams stewards and 'irresponsible' Leclerc |date=13 October 2019 |website=[[ESPN]] |publisher=[[ESPN Inc.]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250128100441/https://www.espn.co.uk/f1/story/_/id/27833451/verstappen-slams-stewards-irresponsible-leclerc |archive-date=28 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="HUN25"/> The {{F1|1996}} World Drivers' Champion, [[Damon Hill]], described his racing mentality as "win or bust".<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/hes-got-the-ingredients-1996-world-champion-damon-hill-picks-the-title.7ompTx6dsTUE9BibGmJoBA |title='He's got the ingredients' – 1996 world champion Damon Hill picks the title winners of the future |date=1 October 2024 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=4 August 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250622121607/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/hes-got-the-ingredients-1996-world-champion-damon-hill-picks-the-title.7ompTx6dsTUE9BibGmJoBA |archive-date=22 June 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Helmet ===
[[File:2020 F1 Pre-Season Testing Catalonia (49629040498).jpg|thumb|right|Leclerc's {{F1|2020}} helmet design featured the [[flag of Monaco]] surrounded by his logo in [[rosso corsa]].|alt=From above, Leclerc sat in the cockpit of his Ferrari SF1000 at 2020 Formula One pre-season testing]]
Leclerc's helmet design features a base colour of [[rosso corsa]] with a [[Monégasque flag]] stripe along the lid.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2024-f1-helmet-designs-every-drivers-racing-lid-for-new-campaign/ |url-access=registration |title=2024 F1 helmet designs: Every driver's racing lid for new campaign |last=Kisby |first=Cambridge |date=22 February 2024 |magazine=[[Motor Sport (magazine)|Motor Sport]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0027-2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250115122345/https://www.motorsportmagazine.com/articles/single-seaters/f1/2024-f1-helmet-designs-every-drivers-racing-lid-for-new-campaign/ |archive-date=15 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> The words "Papa" and "Jules" are inscribed on the side, in remembrance of his father, Hervé Leclerc, and his godfather, [[Jules Bianchi]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.monaco-tribune.com/en/2025/01/f1-leclercs-new-helmet-a-tribute-to-his-family/ |title=F1 : Leclerc's new helmet, a tribute to those he has lost |last=Riu |first=Anaïs |date=28 January 2025 |work=Monaco Tribune |access-date=15 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250216032943/https://www.monaco-tribune.com/en/2025/01/f1-leclercs-new-helmet-a-tribute-to-his-family/ |archive-date=16 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He wore a full tribute helmet to both at the [[2019 Monaco Grand Prix]] and to Bianchi at the [[2024 Japanese Grand Prix]], the tenth anniversary of [[2014 Japanese Grand Prix|his fatal accident]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/ferrari-vettel-leclerc-tribute-helmet-designs/4394616 |title=Ferrari stars pay their respects with tribute helmet designs |last1=Bradley |first1=Charles |last2=Cooper |first2=Adam |date=23 May 2019 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=7 September 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210803064642/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/ferrari-vettel-leclerc-tribute-helmet-designs/4394616 |archive-date=3 August 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/jules-bianchi-charles-leclerc-f1-japan-suzuka-b2523847.html |title=Jules Bianchi honoured as Charles Leclerc dons special helmet for godfather |last=Jackson |first=Kieran |date=5 April 2024 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241009133716/https://www.independent.co.uk/f1/jules-bianchi-charles-leclerc-f1-japan-suzuka-b2523847.html |archive-date=9 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He had previously worn a tribute for [[Sebastian Vettel]] at the [[2020 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix]]—their final race as teammates.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/russell-grosjean-and-vettel-reveal-one-off-helmet-designs-for-abu-dhabi.63dl0Gc2wM0mASvB0ZErIA |title=Russell, Grosjean, Leclerc and Vettel reveal one-off helmet designs for Abu Dhabi Grand Prix |date=11 December 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=15 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240808164445/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/russell-grosjean-and-vettel-reveal-one-off-helmet-designs-for-abu-dhabi.63dl0Gc2wM0mASvB0ZErIA |archive-date=8 August 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Controversy arose over his [[Gilles Villeneuve]] design for the [[2023 Canadian Grand Prix]], after the Villeneuve family claimed he did not ask for permission; [[Jacques Villeneuve]] permitted it after talking to Leclerc.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/villeneuve-hits-out-at-abuse-over-leclerc-f1-helmet-tribute/10484773/ |title=Jacques Villeneuve hits out at abuse over Leclerc F1 helmet tribute |last=Cleeren |first=Filip |date=18 June 2023 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=13 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240725124208/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/villeneuve-hits-out-at-abuse-over-leclerc-f1-helmet-tribute/10484773/ |archive-date=25 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He wore a tribute for departing teammate [[Carlos Sainz Jr.]] at the [[2024 Abu Dhabi Grand Prix]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5976230/2024/12/07/ferrari-carlos-sainz-charles-leclerc-f1/ |title=The end of Ferrari's 'C<sup>2</sup>': Leclerc and Sainz's genuine F1 partnership faces its sunset in Abu Dhabi |last=Coleman |first=Madelin |date=7 December 2024 |work=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250203165839/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5976230/2024/12/07/ferrari-carlos-sainz-charles-leclerc-f1/ |archive-date=3 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Other ventures ==
=== Film and television ===
[[File:Charles LeClerc, British GP 2018 (43025921904).jpg|thumb|right|Leclerc with a fan at the [[2018 British Grand Prix]]|alt=Leclerc signing a fan's autograph book at the 2018 British Grand Prix]]
Leclerc starred in [[Claude Lelouch]]'s ''Le Grand Rendez-vous'' (2020)—a remake of the 1976 French short film ''[[C'était un rendez-vous]]''—where he lapped the [[Circuit de Monaco]] in a [[Ferrari SF90 Stradale]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/general/news/leclerc-completes-monaco-filming-run/4796094/ |title=Leclerc completes Monaco run for remake of film |last=Kalinauckas |first=Alex |date=24 May 2020 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=24 May 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200706105648/https://www.motorsport.com/general/news/leclerc-completes-monaco-filming-run/4796094/?nrt=111 |archive-date=6 July 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref> In partnership with [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]], Leclerc made his [[voice acting]] debut in the Italian-language version of [[Pixar]]'s ''[[Toy Story (franchise)|Toy Story]]'' animated [[spinoff (media)|spin-off]] film ''[[Lightyear (film)|Lightyear]]'' (2022).<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.si.com/extra-mustard/2022/05/25/carlos-sainz-charles-leclerc-become-voice-actors-for-lightyear |title=Carlos Sainz, Charles Leclerc Become Voice Actors for 'Lightyear' |last=Coleman |first=Madeline |date=25 May 2022 |magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]] |publisher=[[Minute Media]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0038-822X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221229024933/https://www.si.com/extra-mustard/2022/05/25/carlos-sainz-charles-leclerc-become-voice-actors-for-lightyear |archive-date=29 December 2022 |url-status=live}}</ref> In November 2024, Leclerc appeared in ''Charles Leclerc – Supersonique'', a [[Canal+ (French TV channel)|Canal+]] documentary, where he attempted [[aerobatics]] in a [[Dassault Rafale]] with the [[French Air and Space Force]] at [[Saint-Dizier – Robinson Air Base]];<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://actus.sfr.fr/sport/charles-leclerc-supersonique-un-documentaire-inedit-a-voir-sur-canal_AN-202411030003.html |title=Charles Leclerc – Supersonique : un documentaire inédit à voir sur Canal+ |trans-title=Charles Leclerc – Supersonic: an unprecedented documentary on Canal+ |last=Tchikaya Boukhelifa |first=Charline |date=3 November 2024 |website=[[SFR]] |publisher=[[Altice (company)|Altice]] |language=fr |access-date=4 November 2024 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250123020331/https://actus.sfr.fr/sport/charles-leclerc-supersonique-un-documentaire-inedit-a-voir-sur-canal_AN-202411030003.html |archive-date=23 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> he used the [[Military call sign|call sign]] ''Perceval'' and successfully endured a {{Convert|9|g-force|lk=on|abbr=|m/s2 ft/s2}} manoeuvre, as well as an [[aerial refuelling]] mission.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aerotime.aero/articles/f1-charles-leclerc-flies-rafale-french-air-force |title=F1 driver Charles Leclerc trades Ferrari car for Rafale jet with French Air Force |last=Charpentreau |first=Clément |date=4 November 2024 |website=AeroTime |access-date=16 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241207122133/https://www.aerotime.aero/articles/f1-charles-leclerc-flies-rafale-french-air-force |archive-date=7 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Music ===
[[File:2022 French Grand Prix (52279070553).png|thumb|left|Leclerc before the [[2022 French Grand Prix]]|alt=Leclerc sitting on the back of a black convertible before the 2022 French Grand Prix]]
Leclerc began playing the [[piano]] aged six,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/long-read-music-fashion-and-family-getting-to-know-the-real-charles-leclerc.VVVqZ22G4p7is4NlQ2KZy |title=Long Read: Music, fashion and family – getting to know the real Charles Leclerc |last=Barretto |first=Lawrence |date=13 September 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241212225918/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/long-read-music-fashion-and-family-getting-to-know-the-real-charles-leclerc.VVVqZ22G4p7is4NlQ2KZy |archive-date=12 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> before committing to the instrument during the [[COVID-19 lockdowns]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/52358240 |title=Charles Leclerc on coronavirus lockdown: 'I want to put a smile on people's faces' |last=Benson |first=Andrew |date=23 April 2020 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200702205844/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/52358240 |archive-date=2 July 2020 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="RS2024">{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/product-recommendations/lifestyle/charles-leclerc-celsius-partnership-interview-1235088924/ |title=Drive to Thrive: Charles Leclerc Talks Race Rituals, Musical Motivations, and Fond Farewells |last=Chan |first=Tim |date=28 August 2024 |magazine=[[Rolling Stone]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0035-791X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240901020117/https://www.rollingstone.com/product-recommendations/lifestyle/charles-leclerc-celsius-partnership-interview-1235088924/ |archive-date=1 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2023, Leclerc released his debut piano-composed [[single (music)|single]] "AUS23 (1:1)",<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/formula-1-charles-leclerc-ferarri-music-b2328410.html |title=Formula 1 star Charles Leclerc makes surprise musical debut with dramatic piano piece |last=Parkel |first=Inga |date=27 April 2023 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=1741-9743 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230522105732/https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/music/news/formula-1-charles-leclerc-ferarri-music-b2328410.html |archive-date=22 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> whose title is a reference to Ferrari's internal name for the [[2023 Australian Grand Prix]].<ref name="NYT2023">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4551928/2023/05/25/charles-leclerc-piano-music/ |title=Charles Leclerc's music went from hobby to vital – and popular – 'off switch' |last=Smith |first=Luke |date=25 May 2023 |work=[[The Athletic]] |publisher=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250214022216/https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4551928/2023/05/25/charles-leclerc-piano-music/ |archive-date=14 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He released further singles for the [[2023 Miami Grand Prix|Miami]] and [[2023 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]] Grands Prix, titled "MIA23 (1:2)" and "MON23 (1:3)", respectively.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.classicfm.com/discover-music/charles-leclerc-piano-formula-one/ |title=F1 driver Charles Leclerc is a self-taught pianist who now composes his own music |last=Macdonald |first=Kyle |date=22 October 2023 |website=[[Classic FM (UK)|Classic FM]] |publisher=[[Global Media & Entertainment]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241224224632/https://www.classicfm.com/discover-music/charles-leclerc-piano-formula-one/ |archive-date=24 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He used [[Record producer|production software]] to pair his piano notes with [[violin]].<ref name="NYT2023"/> In February 2024, he released his debut [[extended play]], ''[[Dreamers (EP)|Dreamers]]'', alongside French pianist [[Sofiane Pamart]],<ref name="Dreamers"/> which peaked at number two on the ''[[Billboard charts|Billboard]]'' [[Classical music|Classical Albums]] chart and number one on the [[Crossover music|Classical Crossover Albums]] chart,<ref name="DreamersUSC"/><ref name="DreamersUSCC"/> amongst charting in [[GfK Entertainment charts|Germany]] and [[Swiss Hitparade|Switzerland]].<ref name="DreamersGER"/><ref name="DreamersSWI"/> Talking to ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' that year, Leclerc stated "whenever I'm not [racing], music is what I love."<ref name="RS2024"/> In February 2025, he released a [[A-side and B-side|two-sided single]] titled "MC24 / SIN24", featuring compositions from the [[2024 Monaco Grand Prix|Monaco]] and [[2024 Singapore Grand Prix|Singapore]] Grands Prix in {{F1|2024}}.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.si.com/fannation/racing/f1briefings/news/charles-leclerc-unveils-new-music-ahead-of-2025-f1-season-01jmaxq3bxrp |title=Charles Leclerc Unveils New Music Ahead Of 2025 F1 Season |last=Mee |first=Lydia |date=17 February 2025 |magazine=[[Sports Illustrated]] |publisher=[[Minute Media]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0038-822X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250218195311/https://www.si.com/fannation/racing/f1briefings/news/charles-leclerc-unveils-new-music-ahead-of-2025-f1-season-01jmaxq3bxrp |archive-date=18 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Endorsements ===
[[File:Charles-Leclerc (crop3).jpg|thumb|right|Leclerc (pictured in 2020) has been partnered with [[Richard Mille]] since 2009.|alt=Leclerc wearing a Ferrari polo shirt and Richard Mille watch, standing with his arms folded in front of a bookshelf]]
Leclerc has been partnered with Swiss [[luxury watch]] company [[Richard Mille]] since 2009, who supported him through his [[kart racing]] and [[junior formulae]] career.<ref name="RM">{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-richard-mille-a-shared-passion-for-racing/6637064/ |title=Ferrari & Richard Mille: A shared passion for racing |date=26 July 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231025185120/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/ferrari-richard-mille-a-shared-passion-for-racing/6637064/ |archive-date=25 October 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> He has also been sponsored by [[Bell Helmets]] throughout his career.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-helmet-and-racewear-company-to-become-publicly-owned/6788247/ |title=F1 helmet and racewear company to become publicly owned |date=16 November 2021 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240919152713/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/f1-helmet-and-racewear-company-to-become-publicly-owned/6788247/ |archive-date=19 September 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He launched his own [[go-kart]] brand in 2019, as part of a collaboration with [[Birel|Birel ART]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.vroomkart.com/news/36415/charles-leclerc-launches-his-frame-brand-with-birel-art |title=Charles Leclerc launches his frame brand with Birel ART! |last=Alosa |first=Maurizio |date=6 November 2019 |magazine=Vroomkart |access-date=20 February 2025 |issn=1724-9147 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240422094327/https://www.vroomkart.com/news/36415/charles-leclerc-launches-his-frame-brand-with-birel-art |archive-date=22 April 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> In 2020, Leclerc became an endorsement model for Italian fashion house [[Armani|Giorgio Armani]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.gq.com.au/fitness/sport/f1-young-gun-charles-leclerc-is-the-new-face-of-giorgio-armani/image-gallery/b5fabab249bbda849835cddb0a9f2f09 |title=F1 Young Gun Charles Leclerc Is The New Face Of Giorgio Armani |last=Nash |first=Brad |date=19 May 2020 |magazine=[[GQ Australia]] |publisher=[[Condé Nast]] |access-date=4 January 2021 |issn=0016-6979 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210513221929/https://www.gq.com.au/fitness/sport/f1-young-gun-charles-leclerc-is-the-new-face-of-giorgio-armani/image-gallery/b5fabab249bbda849835cddb0a9f2f09 |archive-date=13 May 2021 |url-status=live}}</ref> He has additionally held [[ambassador]]ship roles at [[APM Monaco]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.esquiremag.ph/style/charles-leclerc-apm-monaco-brand-ambassador-a2501-20240321 |title=From the Racetrack to Fine Jewelry: F1 Star Charles Leclerc is APM Monaco's New Brand Ambassador |last=Uy |first=Alvin |date=21 March 2024 |magazine=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire Philippines]] |publisher=[[Hearst Communications]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0194-9535 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250217183117/https://www.esquiremag.ph/style/charles-leclerc-apm-monaco-brand-ambassador-a2501-20240321 |archive-date=17 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Bang & Olufsen]],<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://variety.com/2024/shopping/athletes/charles-leclerc-bang-olufsen-earbuds-speakers-1236058827/ |title=Speed of Sound: F1 Star Charles Leclerc Races to New Partnership With Bang & Olufsen |last=Chan |first=Tim |date=2 July 2024 |magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] |publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=0042-2738 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240704020607/https://variety.com/2024/shopping/athletes/charles-leclerc-bang-olufsen-earbuds-speakers-1236058827/ |archive-date=4 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> [[Celsius Holdings]],<ref name="RS2024"/> [[Puma (brand)|Puma]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://autosprint.corrieredellosport.it/news/formula1/2024/10/11-7607140/charles_leclerc_e_il_nuovo_global_ambassador_di_puma |title=Charles Leclerc è il nuovo global ambassador di Puma |trans-title=Charles Leclerc is the new global ambassador of Puma |date=11 October 2024 |work=[[Corriere dello Sport|Autosprint]] |publisher=[[Corriere dello Sport]] |language=it |issn=2531-3843 |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250217181821/https://autosprint.corrieredellosport.it/news/formula1/2024/10/11-7607140/charles_leclerc_e_il_nuovo_global_ambassador_di_puma |archive-date=17 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> and [[Chivas Regal]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.complex.com/sports/a/steve-slocombe/charles-leclerc-chivas-regal-new-global-brand-ambassador |title=Chivas Regal Unveils Ferrari F1 Driver Charles Leclerc As New Global Brand Ambassador |last=Slocombe |first=Steve |date=4 March 2025 |website=[[Complex (website)|Complex]] |publisher=[[Complex Networks]] |access-date=27 October 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251027212340/https://www.complex.com/sports/a/steve-slocombe/charles-leclerc-chivas-regal-new-global-brand-ambassador |archive-date=27 October 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2024, Leclerc launched an eponymous [[ice cream]] brand called ''LEC'', a reference to his three-letter code on Formula One television graphics.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2024/06/17/style/ferrari-formula-one-charles-leclerc-ice-cream.html |url-access=registration |title=From Ferrari to the Frozen Food Aisle |last=Olsen |first=Kerry |date=17 June 2024 |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |issn=1553-8095 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250214112107/https://www.nytimes.com/2024/06/17/style/ferrari-formula-one-charles-leclerc-ice-cream.html |archive-date=14 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Philanthropy ===
Leclerc was named an [[ambassador]] of the {{ill|Princess Charlene of Monaco Foundation|fr|Fondation Princesse Charlène de Monaco}} in 2018, helping to promote the benefits of learning to swim.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.hellomonaco.com/news/latest-news/charles-leclerc-is-ambassador-for-princess-charlene-foundation/ |title=Charles Leclerc is Ambassador for Princess Charlene Foundation |date=21 December 2018 |website=HelloMonaco |access-date=16 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241208070814/https://www.hellomonaco.com/news/latest-news/charles-leclerc-is-ambassador-for-princess-charlene-foundation/ |archive-date=8 December 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> In April 2020, he won the ''Race for the World'' [[sim racing]] championship, raising over {{currency|70,000|USD}} for the [[COVID-19 Solidarity Response Fund]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://lat.motorsport.com/esports/news/leclerc-titulo-esports-pilotos-recaudan-70-mil-dolares/4781996/ |title=Leclerc gana título de Esports y pilotos recaudan 70 mil dólares |trans-title=Leclerc wins Esports title and drivers raise $70 thousand |last=Suttill |first=Josh |date=17 April 2020 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |language=es-419 |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240410211821/https://lat.motorsport.com/esports/news/leclerc-titulo-esports-pilotos-recaudan-70-mil-dolares/4781996/ |archive-date=10 April 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> The following month, he assisted the [[Red Cross of Monaco]] by delivering meals and transporting hospital equipment amidst the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Monaco]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/charles-leclerc-volunteering-with-the-monaco-red-cross-to-help-coronavirus.4BpIts9gVqvJlOb20T00Gb |title=Charles Leclerc volunteering with the Monaco Red Cross to help coronavirus effort |date=30 April 2020 |website=[[Formula 1]] |publisher=[[Formula One Group]] |access-date=16 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250129152225/https://www.formula1.com/en/latest/article/charles-leclerc-volunteering-with-the-monaco-red-cross-to-help-coronavirus.4BpIts9gVqvJlOb20T00Gb |archive-date=29 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Leclerc [[auction]]ed the equipment he wore at the [[2023 Monaco Grand Prix]], raising {{currency|368,800|EUR}} for victims of the [[2023 Emilia-Romagna floods|Emilia-Romagna floods]]; his [[Racing helmet|helmet]] sold for a record €306,000.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/formula1/65850693 |title=Charles Leclerc: Ferrari driver's race helmet breaks record at Emilia-Romagna flood auction |date=8 June 2023 |work=[[BBC Sport]] |publisher=[[BBC]] |access-date=17 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230617054721/https://www.bbc.com/sport/formula1/65850693 |archive-date=17 June 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
[[File:2021 British Grand Prix (51349271106).jpg|thumb|left|Leclerc driving the [[Ferrari 375 F1]] at the [[2021 British Grand Prix]]|alt=Leclerc driving the Ferrari 375 F1 before the 2021 British Grand Prix]]
Leclerc is [[trilingual]]: he is fluent in French, Italian, and English.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/en/charles_leclerc_wins_the_monza_grand_prix_triumphs_for_ferrari_in_italy-8328124.html |title=Charles Leclerc Wins the Monza Grand Prix, Triumphs for Ferrari in Italy |date=1 September 2024 |work=[[Il Messaggero]] |publisher=[[Caltagirone Editore]] |issn=1126-8352 |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250223010249/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/en/charles_leclerc_wins_the_monza_grand_prix_triumphs_for_ferrari_in_italy-8328124.html |archive-date=23 February 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> Outside of motor racing, he is interested in [[architecture]], music, and fashion.<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.thegentlemansjournal.com/article/charles-leclerc-interview-2024/ |title=The life goals and lessons of Charles Leclerc |last=Smith |first=Rory |date=Summer 2024 |magazine=Gentleman's Journal |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=2052-4285 |issue=43 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250114224608/https://www.thegentlemansjournal.com/article/charles-leclerc-interview-2024/ |archive-date=14 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> He chose 16 as his personal driver number in Formula One because the digits sum to his lucky number, seven, in addition to it also being his birth date—16 October; his first options, seven and 10, were taken by [[Kimi Räikkönen]] and [[Pierre Gasly]], respectively.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/f1-race-numbers-2023-which-driver-uses-what-number/10404332/ |title=2024 F1 driver race numbers: Who uses what number and why? |last=Bekking |first=Casper |date=6 January 2024 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250114132315/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/f1-race-numbers-2023-which-driver-uses-what-number/10404332/ |archive-date=14 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> From 2019 to 2022, Leclerc was in a relationship with Monégasque architect and [[influencer]] Charlotte Siné, daughter of the then–[[director general]] of the [[Société des Bains de Mer de Monaco]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://madame.lefigaro.fr/celebrites/actu-people/coup-de-foudre-sur-les-circuits-charlotte-sine-la-monegasque-qui-a-conquis-charles-leclerc-le-pilote-prodige-de-f1-20220323 |title=Coup de foudre sur les circuits : Charlotte Siné, la Monégasque qui a conquis Charles Leclerc, le pilote prodige de F1 |trans-title=Love at first sight on the circuits: Charlotte Siné, the Monégasque who won Charles Leclerc, the F1 prodigy driver |last=Dutrievoz |first=Leonie |date=23 March 2022 |magazine=[[Madame Figaro]] |publisher=[[Le Figaro]] |language=fr |access-date=23 February 2025 |issn=0246-5205 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241012133435/https://madame.lefigaro.fr/celebrites/actu-people/coup-de-foudre-sur-les-circuits-charlotte-sine-la-monegasque-qui-a-conquis-charles-leclerc-le-pilote-prodige-de-f1-20220323 |archive-date=12 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://f1i.autojournal.fr/infos/people/charles-leclerc-et-charlotte-sine-officialisent-leur-rupture/ |title=Charles Leclerc et Charlotte Siné se séparent ! |trans-title=Charles Leclerc and Charlotte Siné separate! |last=Georges |first=Rémy |date=7 December 2022 |magazine=[[L'Auto-Journal]] |publisher=[[Reworld Media]] |language=fr |issn=0005-0768 |access-date=23 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230515145637/https://f1i.autojournal.fr/infos/people/charles-leclerc-et-charlotte-sine-officialisent-leur-rupture/ |archive-date=15 May 2023 |url-status=live}}</ref> Since 2023, he has been in a relationship with French influencer Alexandra Saint Mleux;<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.tatler.com/article/who-is-alexandra-saint-mleux-f1-wag-charles-leclerc-girlfriend |title=Ferrari WAG, Rhode pin-up, Monaco gallerina: is Alexandra Saint Mleux the most glamorous woman in Formula 1? |last=Parker |first=Jasmine |date=5 December 2024 |magazine=[[Tatler]] |publisher=[[Condé Nast]] |access-date=19 February 2025 |issn=0039-9906 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250103133723/https://www.tatler.com/article/who-is-alexandra-saint-mleux-f1-wag-charles-leclerc-girlfriend |archive-date=3 January 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref> they announced their engagement in November 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-engaged-to-long-time-partner-alexandra-saint-mleux/10773305 |title=Charles Leclerc engaged to long-time partner Alexandra Saint Mleux |last=Harrington |first=Alex |date=2 November 2025 |website=[[Motorsport.com]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=2 November 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20251102190835/https://www.motorsport.com/f1/news/charles-leclerc-engaged-to-long-time-partner-alexandra-saint-mleux/10773305/ |archive-date=2 November 2025 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Leclerc served as a [[Olympic flame|torchbearer]] for the Monégasque leg ahead of the [[2024 Summer Olympics]], alongside [[Alexandra Coletti]], [[Xiaoxin Yang]], [[Rudy Rinaldi]], [[Prince Albert II]], and [[Princess Charlene]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.monaco-tribune.com/en/2024/06/prince-albert-ii-princess-charlene-charles-leclerc-monacos-olympic-torchbearers/ |title=Prince Albert II, Princess Charlene, Charles Leclerc: Monaco’s Olympic Torchbearers |last=Riu |first=Anaïs |date=17 June 2024 |work=Monaco Tribune |access-date=13 February 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240713040831/https://www.monaco-tribune.com/en/2024/06/prince-albert-ii-princess-charlene-charles-leclerc-monacos-olympic-torchbearers/ |archive-date=13 July 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> That year, he purchased a {{currency|3.1|USD}} million [[condominium]] in [[Miami]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/charles-leclerc-formula-1-racer-buys-unit-in-waterfront-miami-tower |title=Charles Leclerc, Formula 1 Racer, Buys Unit in Waterfront Miami Tower |last=Schultz |first=Katie |date=7 May 2024 |magazine=[[Architectural Digest]] |publisher=[[Condé Nast]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=0003-8520 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241006140832/https://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/charles-leclerc-formula-1-racer-buys-unit-in-waterfront-miami-tower |archive-date=6 October 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> Whilst leading the World Drivers' Championship, he entered the [[Historic Grand Prix of Monaco]] in [[2022 Historic Grand Prix of Monaco|2022]], where he crashed a [[Ferrari 312B3]]—driven by [[Niki Lauda]] in {{F1|1974}}—at ''[[Circuit de Monaco|La Rascasse]]'' following a [[brake]] failure.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/pictured-the-broken-brake-disc-that-caused-leclercs-monaco-crash/10305389 |title=Pictured: The broken brake disc that caused Leclerc's Monaco Historic GP crash |last=Noble |first=Jonathan |date=17 May 2022 |website=[[Autosport]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=8 September 2025 |issn=0269-946X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20240524203801/https://www.autosport.com/f1/news/pictured-the-broken-brake-disc-that-caused-leclercs-monaco-crash/10305389 |archive-date=24 May 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref> He owns several [[Ferrari]] cars, including custom versions of the [[Ferrari SF90 XX|SF90 XX]], [[Ferrari Daytona SP3|Daytona SP3]], and [[Ferrari Purosangue|Purosangue]].<ref>{{Cite magazine |url=https://news.dupontregistry.com/ferrari/charles-leclercs-brand-new-ferrari-sf90-xx-spotted-in-monaco/ |title=Charles Leclerc's Brand New Ferrari SF90 XX Spotted In Monaco |last=Aquistapace |first=Jordan |date=25 October 2024 |magazine=[[duPont Registry]] |publisher=[[Motorsport Network]] |access-date=22 February 2025 |issn=0890-362X |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241106232736/https://news.dupontregistry.com/ferrari/charles-leclercs-brand-new-ferrari-sf90-xx-spotted-in-monaco/ |archive-date=6 November 2024 |url-status=live}}</ref>

