{{Short description|Institution charged with local government and administration in Spain}}
{{Multiple issues|
{{Expand Spanish|topic=gov|Consejo comarcal|date=January 2012}}
{{More citations needed|date=February 2024}}
}}

The '''comarcal council''' ([[Catalan language|Catalan]]: ''consell comarcal'', [[Galician language|Galician]]: ''consello comarcal'', [[Aragonese language|Aragonese]]: ''concello comarcal'', [[Spanish language|Spanish]]: ''consejo comarcal''), also somewhat misleadingly referred to as ''[[Comarca|county council]]'', is a local administration and government body in the [[comarca]]s of some parts of [[Spain]], mostly in the [[Autonomous Community|autonomous communities]] of [[Catalonia]], [[Aragon]] and [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|the Basque Country]].

The comarcal council is normally constituted by representatives of the [[municipality|municipalities]] within the comarcal demarcation, who are elected according to law-regulated mechanisms.

==In Aragon==
{{see also | Comarcas of Aragon}}
{{Expand section|date=February 2024}}

===Membership of the councils===
Council membership of a comarca is allocated according to its population using the following table:<ref>{{cite web |url=https://elecciones.aragon.es/consejos-comarcales |title=Consejos comarcales &#124; Portal Elecciones |language=es |website=elecciones.aragon.es |date=7 February 2023 |publisher=[[Gobierno de Aragon]] |access-date=February 4, 2024}}</ref>
{| class="wikitable"
